,Recommended,251570,8581240,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,Crispy Liquids,"This game really puts into practice so well the concept of survival, scavenging, crafting and buildling - I really recommend it if you like this. Think about fallout 3 with zombies, hunting, and building/renovating a place of your own. Set in a post-apocalyptic landscape, the constructions players can set up are equally representative of a post-apocalyptic environment.If you heard of project zomboid, well if you ask me this is exactly that but better; the annoying needs are removed, the game plays fluently, the environment is already less buggy, and your freedom is more obvious. The crafting system is worked out very well as well: the game lists everything you can make with your inventory. When you choose something, it shows the shape but not the materials. Fill in the correct materials and you now know the recipe; so no need to fill it in yourself next time: just click what you want to craft (like in terraria). No need for a wiki indeed - great!"
