,Recommended,251570,29648670,Posted: 2 February,all,Patroll,"If you ever thought of trying out a survival genre but hate dealing with trolls, toxic community in general and defend your base 24/7, 7 Days to Die is a way to go. It's a zombie survival, open world game, heavily PvE oriented with flexible difficulty settings, great for both solo and co-op. Player's goal is to survive each week that gets progressively harder by fighting zombies and by scavenging wide variety of items which increase survivability and allow to improve your base. Speaking of bases, it's a requirement that you build one and keep improving its defenses if you plan on staying alive as during the 7th night, a horde of zombies will rush at the player. Staying alive is the ultimate goal, however dying isn't a definitive ""game over"". You only lose your stuff which can still get picked up and a bit of wellness (health + stamina) which is gained by consuming top tier food products. Sadly, that's basically it and it gets redundant over time. Hopefully the developers will come up an actual goal like Mojang did with the Ender Dragon in Minecraft, like e.g, waiting for a rescue chopper or building/scavenging aircraft parts to fix some sort of aircraft and get away before the 7th day or whatever... Gotta keep in mind the game is still in development. Currently it's really fun to play and I'd recommend it to anyone looking for a singleplayer/co-op survival genre game.Cheers to Bacon-Snack for this gift <3"
