76561198052395746,Not Recommended,251570,34579295,Posted: 29 August,all,Darth_Wayner,"Seeing as how I've logged over 800 hours in this game and I bought it on sale for $15, i've gotten entertainment at the price of about 2 cents an hour.   That alone means I should be giving this game a positive review, but since my review is meant to help new perspective players to decide whether to spend their money, I can't.  I loved (past tense) the hell out of this game.  However, alpha 16 is the last straw for me.  Every release seems to break the game worst than the last.  Frame rates grind to a halt, glaring gameplay issues like zombie spawns that got fixed 2 releases ago reappear.  Terrain generation glitches are broken in one release, fixed in the next, and then broken again in the next.  ""Creating player"" issue which completely prevents playing the game goes ignored.I've been playing this game since alpha 8.  The game peaked for me somewhere around A12.  The biggest issues i see are that the devs seem to be easily distracted and can't seem to focus on the end goal.  Example...they can't seem to make up their mind about how the player gathers resources.  When i first started playing, boulders on the surface would give iron, coal, and potassium nitrate when harvested.  That was removed in favor for underground nodes only.  That was subsequently changed to make certain mineable materials specific to certain biomes, that was changed again, and now we're back to where it all started.  There are numerous other examples of this.  That wouldn't bother me as much if the glaring issues like performance, lack of story or end game content, etc were getting addressed.  For pete's sake guys, not every player will like the system, but this will be true no matter what you do.  Develop a system, stick with it, and keep your eye on the end goal of finishing a game sometime this decade by not breaking what you've already done at each release.Speaking of ""each release"", they are down to a new release about every 9 months now.  At the rate of 1 step forward and 2 steps back at every release, they'll simply never get there.  As of A16, I can no longer recommend this game."
