,Recommended,251570,29581013,Posted: 29 January,all,The Nates Templar,"Let me begin with a few basic overview marks.The graphics aren't the best, sure. They're not fallout or dying light quality, but they don't need to be and they're still quite good for what the game is, a unity game. Still a great set of assets and a hell of a lot better than minecraft or unturned but with the same or I'd say even more freedom and crafting options.The sound makes up for the graphics when it comes to atmosphere, seriously, they got some of the sounds down really well, the hair raising clicks of a spider zombie, the growling and barks of the zombie dogs (I Hate these things), the nerve jittering sound of a wondering zombie cop, the music's ehish, not sustained and more just used in short bursts to indicate day/night/horde cycle.Now on gameplay!This is where this baby get's most of it's points. If you're into crafting games and survival, this is the game for you, with everything from hunger and thirst, to body temperature, infections and illness. You have to battle these things as well as the zombie hordes. Detailed and awesome, don't think you can just stand around in the rain and you'll be ok, your temperature will start dropping sharply if oyu're not wearing the right clothing. Clothing, just another aspect of the level of depth, so many layers and tiers, the fact that even guns and power tools are made up of individual working components and such, SO much depth and detail to this game it doesn't even need a story, survive and build is all it needs.A first hour or two Experience in 7 days to die:Have spawned on a road in the desert with some basics, a can of stagg err, I mean cragg? (something) chilli, a jar of water (It says it's a bottle but it's a jar god dammit), a flaming stick (torch), a bandage a backpack and underpants. For some reason I remembered my backpack and flaming torch, but only had time to put on underpants before the apocalypse hit.  Game tells me to make a primitive stone axe. Noted. Need wood. Start punching a tree into submission, eventually it yields beneath my mighty fists and coughs up some wood. I see my next victim, a stone. I charge at it, arms flailing and swinging wildly at bits of grass as I go. WHAP! whap whap whap whap whap, 40 punches later the rock still stands beneath my awesome power and has yielded little. I find a few stones on the ground, enough to combine with the wood and grass punchings to make an axe. I craft the axe, AH HA! I hold it aloft, I have evolved, I am man, I have made a tool. First course of action, charge the mighty rock beast with my newly created tool and beat it into submissions. I hit the rock repeatedly, feeling it crumble to my will offering up it's many goodies until CRACK, it becomes dust beneath my mighty tool! I am man, I am unbeatable! (Low grumbled growling) ZOMBIE! Ha, a moment ago I would have been zombie chow, but I have my trusty stone axe, ready to beat down this zombie. CHAAAARRRGGEE!! whack whack whack, Take that zombie I scream as I wildly hack at it, engaging it from behind. The zombie stops and turns, responding to these attacks unfavourably. OH GOD IT'S EATING ME, IT'S EATING ME OH GOD WHY, WHY DID YOU FAIL ME SO TERRIBLY AXE. I perish in an horrific fashion. My soul rises above me, to watch the zombie chow down only to be zapped and snapped back into the body of another survivor! I can only assume my spirit has possessed him because he TOO is wondering the wilderness with little more than a pair of underpants and a backpack. I start to walk back to my old body to see what has become of it. I trudge forward, barely noticing the dimming light of day until the sun has almost set. Night time approaches! I should find somewhere safe to hole up for the night before I can varily trudge to retrieve my stone axe for sentimentality reasons. A town, that should be a good spot to find some gear and hole up til morning, let's try there. OH GOD, NO, NO, ZOMBIE DOGS, WHY OH WHY THEY'RE SO FAST AND ANGRY OH GOD THEY'RE EATING ME annnnnnd death, floating away watching myself become Zomdog food. Well then, back in my underpants in the middle of nowhere wearing nothing but the baseball cap I found near my spawn point.Ok so, time to make a stone axe....11/10 Still addicted almost 200 hours in."
