76561197999039395,Recommended,251570,25986188,"Posted: 11 October, 2016",all,Rei,"Oh look yet another zombie game.  That being said it's a really really good zombie game.  After 1300+ hours of game play I am still enjoying this game.  I have owned the game since Alpha 6.  We're currently on Alpha 15 and The Fun Pimps continue to make this game better and better.  On the rare occasion they add something that makes the game worse and the community complains, they tweek it and find a way to make the game fun without making it easy.  If you like murdering zombies, building, scavenging, crafting or trading, you'll probably like this game."
76561197992949754,Recommended,251570,15820029,"Posted: 13 May, 2015",all,Egon Spengler,"This game is so cool! I'm not worthy! I'm not worthy!No seriously, this game is excellent. For being an alpha game still under heavy development, it is fun. Several friends and I have made a few multiplayer servers to play on for days to weeks at a time. The developers are very active in the community with the players. While they do have a planned agenda, they do accept ideas from the players or suggestions and incorporate them into the game. This game will also be open for players to mod.While the graphics aren't the best I've ever seen, they aren't too shabby and they are friendly to low-end PC's. There are still a lot of bugs to be fixed. The content at the moment is a little limited in terms of building materials and the different types of buildings/structures that you encounter. However, they are consistently adding new content. I expect the finished product game to be nothing like the alpha I started playing a few months ago (for better or worse).Gameplay is survival horror rpg. You start with nothing and build your way up to having consistent food, water, weapons, and shelter. Alternatively, you could be a nomad and live off of the buildings and structures you encounter on your journey. Either way, beware of the 7 day night horde. Health, stamina, hunger, thirst, and general wellness are all taken into account while playing. Negative things such as becoming infected by a zombie, broken legs, dysentery, and bleeding out are all things that you will have to deal with during your travels.The zombies in this game are a force to be reckoned with. During the day, they are slow and can be dealt with individually if one is careful. If one becomes alert to your presence, many in the area will soon come to investigate. Fighting one zombie can easily turn into running away from fifteen. When the sun sets, the game becomes a whole new animal. Since the zombies run full speed at night, things can be absolutely terrifying. The sheer suspense of hearing the zombies search for you at night can be unnerving. Or the times where you are looting a house and you accidentally slam the cabinet doors in the kitchen only to realize that they heard you and they are coming.Did you ever wish that a game like Minecraft had formidable enemies that wouldsmellyou,hearyou, andhuntyou?Enemies that will dismantle your base and annihilate you if you didn't take proper precautions to protect yourself?That is this game."
