,Recommended,251570,35043966,Posted: 18 September,all,Krevan,"Been keeping an eye on this game for a couple years, but never pulled the trigger and bought it. Finally did that just over a week ago, and absolutely no regrets. Love the crafting, the building, and even the digging. I'm a huge fan of underground bunkers, and the idea of hiding in (almost) plain sight, so when I found out you could dig, and live, underground, I instantly was hooked. The idea that you might be passing a large corn field, and there could be a massive complex of tunnels and rooms underground is awesome.On top of the vanilla flavor of the game, you can also mod it to add more features. I've looked up and found mods that allow you to have classes which automatically give you specialized skills, so you can jump right in and play your way. You can find different User Interfaces, or even write your own one, with the ability to completely edit the game's XML files. The best part of the implementation of modding in 7D2D, is that if you edit your XML files, you can still join other people, and not worry about getting banned for altered files, because when you're logged into a server, you're using the files from that server, instead of the ones on your system.Of course a game in Early Access like this one, doesn't come without flaws. Above all, in my opinion, are the animations and graphics. While your primary perspective during your time in 7D2D is First Person, there are occasions, when playing with others, that you notice that characters don't have look up and look down animations in Third Person, so when a friend is pointing a rifle at your face, he might actually be looking straight up in the air, trying to figure out where an air drop just landed. Also, when riding a minibike, later in the game, you notice a stuttering that, at first, appears to be FPS lag, but after closer inspection, it appears to be a game sync issue, that makes riding a bike hard to get used to at first.All in all, I highly suggest getting this game. I paid $25 for it, and at the time of writing this review, I've gotten more value out of this game, than any other game I've paid for recently. The price per hour is unbelievable."
