76561197965271130,Not Recommended,251570,26373423,"Posted: 2 November, 2016",all,Irreverence,"I bought this game on sale for 10€ since it's PvE style offers a different take on the well saturated open world survival genre. The review is based on Alpha 15.Pros:+PvE approach offers the comfort of playing on a sandbox server at day and handing you big scale fights at night (especially on the 7th night a week).+Landscaping/Mining. This is something that a lot of the other survival games are missing.+Characterleveling and skillsystem.+Randomly generated maps and a static map.+Quests.Cons:-Bad optimization. I get 40fps and below (GTX970/FX8370/16gb@1080p) next to big buildings and hordes of zombies which doesn't change when lowering graphics settings.-Graphics can't compete with other games of the genre.-Controls aren't fully customizable.-Very few special infected.-Somewhat clunky and unfinished UI.-No PvP due to small servers and the way the game works.-Bad and easy to abuse AI.-You will reach the point of ""What now? Why am I doing this?"" fairly early in this game if you aren't into straight up sandboxing.Conclusion:While playing this game I couldn't stop thinking about how Rust does everything (apart from the Zombies obviously) better - whether it's looks, optimization, controls, interface or the actual gameplay. It's not DayZ-bad but there's still a whole lot to be done for a game that has already spent more than 3 years in Early Access.The real buzzkill to me is what is supposed to make this game different: PvE base defending. Having 50 generic zombies literally pile up on your doorstep and slaughtering them 1 by 1 through holes in the walls just isn't my understanding of a fun and well thought out game concept. Also there are obstacles zombies can't get accross and if you feel like you won't be able to hold your base you can just hop out and kite them all away until the night is over since zombies won't attack empty bases if there are players around.I recommend to not buy this game at this stage althoughthis stagecould mean never as many other EA survival games have shown."
