76561198010545742,Recommended,251570,13868920,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,CrossFire,"I normaly dont spend much time on reviews of games becouse i tend to play them, but this game deserves it.Its been what, over 2 years now since i bought the game? I pretty much got it when it got on steam, and wow what a great 2~ish years it has been.If you are looking at a game in early access, you want one thing, and thats propper development.Well stop looking since this game had exactly that and much much more.In the years i played it up till now, this game has always been great, and it just keeps getting better with every update. This review is for version 14.5, but i will also take the development in the past years into account.Ill give an overview of pros and cons, then a summary of when to buy this game, and last some game tips and tricks for when you start off.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Pros;+ Large open world, multiple biomes each with a unique feel to them+ Interesting, realistic and versatile crafting system+ Great gameplay (controlls, movement etc)+ Skill and level system+ Good grafics, and music+ Lots of  tools and weapons, for everyone something (melee brawling, guns blazing or stealthy, you can play how you like)+ Lots of loot and building materials+ Weather system, that changes depending on the biome your in.+ Set world, random generated worlds, single player and multiplayer (with easy to set up server)+ Propper development, every update makes the game betterCons;- Its an early access game, meaning you might encounter some bugs, and saved games might not work after major updates.- Loading screen takes long when you start the game up.The few bugs or gliches that i have encountered in the past years are few and got fixed in a matter of days sometimes even hours.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------When should you buy this game?--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------If you like Zombie games, Survival, Crafting, Building, Lots of loot, the option to play the way you want, and a game that keeps getting better with every update, this is the game for you.If i had to compare this game with other games, i would say it reminds me of Minecraft, and survival games like DayZ, Rust etc.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Below i will give some tips on how to start off, beware of MINOR SPOILERS!--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Last updated: April 2016---------------------------When you start off in the world you get only the most bastic needs, a bit of water, and food, a torch, and a bandage.First thing you want to get as fast as posible, is a stone axe, the game tells you in a little tuturial what to do. You need to pick up stones laying arround with the button ''E'' or hit some boulders with your fist (left mouse button), then you need some grass, hit it with your fist to pick some up.Then you need wood, any tree or bush will give you some when hit.You can craft the stone axe in your crafting menu by pressing ''TAB''.The stone axe is a multi purpose tool that is your new friend, you can use it as a club to smash zombie heads, use it as an axe to chop down trees, and a pickaxe to get stone.Make sure you pick up a lot of stone, wood, and grass becouse you will be making lots of stone axes.You might want a save way to kill a zombie here and there, the bow is a cheap and easy item for this.You will need some wood, and grass to build the bow, the arrows can be made with stone, wood and feathers.Feathers can be found in bird nest that are scattered on the floor here and there (and in or on some buildings)Food/Water; you can fill glass bottles and empty cans with water from rivers and lakes, also you can cook the water on a campfire so you wont get sick.Food can be cooked in different ways, altough not all food needs to be cooked to savely eat it, all canned food can be eaten right away.Surviving is your main priority at the start of the game, you want to loot as much as you can and stay away from zombies, getting hurt early in the game is a bad idea, and dieing (if you dont have perma death on) will lower your wellness, wich is the maximum hitpoints and stamina you have.Only take out the lone zombie here and there if they are in the way of a building you want to loot, by using a bow and/or using the hit and run tacktic. Try hitting zombies in the head.You can find Cloth fragment by looting, breaking down clothing you find, and by crafting it from cotton plants (those bushes with white fluffy balls on it). You will need it for making bandages, and first aid bandages in case you get hurt.Where to survive your first night: Its best to find 2-4 buildings together, and choose the highest one. There you would want to make your first base at the top floor or roof.While one of the  buildings will be your starting base, the other buildings can provide food and materials to survive.If you play with a seed or random generated game, you might have to do with what you find, always try to be from the ground so zombies cant reach you straight away. (shops have a flat roof with a ladder at the back and will do just fine)Every 3 days, unless set differently a plane will fly over and drop a supply crate, this always contains resources like antibiotics, medkits and sometimes other suplies.If you get infected you have 3 days to live unless you take antibiotics or honey, so make sure you get that crate, since its a great help.Usefull loot: Canned food, Water, Medical suplies, Mining helmet (great protection and flashlight that you can turn on with ''F'')Tips!If you are having trouble with surviving at night, instead of setting the dificulty lower, you can also set the zombies to always walk. As default the zombies run when its dark and walk when in (day) light. I always have them set to walk becouse it feels to me like zombies should walk.This however does not affect zombie dogs.Dont go into cities or any big cluster of buildings, more zombies and also stronger zombies spawn here.Every 7 days at night time a horde will come for you, if you are having trouble with them or find them anoying, either keep moving when they come or go back to menu when they have spawned and then go back into the game, and they will be gone.___________________________________________I hope this review was usefull to you."
