76561198004625244,Recommended,251570,16400606,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,Lord Kek,"Others have said it and I will say it as well: this game is the best zombie survival, open world crafting game ever made.Before I begin my review, can I just say - THIS GAME IS HARD WHEN YOU FIRST START OUT!When you first start out, you don't know what to craft. You don't know what specific survival actions you need to take to make life easy. So, you just run around like a chicken with its head cut off. And then you complain saying the game is hard. I put in 30 hours before I understood some of the basic survival mechanisms to increase my survival actions per minute.IF YOU'RE FRUSTRATED BECAUSE THE GAME IS TOO HARD, PLAY ON A PVE SERVER WITH LOW DIFFICULTY SUCH AS 3.Do NOT do PVP if you are frustrated about the difficulty of the game. Seriously. You are doing the game developers, the community and yourself a disservice. Stay away from PvP. It's not worth it. Once you've put in 30 hours on a PvE server, start on a PvP server with low zombie difficulty and high loot. This is what I am currently at and I love it.If you don't care about the difficulty and are willing to endure the learning curve against greater odds of difficult PvP, then by all means, knock yourself out.Part of what makes this game great is that its potential is actually getting converted to reality piece by piece with each patch (unlike other games we know of..) Also, the developers are awesome and connected with the player base and are determined to make it the best zombie open world survival game.>Crafting system? Awesome.>Fully destrucible / constructible world? Yep.>Want a scary, atmospheric environment where you could die any second from hunger, thirst or zombies? Yep.>Want to build a mighty underground kingdom that no one knows about? Go right ahead.>Want to build a great castle fortress above ground? You can do that - just be prepared to deal with the attention.>Want to build obstacle courses for zombies? You got it!>Want to play like CS:GO? Go right ahead. You will be known on the server as the local serial killer.>Want to play like a pirate without a permanent base? You can do that. Just write down the coordinates of your buried loot.>Want to play survival with your friends on hellish difficulty? You can do that. You better hope your friends don't tip off the zombies.>Want a server customized to your tastes and preferences? YES. This is actually freaking awesome.>Want to survive in a cold, snowy wasteland? You can.>Want to survive in a scorching hot desert with little water? You can.>Want to survive in a forest with wild boars and elk to kill? You can.>Want to construct base defenses (traps, thick walls, etc..)? You can.>Want to create hidden chambers and passage ways? You can.>Want to get in gun fights with other players? You can.Bottom line is, this game, even in early access, is incredible. Yes, it has some bugs. They're frustrating sometimes, but not game-breaking."
