,Recommended,251570,16456485,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Black Puppet,"=HEADS UP=I had a review before this one about the game being good. This stays of course but i had to clarify some points and fix this old messy review that i made before.=INFO ABOUT THE REVIEW=1. This review might be a bit longer.2. This review is about my point of view and opinion. [If you disagree on a certain point or want to correct me: Be reasonable or i will ignore your comment.]=REVIEW=This game is just amazing. Lets start with that and go right to the first point. Most of the Zombiesurvival games promise you so many things. They promise you a great Craftingsystem. They promise you that you can build your own base. They promise you intense gameplay and that you have to stay on your toes all the time.And most of the time we do not get what we pay for. We do not get the great Craftingsystem. We do not get the cool buildings. We dont have to watch out or get killed in one second because the game is so unbalanced that you literally cant stay alive long enough to even get some kind of weapon.This game is different. Before the actual danger begins you have a full day, that you can configure (more of that later) of getting supplies up to build or just barricade you. You might be even able to find something really usefull in a nearby house or little village. And you might even be able to find a higher tier tool. And that is important. With A11 we got a new system for the tools. The longer you play the better you can craft your tools. The better you can craft the better the tools get. More damage to a block or enemy. More durability and such. But you can also find them. That will help you greatly in some cases. If you are at the beginning the pickaxe and the axe in good quality can help you greatly. Without you will have to go on just like normaly and take what the game gives you.But you have to be fast about what you are doing since there are Zombies everywhere and it is slowly turning to nighttime. But what happens when the night hits? Well lets just call it literally Hell. The Zombies begin to run and with that i mean every Zombie. On the hardest settings they are even able to sense you in your base through the walls and begin to break down the blocks you have placed or the blocks that are naturally in place.You have survived your first night? Congratulations. But this isnt over. Because now you have 6 more days. 6 more days to die on the 7nth day. And why? Well you remember that this is a horde survival? Well make sure that you are ready to face the horde. Not to speak of the infamous ""Day 14"" horde. That was a nice time when i suddenly heard... Oh wait i shouldnt tell you more. Heh Heh.But now we should head to the performance of the game. For my personal prefference the performance could be better but it still isnt bad. My PC is decent and so are the parts and i get a good 40 up to 50 fps with higher settings. The newer Unity engine makes the game even more beautiful than it was before. But what about the settings?Well of course you can change everything you would need. There are some things that i would love to have implemented but the game is not finished yet so we will see what comes in the future. But lets go over to the main settings that you have to set up your game.First you have a selection of which world you want to use. You can choose between the handcrafted world they present with the game and a world that is randomly generated. With both worlds you can configure everything else about it though. Like if you want a longer day or night. Or if Zombies should run at all. How hard the game should be for the world and so on and so forth. You can change everything that is important about the gameplay."
