,Recommended,251570,11186345,"Posted: 11 July, 2014",all,TheChaosmachine,"Since the beginning of time, I have been a zombie fan. I have all the movies and try to play all the games. However, I have always been wanting a game where it was me and some friends surviving against hordes of the living dead. I have played many games with zombies, and have lots many, but this game is the closest I have ever been to the perfect zombie game.I have played several zombie games, across many platforms, and I have spent 10x more in this game than any other. I love the combination of the survival aspect and the buidling aspect. I love that the zombies actually pose a threat and you can't just hide in your home. With the combo of the Zombies and the physics based gameplay, you must be innovative in your attempts at survival. You cant' just pillar up and wait out the night. You can't just dig a hole and everything will be alright. The zombies will come for you.I also love the fact that the devs have allowed options inside the game. For example, my current server I play on is walking dead style. Walkers Only, No specials. You can set length of days, if the zombies run or not (when they run too), loot probability, and so much more. No matter your style, you can tweak the game to your satisfaction.However, I do want to emphasize that this game is Alpha. You will find bugs. You will have to start over several times. Things will go wrong and you will get frustrated. Very frustrated. You will probably rage quit a few times. I have. However, each time I do, I soon come back for more. In fact, on my server, I am known to be the one who finds bugs and to get stuck in them.As the game stands now, it's a 7 out of 10 for me. Which, honestly for me, that's a very good score. Very few games score any higher."
