h zombies.It's a decent tent, i made a door and blocked up the windows, it will have to do until i find a real place.The last 2 days were awful, man :(Day 6GOD DAMNIT. It's the middle of the night. I just wrote the diary for day 5 and went back to playing.Y'know how I mentioned that I was a damned fool? I PUNCHED THE WINDOW IN MY TENT (Yes it had glass pane windows)This may not seem bad to you but the game has gravity. The entire roof fell down.I've had this tent for 5 minutes.Went hunting, killed a few rabbits and a pig.Cut down some trees, started melting down some iron to make a gun safe. I want one because I need storage and gun safes are the biggest kind.I started building a little shelter across the road  from my campsite. I hope I can build a huge base eventually. I'll start a fence tomorrow/So it's about to tick over to Day 7 and a giant bee thing flew up to me. It was obviously an enemy because it was marked on the map. I shot it down with my hunting rifle. It didn't drop anything or even leave a body. I'll look it up on the wiki because I've never seen one before and i'm tripping out right now.Edit: Hornets. It doesn't say anything about them being rare so I don't know why I only saw my first one on Day 6Day 7I hope this game isn't literal and I actually suvive today.So I went for a walk, found some guns in a building down the road. Nothing much else.Today was very uneventful until I got attacked by a zombie and got infected. Of course, I didn't know I was infected until I did some research.Thankfully you can craft antibiotics and fix it.Unfortunately that's not easy.I needed to scavenge some moldy bread, some potassium nitrate powder and a beaker then cook it on a camp fire.I had no beaker or bread. Crap. I've got the camp fire and the potassium nitrate from cracking open some rocks though.So I bolted to the nearest building I hadn't touched and bang! 2 beakers and 3 guns. Nice!On the way out the door I accidently pressed 'E' to search some garbage and you'll never guess what's in the garbage. Mouldy bread.I couldn't beleive my luck. I cooked it up right then and there, took my meds and went on my way with some left over. Today was a good day.I logged off before the sun went down so I'll edit later.Edit: Nothing major, cooked a bunch of meat and some more antibiotics, which was lucky because I got infected again :/Day 8This morning was boring as hell, I just cooked and stuff. Still haven't built a new place for myself. Tent's just fine. In the middle of the day a huge♥♥♥♥♥horde moved through my camp. Like 40 zombies man. I have screenshots to show for it. I killed them all and was looking for anything useful on their bodies when I heard a plane fly over. I looked around and saw it drop 2 crates! I bolted to the first one, nothing major, bandages, food, 2 antibiotics. Then I went over to the second crate. Medical supplies for days: 50 antibiotic pills and 20 bandages. I'm in heaven.Night's coming as I write this. I'll keep you posted.So another horde attacked. On the same day. It as even bigger this time, I think. I took another screenshot but I had killed most of them beforehand.Day 9Another horde attack in the morning, nothing major today. Made some leather clothing, collected heaps of water because I didn't have any. Planning on starting a farm.The tent is pretty much wrecked."
