76561197960446481,Recommended,251570,33727483,Posted: 22 July,all,BygoneSanity,"One of the best creative survival sandbox type games out there at the moment. The developers are constantly working on it, and the updates are consistent and usually include quite a bit of new content and bug fixes. I give a lot of credit to the developers for really keeping in touch with the community to improve the future of the game.From these reviews I notice that the few negative reviews out there mostly seem to be about weapon damage and realism. I think some of these players are looking at the game in the wrong light. Besides being in Early Access, 7 Days to Die does have a skill system and weapon tiers. You will increase your skills from building and fighting, which will allow you to do more damage. As your skills go up, your character will level up and you will gain points to unlock more perks which include extra damage, increased stamina and regeneration, new recipes and tons of other perks.TL;DR: Great game. Awesome to play with friends. Geared more towards long term survival where you need to tier up your gear and skills, be a bit creative, explore, scavenge. If you want to just smash zombies in 1 hit right off the bat, then you might want to look at something else."
,Recommended,251570,31457348,Posted: 30 April,all,redtacular,"Overall(tl;dr)It's a bit rough around the edges still. They're improving it albeit at a slow pace. I would definitly recommend this game to other people despite the unfinished state.GameplayThe game itself is very unforgiving at the early stages unless you are aware of what you're doing. There are tons of crafting recipes and a lot of oppertunities to unleash your inner creativity with base building. The combat is solid, and manageable even at higher difficulties. The end game is not really polished and once you get far enough in you will become more or less unkillable.GraphicsThe graphics are not the most crisp out there, nor are they the most up to date. However in my opinion it's at the point where it's not bad, and it's not great, somewhere in between. The gameplay more than makes up for it.I would recommend this game, and give it a solid 8/10"
