76561198040340563,Recommended,251570,16021588,"Posted: 26 May, 2015",all,rustbucket80,"I am reviewing this game based on the Early Access version as of 5/27/14 -My playtime on this account is not representative of my actual time with this game -I like 7 Days to Die. The game works as advertised and has a great track record of consistent and substantial updates. Personally, I find the zombies to be a little tough to kill and the zombie dogs to be a bit overkill but if you like your survival zombie games more on the challenging side then this should appeal to you. Lots of things to craft, building a fort and surrounding it with defenses is a good time. You can even mine for ore like that one game (you know which one). Playing with friends is fun as well and I have not had any large issues with lag or network connectivity.The only negative thing I can say about this game, which isn't so much the game itself but the Early Access aspect of many games, is that you will play it and get tired of it long before the game is completed. Again, this is my opinion. This is a solid game as is right now and it is good. But that just makes me want to wait to play it until I can get the full experience.  So while I have spent a significant time with the game and it's systems, I have not tried to dig deep into the games meaty bits.Overall, I would strongly recommend a purchase; especially if you have a buddy or two to survive with."
