,Recommended,251570,16240557,"Posted: 7 June, 2015",all,SuicideBars,"A really well-constructive zombie game, giving you the option of playing solo or going to PVE/PVP. This game goes from crafting out of any way possible to get the item you desire; while still trying to maintain hidden from the zombies lurking around (which have special abilities as night emerges). I really enjoyed exploring the map even though i died almost 11 times to finally understand how almost everything works. The crafting is great, the experience is great, but just like every other game, there are some flaws. Here are some pros and cons:Pros:- The lot of changing settings is enormous, you can literally change things on how you want it as far as how gruesome the zombies are and etc.- Endless possibilities of random maps.- Great crafting and building system (able to construct and reconstruct anything)- Loot respawn ( Searching around for items can sometimes give you pieces for a nice weapon such as a shotgun)- Hunt/Plant ( Animals sometimes lurk around which you can kill for food or crafting materials, also plantation is available)- Unique zombie experience ( Zombies are able to sense; either from you making noise or having food that attracts them. Also the zombies are able to run fast when night hits)- Great developers and feedbackCons:-Dated graphics ( This is still on alpha)-Zombies are a bit gruesome at night, you can't outrun them as their stamina exceeds yours 3x as much =-=.-Bad community ( Just like in Rust and Dayz, You will always find a phsychopath trying to kill you)-Map design ( Just talking about the map showing you the world, hard to find houses and such with a map like that)-Lag? ( Seen people complain about this. This game runs fine to me though)- Reset ( As the game goes through updates you will find your saved game wiped out, need to start fresh)- Bugs ( Still in alpha so expect it). This are some bugs to look out for though:Breaking a leg when falling/jumping 4ftObstacles sometimes standing in your wayUnable to look at inventory or map for a few minutes. ( Happens to me not too often but still does)I haven't played much so this review will be updated as i go along exploring the game and looking for bad or good things about it. It's a really fun game overall, i had fun playing it. You will die alot as you learn about the game but it will be worth it. Went from living on a self-dugged hole to a house that i'm at recently, secured with a wooden door and a couch for extra protection, i say that's an improvement lol."
