76561197961909777,Recommended,251570,9921597,"Posted: 24 April, 2014",all,The Major,"Below this is the current review. I opted to leave the original as well for reference.------ORIGINAL REVIEW: VERSION 7.11----------I played this game for a little bit when I first purchased it, just before alpha 6 was released. I was impressed. I played again later, around version 7.11, and I can say without a doubt that I enjoy this game. Having to take structural integrity into account to make sure your buildings and mining tunnels don't collapse on you rather then just as eye candy is a very welcomed plus. While there is equipment degredation and normal needs (food, hydration, stamina,)  I have never felt that these were too prevalent, yet it's just taxing enough to make you actively think about it.In the end, it will be very interesting to see how this game turns out, but from what I'm seeing right now... We're all in for a very good game.---------NEW REVIEW: VERSION 12.4---------Ok, I've put a good amount of time in the game between each patch. So far I am greatly impressed with the changes that the team has made. The game is starting to take shape and it leaves so much potential for mods when it's done!  But, this isn't much a review without actually reviewing it, so here we go.Graphics: As I said in the opening, they have upgraded the engine and it now supports better graphics as well as weather effects such as rain, fog and snow. Unfortunately, for one reason or another, there seems to be some kind of issue with high end video cards and the game. That, however, will be patched out soon enough. The night sky looks great; first thing a friend of mine said when he saw it was ""Woah, check out that blue nebula!""Sound: The ambience is much, much better then it was before. Not saying it's the greatest in the world, mind you, but it's much better none-the-less. Before, it would just repeat the same one or two ambient noises. While they aren't 100% ""there"" yet, the new ones at least make sense and fit the time and area. Game sounds, such as shooting, could use a touchup, but it still sounds good enough and I believe there are plans to improve upon that. In fact, I think they recently updated the reloading sounds as well gunfire.Replayability: A lot. There have been quite a few world clears (due to patches) over the time I've played this and I generally have at least 1 SP game and 1 MP game going on in tandum. Even now, with so many of the promised mechanics not yet in the game, there is still many ways you can change up the playstyle to keep it interesting. Things like: ""This time I'm going melee only!"", ""I can only use a crossbow! That means I can't actually kill a zombie until I get one!"" and ""I cannot eat canned food or drink purified water. I must eat only cooked food and tea.""I don't like to give numerical ratings due to the misconception that ""7/10 = crap"" that reviewers such as Game Informer do. However, if I absolutely had to I'd give 7 Days to Die (in its current state) a ...7/10(5 = average, so 6 = slightly above average and 7 = above average)Can't wait until it's finished."
