,Recommended,251570,9958702,"Posted: 27 April, 2014",all,Praxius,"I bought this game about two weeks ago now after playing Rust for months on end (since January) At the time I wasn't sure if I'd go for DayZ, Rust, or 7 Days to Die (which a lot of players seem to be stuck in deciding)I went for Rust because it was the cheaper of the three and seemed to be in the middle of 7 Days and DayZ in regards to gameplay. It was fun and entertaining and I loved building a base from starting out with not much. However, the gameplay got repetitive, it involved a lot of play time in order to maintain everything you owned and to try and make sure nobody blasted your base and took your stuff while you were offline. As a father and single income worker, my free time for games is limited. The other issue is that updates for Rust have been very lacking lately and it has just become a bit stale. DayZ seemed even worse with updates, and the amount of content in the game is very lacking in comparison to 7 Days and Rust. It looks pretty, but eye candy can only go so far.7 Days to Die is impressive and deserves a larger player base than it currently has. I was originally put off by the graphics in its early versions a few months back, but that was clearly a mistake. Besides, the graphics have been getting better and currently are about par with Rust. The reason I can see for the lesser quality graphics is that they focused so much more on the gameplay and content and it all works very well, especially for an Alpha.The other issue I had with 7 Days to Die back in January was its price, which was the most expensive out of the three. Now it has dropped in price and is cheaper than DayZ.And for someone who doesn't have a lot of free time to play games, having a single player / offline mode to play is great. The Zombies are very effective and keep you on your toes. With the new update coming with the motion capture animations for them, it's just going to get a hell of a lot better.Now, let's say you get the basic stuff to survive for the night, or so you think, now you gotta find a place to settle down. There's a little neighborhood with some houses. Smack a few zombies around and drop them, ok, so this house is empty and I'll call it my own. I'll put my stuff in the fridge, make some storage boxes, start crafting a few things. Hmmm.... it's getting night time now. Guess I won't be going far. Wait, what's that noise? Footsteps? Screaming and odd breathing?? Well they won't find me in here, I'll just keep quiet and put out the fire. Uh oh, they're getting close. They're on the doorstep. Now they're banging on the door and screaming! Oh crap, the windows smashed in the back. Jebus! They're bashing through the walls!! Is that a Zombie Bee I hear? Oh MY GOD THEY'RE INSIDE!!!! THEY'RE RUNNING AT ME!!! HOW DID THEY FIND ME!!?? CRAP THEY SMELLED THE FOOD IN MY BACKPACK!!! AAAAAHHHHH!!!!!^My first night.I did survive though :P"
