76561197981548323,Recommended,251570,22079082,"Posted: 26 March, 2016",all,Shonkawakan,"This is a really great game of its kind and it's always been right from the 1st of my runs in it more than a year ago. Maybe even unmatched in things it's focused on.No storyline or directly given quests(update - it has some optional quests now), it's just about surviving under harsh conditions in the post apocalypse world full of walking dead (Or running dead, depending on which settings you prefere). Kind of a fine quality surviving, which feels like a perfect subsitute to the storyline and quests as trying to make it as far as you can becomes a storyline and quests by itself.Which ever stage of this game's developement  in eary access i've tried so far, they all were a damn great survival experience. Even at times when some other people were not content with any bugs, lags or just changes brought by an update.The only issue worth mentioning i had myself was that it can't be normally  played on full hard difficulty with always running zombies from the start, there's just no chance to survive with such settings (doubtful that i just failed to find the way to do this) long enough to call it surviving. Since i've picked warrior(4th of 6) difficulty with Zs running at nights and walking at days and feral as my  regular one, there's been nothing to complain about, except my own mistakes.The game is about being spawned on the map naked and bare-handed, and then collecting resources, making yourself some basic tools, weapons and clothes, building your base, hunting, growing plants and fighting zombies.There are quite branchy crafting and building menus there and lots of recipes of advanced staff you will eventually find looting different containers and dead bodies.Recrafting things brings you some slightly better staff each time you do this.No sleeping option, but there's always a lot of things to do at night, except maybe first 2 or 3 nights when you don't have enough resources in your inventory to craft or build something. I just punch a would frame or smth else then to get some additional exp. points to the athletics skill before Zs show up and provide some entertainment (good time to explore the crafting menu, too) . Otherwise the length of night may be adjusted to end at 02.00 e.g., never done it myself  though, it's 06.00 by default.The number of Zs in your vicinity eventually grows bigger, starting from the 7th night you have to deal with an attack of a whole big horde of them once a week, which gets stronger every time, so you need to constantly improve your equipment and fortifications.The game can be played solo or in PVE or PVP multiplayer. There's a good default map of a reasonable size or you can choose playing on a randomly generated endless map.Food and water gauge and environmentally triggered effects like cold, heat, being set on fire, a couple of deseases, bleeding, being stunned by a slap from a zombie or getting your leg sprained or broken or whatever else, are all of crucial meaning, each brings you special trouble and requires special treament or action.In fact, there's too many good things to tell about this game, but that would soon degrade down to unnecessary spoilers or epic episodes from author's own in-game experience. You better try it yourself, that's a must have if you're into fighting Zs and surviving.PS Just remember to find a safe place to hide or convenient to defend, a bow and several dozens of arrows before it's 22.00 if you set Zs as running at nights:)),3 block long 3 high wall of  wood frames upgraded with wood and  a little scrap iron if you have some, with a row or two of spikes on the ground around it was enough for first couple of nights until the last update but now it seems to be 4 high, optionally with unupgraded frames or ramp frames(to be able to remove one to shoot down through the gap) around the top, and you will need 4 or 5 high, 3 or 4 thick and 3 long upgraded(as much as you can) wall with frames around the top to survive the first couple of hordes(days 7 and 14). A friend of mine says Zs can't dig down, so another option for spending nights is having an underground shelter with level(not a slope e.g) and as hard as possible terrain above it. Best of all if it's 2 block thick at least, fortified with a layer of upgraded wood frames and with support pillars (avoid flights longer then 3-4 blocks, to prevent the ceiling from falling down on your head). The entrance should be stopped up and levelled with the surface and you shoudn't be close to it when Zs show up..PPS English isn't my native, my apologies for any inadvertent errors i could have made."
