,Recommended,251570,15036826,"Posted: 24 March, 2015",all,PrimeCutt,"About 80 hours in I'm still nowhere near done playing this game. If you love making forts then you will love this game. Making a fort takes a labor of love and doesn't happen over night like most voxel-based games. Having a good fort means something and is all the more rewarding.I feel a very stron emphasis on the importance of forts in this game which is something I love. The foraging and crafting is pretty complex and fun to work with and will suprise you in little ways.Stuff like making reinforced concrete isn't as simple as a craft menu but takes seperate actions and resouces to make. You first make rebar frame in the craft menu, then you use tools to add a wooden frame around that and then you pour concrete into it. It's much more involved and interesting compared to most crafting/survival games.And this game perfectly encapsulates the surival aspect. There is just so much to this game that I love and the upcomign graphics update will make it even more immersive."
