76561198006549943,Recommended,251570,16258362,"Posted: 8 June, 2015",all,BlueMoon,"Although I haven't played it recently I have enough game time on the ""very"" early access to say I thoroughly enjoyed it.I'll start with game machanics; the crafting system is vast with usefull items pretty much all the way through, you wont want to leave anything behind because pretty much everything has a use some where along the way. The challenge of making molds for certain parts is clever aswell, adding a nice feel to the craffting system. It makes making the more complicated items all the more worth it.To follow on from this, buildings and construction are done very well. Searching buildings is standered, but the buildings them selves look very good for the enviorment they are in. For example the destryed city with it's half destryed buildings look dangerous and with the meterial strengh machanic (talk about that in a second) the buildings look like they are about to fall on your head, be careful. While other buildings like one found on its own in a foggy area look very creepy and mysterious. Construction is fun and simple while feeling really cool and characteristic to real construction. The fact you have to put a wood frame down first that can be destryed easily makes home building effecient and easy. Then using your tools add meterial to the frame, I also had to make frame scafolds around my house to get to certain reaches, very cool. This along side the meterial strengh system where some meterials can reach out further without support than others made building a home with the correct supports very imptortant. This just had a really nice feel to making my house and made it worth the effort.The zombies! Like I said i haven't played it recently but when I did this was something that kinda spoiled the game for me. I'm happy to fend off zombies attracted by the smell of my raw meat, or empty a house of the masses because there might be vaulable loot inside. But when the game turns into a wave survival game, it gets pretty annoying. At random points the game will throw a hord of zombies to the posistion you where standing when they spawned util they see you. Now, when the position they are heading for is the center of your home, and maybe I'll sneak out the back to avoid confilct, they will happily tear a hole in your walls, look for you, and then tear a new hole out of your home again. So if you dont kill them with guns, 5 rows of spikes (not very asthetically pleasing) or lead them away your home will be trashed. I had 3 hords come attack one straight after another and frankly I was getting bored of it. This is probably the main reason I stopped playing.The multiplayer is fun so long as you are with friends. The textures do well to make it look nice. And they are always adding new content, they seem dedicated.Overall I did enjoy this game with the building and scavenging, killing zombies and finding new equipment, crafting tea (too English for words haha) and making molds, along with a very neat mining system that i love. Tis game is all round fun to play, gets some friends on, build a safe house and beat the crap out of any zombies that come near. Enjoy o7"
