,Recommended,251570,23966035,"Posted: 30 June, 2016",all,Janse,"I speak Portuguese, so probably this review contains grammatical mistakes. I apologize in advance.This review is about Alpha 14.7. The next version (Alpha 15) will add new features!In a few words, it is a survival game about zombies, where you need defend yourself against hordes every seven days. But this game is not focused in building a base in the beginning and wait. On the contrary, it forces the player to explore the world gathering resources, since you spawn with nothing more than a bottle of water, one torch and few medicine. Each new release, the game is balanced and some resources (like food and water) becomes more scarce (I believe that they don't need balance these two any more), giving a better and bigger challenge - just like a survival game would be. There are some RPG elements, where each action gives you experience, leveling up the character, giving points to spend in some stats (or skills and perks, in this case). This is important since every day the number of zombies rises and spawn some harder ones. Also, you will start from pretty nothing and will have a progression path, learning some recipes and leveling up, until you can craft some better equipment (tools, weapons and armor). After a while it is possible build a self-sufficient base (or upgrade the existent ones), with forges, plantations and digging the ground for mining, which stops the real need to explore the map. In this stage it is possible hunt animals but you can not domesticate them (plantations works just fine though). I hope they add some new features to force at least some roaming from time to time (just my gameplay style preference, not a problem at all). Oh! I almost forgot... If you are playing in the default settings, you will need to be very careful to roam at night. Take a look for yourself - no spoilers. hahaThat said, it is a solid game even for an alpha. Not many updates as other alpha games, but the developers usually informs the community what they are doing in each minor release. Major updates only occurs in major releases (from alpha 14 to 15, for example), which will break your saves, unfortunately (I believe it is OK, since is an alpha). Most bad reviews are about the save breaks from release to release. Be advised!It is a voxel game, so, if you do not like, that is not for you. They implemented physics, so take care about foundations! If you want to build a mine, for example, you will need some support pillars. The same goes to walkways and bridges. Almost everything is destroyable... I believe only bedrock (the foundation of the game world) is not. Not sure about the height limits of the world, but is pretty big. The default map also is pretty big in length too. It will take a lot of time to explore and loot all.I'm not adept of high graphics settings in my games, but I see a lot of people saying they are having problems with performance. I play in medium with my laptop (i5, 6GB RAM and nVidia 930M) only with 'no shadows' and it runs fine. Every update and release they are trying to optimize the game as much as they can, so let's hope.As I said, if you keep in mind that is an alpha game and they are working every day to bring some new features and balance the game, it is a very good and fun game. Pretty solid in features and gameplay. I believe that optimization, as I said, is the only bigger problem, but the developers are working hard on this. I believe the game has some problem about some hit boxes as well, where some zombies can hit you from distance even if their arm don't hit you in the animation.It is known that some MAC users are having problems each new release, but it seems like is and engine issue... So, if you are a MAC user, you need to go to the forums and find if the issues were fixed. In the Windows, where I play, I had no problems.Never played multiplayer, but the mechanics is the same."
