76561198171441691,Recommended,251570,14989387,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,Programme,"I think that this game is one of the best voxel/survival games out there. 7 Days to Die is rich in gameplay; the combination of Minecraft-style building and digging with DayZ's gritty atmosphere and scavenging makes for one heck of a game. And hey, it has its own meat on the table too. Looking closely at the game you can see the devs put a lot of thought and secrets into the game (ahem, Pass n' Gas) and made it a challenge to actually build a sanctuary from the zombies. And yes, it is still in development, so keep your eyes peeled for everything leading to v.1.0.It should be said that this has performance issues on older/less powerful computers, so if you're playing on a laptop expect some awful lag!"
76561197963975438,Recommended,251570,8849785,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,Grampybones,"If I was going to boil this game down to one word it would be ""FUN"".Yes its an alpha and it has its share of issues but nothing game breaking at least for me. The graphics are pretty good and the mechanics of the game are much better with alpha 6 than in alpha 5. If your familiar with the game Minecraft than you will be familiar with this game when it comes to the crafting and mining aspects, just the graphics are much better as well as the graphics engine. The new forging system in Alpha 6 make for more realism and some added complexity but its a welcome change for me.Crafting houses, farms, furniture, farming for food, mining for ore and stone, making your own ammo and weapons are what make the game fun. I can only see this game getting better with time. Not sure what is next on the features list but here is a wish list from me.Some basic vehicles(I have a ton of gas and no chainsaw yet. Maybe a horse!. Or just to get around the map faster when you don't want to walk)Ability to make more furniture and household items.(I saw double and queen sized beds as well as lamps)More faming options(more crops, and tools)Fence gates(just can't keep out those pesky critters)More food and crafted food options.Double doors that work(They seem to be inthe premade buildings but thedon't work correctly.)Boss zombies(know they were listed as a coming feature but just stating how much I would like them.)Ramdom Dungeons(Something to explore. Might even be filled with zombies and that zombie boss)Third person view (So I can take a look at myself)Seems F5 does the trick in Alpha 6.Clothes and hats( So I can see myself all decked out. Can you say hunting outfits so I can hang around the abandon hunting lodge)Item slots(For the clothes and hat)The only problem that I can see with the game is that the zombie aspects are fun but at night its pretty much death city because there is no way even at the highest daylight to night time period setting that you can gather enough resources and defend yourself. The zombies are way to aggressive at night and seem to make a bee line right for you even though they can't even see you. Its almost like at night they can sense where you are, even when I was at the bottom of a deep pit. If they would not seek you out then the game would be more playable in my opinion with zombies turned on. Mostly I just play with them turned off which also is a nice feature.Grampybones"
