76561198037462721,Recommended,251570,16437112,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Zedakah,"Day 1 - I'm alone in the snowy wilderness with nothing on me but my underwear. Must of been one heck of a night, but that's over with. I rip what little weeds are around me from the ground, pick up a stone, and punch some shrubbery to make a simple stone axe. From here I can scavenge and forage until I find enough to make some bows and arrows. Night is coming, so I decide to crash into an old semi-abandoned lumber mill...just have to clear out the frozen lumberjacks first...Day 2 - I scavenge the nearby areas for supplies, while honing my skills with a bow and arrow on frostbitten zombies. There's a nice lake with some cabins, and a big hunting lodge in the other direction. I take what I need and crash at the lumber mill. I fortify it a bit to help out at night.Day 3 - A dog bit me and infected me. I will die without antibiotics in roughly 3 days. I need to find them fast. I scavenge some more, but no luck. I board up all the windows to the 2 story house next to the lumber mill and add a shooting platform out back.Day 4 - The infection has spread; I must leave to find medicine. My health is dropping slowly...but dropping. After a while, I stumble upon a holy grail of weapons - the Shotgun store in the frigid wasteland. They must cater to hunters. I manage to find an antibiotic and clear the infection. Zombies are everywhere, but things are looking up. I have weapons to even the playing field.Day 5 - I scavenege for supplies only to come across what looks to be like a small military outpost. It's abandoned except for a few zombies throwing themselves on landmines for some reason. I take all 66 landmines and bring them back home. Suprisingly there were no weapons in the outpost. It was much to open-air for my taste, so I bring everything of use back to my lumber castle.Day 6 - I spend the day gathering supplies to build additions to my wooden fortress. I build a forge, smelt metal and craft better tools and improve my weapons. I place landmines all around my house and dig trenches.Day 7 - An ominous feeling of dread approaches in the morning. I don't want to go out. I don't want to leave my house, so I spend the day adding mazes of wood to herd hostiles into landmines and trenches. This is oddly relaxing, but the feel of dread approaches.Night 7 - I stand on my shooting platform and watch the sun go down over my minefield and oil drums scattered in the snow. If I had a cigarrette, I'd smoke it. I wait, and wait, but nothing happens. Midnight approaches, and still nothing. I am getting on edge each minute, but still nothing but silence. At 3am, I step away from my shooting platform and head for the door to go in when I hear a dog growl. It shrieked in pain as it slammed against wooden spikes below me. I turned around to see 50 zombies running at full speed. Charging through my landmines and blowing their faces off just to make me bleed. I shoot some oil drums nearby and take out about a dozen. Ten more were unfortunate enough to step on landmines. Another dozen impaled themselves on spikes as their undead comrades climbed their bodies to try and reach me. I pull out a shotgun and shoot wildly at any survivors. An hour passes of rampage and carnage, but I survive. My fortress pulled through as well. I pack up everything and decide to move to greener pastures.Day 8 - I am a zombie slayer. I have survived against hordes, dogs, and everything else I have come across. I pack up and leave my lovely winter fortress to explore. I pass through lovely forests, deserts, and some sort of charred ground shooting every zombie I come across. Nothing can stop me. I make it to the ruins of a city and start looking for a good place to set up for the night. I shoot a few zombies, nothing I can't handle. I see a movie theatre that looks pretty fortified, so I break down the doors. More zombies aproach, but I take them out. I break down the doors and hear dogs. One jumps on me before I can get a shotgun blast off. More zombies bang on the doors all around me. I run around the corner and come face to face with 3 more zombies. One shotgun blasts drops all three. Another dog lunged at me and caused me to bleed. I took him down but need to heal or I will bleed out. I run around the corner to the theater room. The emergency exit door busts open and 4 zombies come in. I shoot them and head up the stairs to bandage myself. I can see a dozen rotten bodies slowly approach me from the bottom of the stairs of the movie room. I pull out the bandages and first aid kits from my inventory. The last thing I hear is glass shattering from above me, and a famished shout as undead arms grab me from behind. I didn't have the high ground...TLDR - This game is in alpha stage, but it is extremely fun. The graphics aren't great yet, but I have seen developer posts of really good graphics, so I assume they will be implemented at some point (beta or later). Basically all you need to know if you should buy this game.Do you like crafting and building games like minecraft?Do you like tower defense games?Do you like open world exploration games like skyrim?If you answered yes to all 3, then you will like this game. There will be story lines and npc quests in later updates, but none are in the game so far. That said, this game is very fun even without those things."
