,Recommended,251570,14093003,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,Big Merry Jeffery,"While this game may not be the most graphically pleasing (they've actually made it look much better than it did before)this game has pretty much ruined all of the other survival zombie games for me.It's similar to minecraft in the sense that the world is never ending (if you set up the server like that) and it's voxel based so the whole entire game world is destroyable.It did take me a little bit to get used to the whole crafting system of the game but as with most games that have crafting involved, it doesn't take too long to learn what you are doing.Setting up a private server for my girlfriend and I was extremely easy and we had a blast.The game really has a 3 part system to it going as:Beginning:You are just starting out, having just a can of food, water, and some bandages. It's an intense struggle to survive but usually the most fun.Middle: You have a somewhat decent base that'll keep you relatively safe during the night and getting food/water isn't as bad as it once was.End game: You have a pretty OP base, more than enough food/water to survive for quite awhile, many guns, loads of ammo, and you are pretty well off on gear. (This is the least fun part of the game for me)The game was a blast while just playing PVE with my girlfriend, however if you enjoy PVP then you won't be let down by this game either. Playing on a pvp server is filled with suspense. One second a guy who's naked says he is friendly, the next he is trying to chop your head off with an axe just so he can jack your stuff.The game has a ton of playability, there was only one VERY SMALL bug that I ever encountered while playing and it wasn't even close to game breaking, and the developers are actively adding new stuff to the game.7DTD is definitely worth the $25, however you can find it on♥♥♥♥♥for like $8-9 if you would like to save quite a bit of money.10/10"
