76561198032937504,Recommended,251570,30348518,Posted: 5 March,all,bemis21,"2 Hours into the game and here is my review.Overall: I like the concept and I found the atmosphere truly frightening, the sounds the zombies make, the difficulty seeing them and ambient music is quite terrifying at times. I would recommend this game if you like the concept and you are willing to support the developers financially. However the games is alpha, and quite early alpha it seems. Therefore below is a list of things I think the developers should work on as a priority.1) Movement and combat mechanics: the way you move and fight is very reminisent of games like fallout 3, it is clumsy and slow, this is bad with mouse and keyboard and terrible with a controller. I think they should improve this first as it will massively improve the enjoyability of the game.2) The inventory and crafting UI and management system: This again is tedious and slow to use and as it is necessary to use it alot it becomes a little tiresome.3)The game textures: They are pretty low resolution even on ultra setting, I think that this game could do with some major update to the quality of the textures.Final Remarks: I think developers get a little hung up on adding new content when they should focus on the game mechanics and how fluid the movement and combat feels.This game certainly requires attention in this area. If I were to score the game from 0 - 10 I would give it a 7 at this stage in development."
76561198025693876,Recommended,251570,31342588,Posted: 24 April,all,JodoKirvanti,"I am loving this game! I bought it back in 2015 during the Steam Summer Sale. I played for about an hour before giving up. It was not very intuitive, had no direction, and was really tough. Recently, after searching for a game that would have similar features to Fallout 4's base building mechanics and defense, I was referred to this game. I came back and gave it a second try... and I love it! I'm addicted and want to play every day. It doesn't feel like an early access game anymore and you can lose several hours quickly to playing this game. I highly recommend it. It could still use a better tutorial on all the features, and there is plenty of room for improvement, but I would gladly pay the current full price if I didn't already own it."
,Recommended,251570,28390748,"Posted: 15 December, 2016",all,Dominic,"RECENT PATCH NEWS----The game is running SO smooth for me. 140 FPS with normal settings on top of a gigantic mountain. Frame rate tends to drop with hordes down to ~60FPS or so. Very dependent on location.END RECENT PATCH NEWS----A beautiful voxel-based game with fantastic exploration and difficulty.Yes, yes. I can hear you complaining already. ""ANOTHER Zombie survival game. With blocks. UGH. How over-done. How over-cooked.""Well - This game is like having a delicious Honey Baked Ham for Thanksgiving instead of the same old Turkey.Let me explain why. First I will do pro's then con's, with each divided into cute sections.PROS:---Base Building...Or not?---Would you like to build a complex and intricate base designed to have layer after layer of fallback points? You can create a home from scratch or upgrade/modify a prefabricated structure in a city, town, or random structure in the wild.What about deciding to live in a cave? Or create your own cave? Digging in the ground may be a long process in the early game but can be very rewarding in terms of protection and stability!Or would you like to remain a nomad, running/driving from town to town? Collecting valuable recipes while carrying only the essentials on your back and bike.---What about those zombies?---During the day they walk. During the night, you just die.Yep. The zombies walk during the day and full-blown sprint at you during the night. My God is it scary.Unlike many, many, many other zombie games (Looking at you Project Zomboid) the zombies actually increase in threat the longer you are alive. The zombies scale in difficulty depending on the higher level you are, the longer you have survived, and  the better equipped you are. This creates game-play that keeps on giving as you aren't simply ""Good to Go"" once you grab your first good weapon.7 Day Horde: Every 7 days a 'feral' horde attacks the player. The horde is scaled by players and the factors mentioned above. These hordes are set on messing you, and your pretty base, up. The first 7 day horde is fairly easy, and then they just keep getting harder and harder. Which means more zombies and different types of zombies.---Leveling System---The leveling system. It may resemble Sky-Rims(? I can't verify that). The more you do an activity the higher skill you get for said activity. The more you shoot a zombie in the face with a shotgun means the higher in skill level you are with shotguns. What's that? You are only level 10 in shotguns and want to be level 50? Well little Timmy, your character level is 30 and you have 60 unspent skill points - so you can just dump those points into 'Shotgunning' to reach the level you want. This game has a good number of skills to choose from, which makes MP so much more fun as each player can choose to specialize if desired.Personally, I really enjoy the aspect of being able to specialize. I frequently dump all my points into looting so I am a looting machine but not the best fighter.---Looting System---This game is centered around looting. Loot loot loot. There are even perks to get faster looting and higher quality loot. This game has a quality system and any item with quality can be from 0-600. This makes looting fairly fun when you find a nice quality 250 hammer to replace your quality 50 hammer. You can also just dump points into looting if you want to find better stuff earlier.---Map---*Technically* the worlds are infinite but are capped at 10,000 Meters (I believe it's meters). The good news is that this is easily changeable in the config files of the game...something I will get to later.Even with that the randomly generated maps are beautiful. They are NOT the most realistic but they are fun and exciting to traverse with many biomes to explore. Each biome can offer a host of unique zombies and structures to loot. Some biome (Wasteland biome) is essentially a death trap for only higher level players to explore.If you get tired of the random gen worlds you can play on Navezgane. Navezgane is a custom made map that has a good amount of detail and interesting locations.---Food, Farming, Hunting, Cold, Hot, and WELLNESS---Of course, with this being a survival game there is much to worry about besides just your Health Points.This game has a 'wellness' feature that punishes dying. What is wellness?Wellness is considered your base HP and Stamina points. You start of with 100 HP/Stamina and you lose ~10 for dying, to a minimum of 60. However, if you take care of yourself you can increase your wellness to 200 as well.Taking care of yourself means staying warm or cool. Staying full with food and hydrated. Not suffering concussions often and not lighting yourself on fire. There are many ways to obtain food such as farming, hunting, and scavenging and I have found a combination is needed until way LATE game.---Guns and vehicle parts---It is possible to find complete guns, but can be rare. This game actually has a parts system. As in, every gun is made up of parts (Gun barrel, stock, etc, etc). Each part dictates a certain quality of that gun such as the firing speed/distance, damage, etc. This makes owning a gun an interesting concept as you are constantly looking for new and better parts to make your gun better. This also applies to the mini-bike. A better engine means a faster bike. Better tires means a better turning radius.---Multiplayer---Co-op Multiplayer, in my opinion, is where this game really shines. Nothing beats the team-work of friends destroying zombies together. Hunting together. Farming Together. Building a base together. If you have a friend or two to play with, I would heavily recommend this game.---Easy to change settings---This is my favorite. This is what has kept me playing for so long. You can change SO MUCH about this game. Do you not like that zombies run during the night? Well then you can simply make them walk all the time. Do you want the in-game days to be a real 24 hours? (Why would you?) You can do that to. Do you want loot abundance to be at 20%? Or block durability to be at 50% You can do that! There is so much to edit. And that is all in-game changes.I personally decided to make the random-gen worlds generate to 40,000 meters and doubled the size of the biomes. Then I quadrupled the size of the towns and cities. Now there is so much to explore and fight in it is insane!Okay let's move onto the con's.CONS:---FPS Struggles---One change I had to do was to use a program to remove EVERY light from every Prefab in the game.Lighting in this game causes FPS issues like no other (I am not sure if this has been fixed or not).So, I edited the game to have MASSIVE towns. Well, with these towns I would get like 20 FPS. After removing all light sources it went up to 80-90 FPS. That is crazy.I recommend everyone mess with the graphic settings to get a stable frame-rate. It doesn't matter how strong your machine is you will not run this game consistently with all settings maxed out.---Glitches or Annoyances---There are glitches for sure. I have yet to see any game-breaking bugs in the recent versions at all.Some of the most annoying bugs I've encountered:1) Zombies can glitch through the player when sprinting - making it difficult to use melee2) If the zombie attack distance is not change via config files, zombies seem to attack too far.3) The player's attack distance is not well broadcasted and takes time to learn.4) Editing things like town sizes/biome sizes takes a lot of time and patience to learn the system.5) Building on a cliff makes it difficult for zombies to get to you, until they chew through the mountain.--RNG Start---Due to the randomness in this game. You may just get screwed 5 minutes into spawning. Or you may not...this can be a huge frustration for some people.---Update Glory---Sometimes the updates to the game are VERY buggy and take a week or two to get fixed. So be careful of the updates..."
