,Recommended,251570,12218089,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,Bort,"Ok, so this is still in an Alpha stage, but even so, it is still an excellent game.Imagine an open, sandbox world where almost everything can be searched, looted, or harvested to be crafted into something else. Imagine a building system that allows you to construct a simple, tiny wooden shack, or a massive, heavily fortified complex containing traps, tunnels, secrets, and everything you need to survive the end of the world. It's all possible.Then, of course, you have the zombies. No zombie apocalypse game would be complete without them. They're zombies. They want to eat your brains, and to stop them, you have to shoot them (or hit them) in the head. This goes for all zombies, even the zombie dogs (which are pretty cool, but hurt like hell when they sneak up on you).To make life with the zombies more interesting, every seven days the zombie horde goes nuts (""feral"" as it is referred to in game), and they come and hunt you down. It's not just one or two that come and hunt you down. So far as I can tell, it's every zombie in the same region as you. It might even be a new horde, spawned especially to eat your brain.All in all, even in the Alpha, I still highly recommend this game if you are into open world craft-em-ups. Or Minecraft-like building. Or zombie apocalypse games."
