,Recommended,251570,15766897,"Posted: 9 May, 2015",all,TigerMusky,"Logged 150 hours here. I personally recommend this game. It is a very fun and interesting game that you can play hours on. I am a very picky person when it comes to my games, but I really like this one. It is a very hard game to get a hold of to be good. It is totally worth it after the first ten hours of learning how to rock at it. I like the graphics and all the gameplay except the dogs. The dogs are the bane of my existence. They used to be bearable when they spawned rarely, but now that they spawn all over, the game has become extremely hard. It is a very fun game. IF you have time.EDIT #1: Logged 230 hours here. Alpha 13. I have come to love and hate this game. It was a really great game once upon a time... There were some rough patches recently that made the game quite unplayable. I was rather disappointed considering that this is the game the I have logged the most hours on. It was a great game a year ago, but now it is just a another zombie killing game. I like the new system for building and gathering resources. It is a change for the better in this game. Although, it still has a long ways to go. I seem to travel about three thousand whatevers from the middle and the map seems to become a total mess. There are no rivers anymore. I really liked the rivers; they were able to save my butt a couple times when a horde would start chasing me. The maps have just gotten a bit ugly now. If you want water you might just have to travel ten kilometers to get it. I like that little aspect, but when the only nearest water is a tiny pond that has three buckets worth of water it can get a bit difficult. I may be attached to the old memories that I have of this game frome when I used to play it, but that helps me prove my point here. What I am trying to say is that if the developers really want to make a big difference to the game they should go way back and implement a few new things there. Like the minibike for instance is a great idea that helps me in my gameplay, but can become a nuesance. It is an extremely glitchy peice of work. I was driving to my base one day when all of a sudden it felll through the world and I havent been able to find it since. The dogs still seem a bit over powered but that might be me. And I am going to say the same about this patch as I did the other; you can play this game and you will probably enjoy, but you are going to sacrifice a lot of time learning how to play and adapt to the changes as new updates come out. I still recommend this game as of 1/4/2016. No matter how hard they mess this game up I will most likely like it. It has a great concept and I am a very picky person when it comes to my games."
