,Recommended,251570,30300951,Posted: 3 March,all,Draconic_Kid,"As a side note, I'd prever a ~ vote rather than Y or N, but I'll ere on the side of nice because this has potential.When I bought this game, I figured I'd have a survival horror Minecraft clone that wasn't blocky, but was visually pleasing and somewhat realisitc. I was disappointed on one end of this.The graphical quality right now is a tossup. Damaging 'blocks' does change their appearance notably (Doors loose planks and you can see through them, et cetera), but the actual textures are worse than Half Life. No, Not HL:S, the original Half Life. In time, I hope to see this get some high-res textures, but for now, don't be too hopeful. They have bigger issues than how your rocks look, seeing as this is an Alpha-stage project.The fighting, while I did very little thusfar, is hit and miss, quite literally. I'm not overly sure how this is to work, but with a bow, I find aiming for the head to be quite difficult, and the crosshair is for nothing beyond centering your screen. The damage is seemingly low on even the most basic zombie, and therefore you're very much at a disadvantage with low tier weapons. A nice horror touch to my original idea, which compared this to minecraft at first glance. I'm more apt to play a game where you can't survive the night in the woods by punching everything you see.The construction in this game is amazing. I jumpped right into creative and have not been disappointed in the system for building. There are in fact 'blocks' of material, but you only notice them when you are placing building blocks, at which point you have a green cube and highilighted area within that shows exactly where you will place if you click place right then. Very nice, and doesn't subtract from the potentially beutiful end result when this game is finalized in the least bit.Movement, without the cheat-mode Flight enabled, is slower than the creeping death by old age of a newborn. I visited three separate biomes (Desert, Fallout Zone, and a Snowy Forest of some sort), and decided temperature has no influence on speed, you just are that slow. Maybe getting clothes helps (Yes, you start in your boxers//bra and undies), but I didn't bother with that because I was focused on the creative aspects of this game.Overall, hold your breath for later updates! This shows a great deal of potential, and just needs a few things fixed up here and there. This IS an ALPHA game, afterall."
