,Recommended,251570,16382660,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,Darkweaver,"Although still Early Access, currently Alpha 14, this captivating game has enough content and replayability to entertain and keep you busy for hundreds of hours if not more. Going forward there is amazing potential and plans in the development process as well. Developers are constantly working on improving and adding new features to this sandbox game.A premade and a random procedurally generated map are the current options for the game world. Haven't played on the premade ""Navezgane"" map very much but random generated world is fantastic and so much fun, be it single player mode or multiplayer. There are public servers to play on as well.One very noteworthy experience I would like to share is playing on a public PvP server. There are a handful of properly managed servers out there, but when done right with active admins etc., the PvP server experience is comparible to Rust itself and the game struck me as a super detailed (in terms of base building and crafting) and a more relaxed, less hostile PvP version of Rust. It is still kill on sight, but bases are much more safe and durable, which is configurable. As a player who is frustrated with the PvP experience in Rust, this was the perfect alternative for me, couldn't have asked for a better improvement over Rust! Cities and towns to loot, spawn containers to control, air drops and hidden treasures to snatch, base(s) to defend both vs. players and zombie hordes, hunt the wildlife for food, character progression, design a base for security AND aesthetics using many different types of building materials, taking into account gravity and block pyhsics in this voxel based world. Dig an underground bunker, build a tower to the skies, whatever you want!An amazing zombie survival voxel based sandbox game. Much recommendo."
