76561198014319882,Recommended,251570,18882852,"Posted: 4 November, 2015",all,EastBeast,"This is one of my favorite games I have ever played. With the saturation of gathering/crafting games in the last few years it almost seems like the genre will be played out soon. But this game, in my opinion, outshines any of the other games remotely similar to it by far.The developers are always active and you can follow what they're working on via their development blog. A lot of people complain about the fact that they estimate a release date and sometimes the update won't be out until a little bit after but, in my book, that's the sign of a good development team. They're willing to push back a release to make sure that it is how they envisioned it, functioning properly, playable. You can tell they love this game and put their all into it.Hosting your own server is pretty awesome, I love the options you have to make the game however easy or difficult you desire. I originally was hosting my own server off of my second computer during alpha 11 but as I was running into issues. I ended up joining a server with similar settings I enjoyed and had a much better experience with letting someone else manage the server so I could just play and enjoy. I believe my map data was corrupting but I didn't spend too much time troubleshooting so I'm not positive.To sum things up, I love this game and would highly recommend it to any one who ever enjoyed minecraft and left4dead...This game is kind of like those two had a kid. Zombies run at night, every 7 days there is a feral horde that will stop at nothing to kill you, PvP servers are pretty brutal (and super fun!), active developers...whats not to love?**************************************************************************************************************Here it is about a year later, Wrote a second review forgetting I had already wrote one:I've been playing since version A-9. I enjoyed it back then and it has come a long way since then and I still love it. I have probably spent 3X more time playing this game than any other game I have ever owned.It is a unique open world zombie survival game. It's like minecraft and left for dead had a baby.The devs, The Fun Pimps, have been pretty on top of this game and, if not pushing frequent updates out, allowing you to follow their progress and work via their Tumblr account. The shear amount of rebalancing and overhaul that they've done on this game gives it a fresh feel everytime I play through it again.If you get this game and it feels like you have everything you could ever want...well my advice is start over from lvl 1 on a new random gen map and have another go at it. Try joining a different server, PVP servers are a whole different experience from PVE servers. If you've only ever played single player, join a pve server and try to join up with a group or get your friends to join you, it really changes the dynamic of the game.I ran my own server for a little while, there are plenty of options to change and customize the game play to your liking from loot spawn frequency and amount, day light hours and over all 24 hour cycle real to real time ratio(zombies sprint at night), zombie spawn frequency and difficulty, and many more options to get it just the way you want it.I highly recommend this game to anyone that enjoys survival games and zombies."
