76561197964232046,Recommended,251570,13543829,"Posted: 23 December, 2014",all,Rainbow Droid,"--Early Access Review---I will update this review as the game develops.If it fails to deliver on promises I will definitely rewrite this review in FULL ALL CAPS GAMER RAGE because I really anticipate this game becoming a ""great"" computer game. It's already quite good, and such an ambitious project, with a large amount of the developer's goals having already been realized during alpha. Progress seems quick on the game, but apparently cheaters are ruining the online experience... good thing I don't play multiplayer computer games with people I don't know, so I could care less about this aspect of the game.Engine is a bit glitchy and buggy, but runs an impressively big and diverse world. Graphics are a combination of beautiful and hilariously oldschool ugly. I actually love the graphics -- voxel based low poly with some high end shader effects on top, and delightfully ugly for 2014. The instant I saw how ugly the game was I was excited because any ugly game with such great reviews is focused on what's important. Game has a good dedicated server with powerful xml configuration already. Memory leaks are annoying. Some bugs, most not very major but occasionally game breaking. Most can be resolved but very annoying at times. Randomly generated worlds is a great feature, and the game is already fully 100% playable (just feature unfinished and buggy) but the developers have promised much more to come.This is a game that actually deserves alpha status legitimately... but is an awesome alpha. It's almost refined enough for a beta, but it lacks the correct percentage of implemented features to be a beta. It has a lot of similar excitement we've seen around other underhyped games in development... KSP, The Long Dark, etc. I can't wait for the beta. And the full release. And the mod community to get going. With the proper development, modding, and improvements, this has the potential to bethesurvival game out there. Zombies can already be fully disabled if you just want to build/explore/survive, so potentially with mod support and development this will easily eclipse other more general survival games in addition to all the stupid/generic/cashin zombie survival games. It could be that good. It's already well on the way.Screencap from kickstarter of the game's stretch goals (100% of the goals were reached during funding, ignore the locked 500k goal in the image, it was reached as well):http://i.imgur.com/sxvJJSC.jpgAs I said, I'll definitely be following this one during 2015, so expect comments and review updates as the developer either further impresses orFAILS SPECTACULARLY AND GREEDILY LIKE SO MANY OTHERS BEFORE THEM !!!111oneoneone"
