76561197978088186,Recommended,251570,10016145,"Posted: 4 May, 2014",all,HAxan ####RoadKill DIsaster,"I usually don't invest in alpha products, there is just something that puts me off when considering paying for a game in development. However, in 7 Days to Die(7dtd)'s case I don't feel like I'm playing an alpha version of a game.7dtd is very much what they claim it to be, a sandbox, crafting, zombie survival rpg. It's drawing influences from other titles like, Wold war Z(sounds), Resident Evil(music), HBC's The Walking Dead, Left for Dead, etc. It pulls all the influences together and imprints them into their own design which imo, works very well.I won't post any pictures with this review, I'll just imply that I have spent 100+ hours on an alpha version of this game, which says alot about the quality of the game. The sandbox feel to the game is present all the time, the crafting system needs alittle work but is already better then the crafting system in some other games that will remain nameless for now. As for the zombies, they are ugly, they are loud and they are absolutely terrifying, unlike other titles like WarZ which have been described as a open world pvp game that happens to have zombies in it, 7dtd is an open world zombie game that happens to have people in it.As for the open world feel to 7dtd, there is nothing special about it yet, the game world actually feels quite small and with any more then 10 people online it becomes quite crouded. An issue that most likely will be resolved in the near future, but as it stands it feels to small.Bugs, there are a number of bugs and rough edges to the game. However on that remark I'd like to state that I have personally played released games that have supposed to be ''completed'' have more bugs and issues than this alpha version currently has.With the developers planning to add alot more features before an actual release of the game there is no doubt that most issues will be resolved.Now I could write a novel about all the things you can or shouldn't do in the game, but I think I've touched on the most important matters before anyone would consider investing their money into this game, to tie it up.7dtd, has a great concept which the developers are doing a great work with, they keep what they promise to deliver, atleast so far they have. Keep in mind that there are glitches and bugs that still needs fixing. The world can sometimes feel quite small and awkward when zombies clipping through it. All of this considered I'd still recommend this game, again, considering it's an alpha version I'll give it a 7.5/10 a rating that may change with time but at the present I think it's a fair assessment."
