,Recommended,251570,17249210,"Posted: 27 July, 2015",all,Thug Potato,"This game is fun, brutal, intense, and rewards intelligent play. On top of this, the devs set a great example for how to release and develop an early access game.Considering the subject of most of the top comments I'll start by talking about the dev process. I play regularly with a couple of mates and we all regularly comment on how great the regular updates and communication from the devs is. Blog updates let players know clearly what is being prioritized and why, and what we have to look forward to in the upcoming patch. Patch notes are thorough and understandable. Decisions about what the devs are prioritising make sense. Major patches are very regular considering the size of the dev studio, and contain big servings of new content. AND WHEN THE DEVS STUFF SOMETHING UP THEY FIX IT IN THE VERY NEXT HOTFIX. For example, in a recent patch bows became very underpowered, forcing low level players into deadly melee combat with zombies. Coupled with this, the forge (which is a key part of progressing from weak hand crafted items to better metal items) became very hard to come by. Both of these issues were identified by the community, the devs listened, and they were rebalanced in the very next hotfix. I can't think of another early release game where I have been so impressed by the dev process.Now about the game itself. It's brutal, tense, replayable, and heaps of fun. In order to survive and progress you need to make intelligent decisions and think about how you're going to use your time. Difficulty progresses as you do, so you never feel overpowered or underpowered (or when you do get rekt you realise it was your fault). The world is interesting, unforgiving and diverse. The zombies are scary, in a good way. If you do die or otherwise suffer a setback you feel it, but you can make a comeback if you play it right. I regularly find myself on the edge of my seat, or scared, or elated, or just generally having an interesting and fun time. It's also great to play coop with a few friends. You can employ different strategies, and you will realise the outcomes of your decisions. It's a great way to play.With that in mind, I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS GAME!As a final note, THIS GAME IS IN ALPHA. If you can't deal with bugs, or losing your save game with each major update, or incomplete features, THEN DON'T BUY IT. If you can't deal with these issues then don't buy ANY early access game. At this point if you buy it the devs DON'T owe you a complete game. They do owe regular and reasonable progress towards a final product, and in a perfect world they should have open, 2-way communication with the community during this process. In my experience both of those are true. Mad props to the devs, they're doing a great job."
