76561198076928454,Recommended,251570,8067807,"Posted: 16 December, 2013",all,Ferg,"Its a tad expensive but the game really is fun even in alpha phase.I was originally looking at Rust but was a little put off by the multiplayer and PVP aspect of it.  7DTD does have multiplayer in the form of hosting a game that can be password protected so only your friends join or open.  I havent tried to do it yet as i dont have any friends with the game.Some features of the game:Upon creation of your ""world"" you can select the mode of the game.  Currently there are three modes tp select from each with thteir own features.  Then there are features such as scavenger that affedct the ease of loot in the world if you like to make i t more difficult.The most interestig part is that you can turn off the zombies if you simply want to build and explore.  Or you could change the zombie behavior.  On default the zombies walk during the day and are slow but run at night, it can get a little hairy.  You can set them to only walk as well.The best part of this feature is that you can create a world where you built multiple fortresses or whatever and then go back and turn the zombies on or invite friends to play them on.My favorite part of the game is the digging/mining and crafting system.  For crafting i recommend going on youtube and watch a how to craft video, once you understand the concept its pretty easy.  The mining aspect is compared to minecraft alot.  I never played minecraft so i cant comment on that.  BUT, i can comment on the fact that you can dig however far you want, i even burrowed under a lake and tapped into it for an underwater spring!!  I was pretty excited about that.The building aspect of this game is pretty intutive as well and also compared to minecraft...you use materials you forage and craft like stone or wood and build in blocks.  There is a bit of physics so you cant have a house floating in the sky supported by a single support.Overall i am very pleased i spent the money on this...yes it was a bit expensive but with how much fun i have had already i see great promise in this game.  If you pick up the game let me know and we can play, i have been wanting to try out the multi aspect of it.Hope this helps ask questions and get this great game."
