76561197974791025,Recommended,251570,12090081,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,Backpocket Productions,"Let's start with the basics.First, no matter how you dice it, it is a survival game mixed in with Minecraft-like building features.I bought this game solely on customer's reviews.Now, that I have been playing it for several days, I have my personal pros and cons.You start out trying to find materials to keep 3 major functions going: Health, Hunger, and Thirst.All the while, trying to avoid the zombie spawns that are all over the map.Once you have enough items to keep your 3 major functions in check, you will need to find crafting materials for building a shelter (which, at night, is sheer necessity).The map is a hodge podge of random land areas (desert, forest, etc.) which, if you travel far enough in one direction, kerplow! you are in a whole different type of landscape (which doesn't necessarily look natural at all).The zombies are in my opinion, not well done. There seems to be something lacking with them that I just can't put my finger on. They just don't seem well ... scary. The dogs on the other hand scare the pee out of me! The zombie hornet IMO can be removed from the game entirely, as it seems more a nuisance than anything else.The crafting system is pretty cool and offers some neat variety in trying to combine junk items to make good ones. It is very well implemented and it's fun to create a much needed item out of different things.The building system is simplistic and easy to use. Even the most novice gamer can build things with ease. This harkens to the Minecraft game which everyone says it's similar to. It's pretty nice.When wandering around the map, I almost feel bored, collecting bits of trash here, watching for the random spawned zombies, and piecing together what I can. There just seems like I am waiting for something spooky to happen and it's just the same thing over and over. Even with the zombies on feral and the difficulty set high, I easily outpace the zombies (not the dogs) and escape to live another day. There is just something a little lackluster about the feel of the game.I do enjoy getting close to a set of buildings at night. You can hear the zombies howling and that's when the game pulls off what it should all along. A feeling of fear. You know, where did that sound come from? Oh crap, I need to get in that building but, did I just see some movement over that way? Maybe, I should go hide and come back when it's daylight?All in all, I believe the game is pretty solid and it is fun to play. The devs have given us creative mode and for those who don't feel like running around crafting items for much needed resources, there is a cheat mode included as well.In the future, if the tension where to somehow be ratcheted up (I truly don't know how they'd accomplish it) I would give the game a pretty high mark.For now, I'll wait and see how this one progresses. For those of you wanting a solid, fun entertaining game, I would highly recommend this to you.I tip my hat to the devs at Fun Pimps. Keep up the good work ladies and gentlemen. You've got something good in the works here.Thank you."
,Recommended,251570,13740827,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,KaliMoose,"7/10 ""Amazing concept, but feels like something's missing.""First off, this game Is loads of fun with friends. But after the first couple of hours, It just seems to get repetitive.In my opinion, this game Is Minecraft in a zombie apocalypse setting. The zombies are relentless and will mess you up If you're not paying attention. There's loads of crafting, but there's really nothing much to discover after that.Those of you out there that love building and crafting are going to enjoy this game substantially more than me. But honestly, that's all this game came down to, was crafting. I did ENOUGH of that when Minecraft came out. To me, It seems more of a chore, than a fun-filled adventure.All in all, I feel like they could of done more with features, maybe a progression system, classes, abilities, or something to that effect. It's a great game, with loads of multiplayer fun & zombie killing. But It's not something that's gonna keep you hooked for weeks/months on end.Recommendation: If you love crafting, and killing endless hordes of zombies, get this game."
