,Recommended,251570,15398646,"Posted: 16 April, 2015",all,Chrithu,"This review is based on Alpha 11.2b4 mostly.As far as survival/building sandboxes go I have played Minecraft, DayZ (mod, mods of the mod [epoch, origin] and standalone), Nether, Project Zomboid, Don't Starve, Neo Scavenger and various Mods for Fallout 3/NV.7 Days to Die is by far the most promising of all of them. While still deep in alpha and thus buggy and far from feature complete it already blends much of the depth of Minecraft's and Don't Starve's crafting and survival mechanics with Minecraftesque block building and does that in quite stunning graphics for a voxel based game (especially after the Unity 5 update). On top of that it features a clever Zombie AI and PvE elements that I have dreamed about seeing in DayZ for 3 years now (and they still haven't arrived although promised).Most of the important stuff is done via XML files which makes this game super easy to mod. That leads me right to the plethora of options a player or server admin has at his grasp to configure his game experience towards his very personal needs/wishes. Tons of options to make the game harder/easier multiplied by the possibilities given through modding of the XML files.This makes the game appeal to quite the broad audience. The game offers unique challenges to overcome for every type of player: Whether you play only single player, are in it for the PvP or do co-op PvE with your friends (my favorite mode). Especially in co-op play there's room fot many different player mindsets: miners, crafters, zombie hunters, cooks, explorers. You name it and there's something to do in the game for sure.Also this game is one of the sadly few outstanding examples of how Early Access should be done. Regular Updates, good communication between devs and players and very quick fixes for game breaking bugs in 90% of cases.To cut a long story short: 7 Days to Die is far from done and has it's bugs. But it is a very playable and very featurefull alpha version already. And compared to the great DayZ it currently is hands down the better and faster progressing game. Mostly due to it's challenging PvE and survival mechanics and for it's customizability. So if you are into block building and/or zombie survival games you really should give 7DTD a shot."
