,Recommended,251570,13276975,"Posted: 7 December, 2014",all,Thezperk,"So I would like to stress first off that when I recommend this game that is as of it's current state (12/7/14), things may have changed by the point you are reading this but as of now, my opinion stays solid.Do NOT just look at the fact that this review is positive and dismiss itThere are a lot of good aspects and parts of this game that Igenuinely enjoybut it has some things that may turn you away from buying itPros:- It is fun trying to escape zombies- The world seems very open and it's great to explore- There seems to be a diverse amount of things you can collect- The crafting system is solid and has many recipes- The zombies are hard enough that you will fail a lot but not too hard so that you don't want to play the game- Playing with friends is a ton of funCons:- Do NOT play this game if you don't want to grind to start out with. Finding anything is very hard at first and usually you will end up dying over and over again- Finding anybody in multiplayer is a pain and it usually takes forever just to meet up with one person- The game, as many early-access games tend to be, it ridden with bugs (ex. Players floating on top of water rather then swimming or various issues with collision)Overall, I'm giving this game this rating because of how much potential I see in it. If you don't mind any of those cons then, sure, buy the game now because I'm sure it will be fully worth the $25. If you happen to dislike those things, however, then I would reccommend waiting until the official release."
