76561198057897576,Recommended,251570,13593680,"Posted: 25 December, 2014",all,LuxuryMilk,"I'm an old school gamer. No not a fan of old school games exclusively but I've been around since the dawn of computer/console gaming. It's not often a game will grab my attention these days longer than a few hours and keep me hooked. I've been quite a fan of the zombie genre since it began, but lately it's a genre I've grown very tired of. However 7 days to die has been a breath of fresh inspirational air.From the start it's quite a challenge. You will die a lot. Starve to death. Run out of water ,It can be frustrating at first, there's no in game guide to hold your hand like modern games. It's about discovery, survival and the uber advanced crafting system. There's alot to learn! I looked at youtube vids and wikis before I even attempted playing online. I suggest you do the same.It's not a game, It's a lifestyle! You make the world you want it to be as it's highly creative and limited to what your own imagination limits you to. You can build and destroy EVERYTHING in this world and the maps are something you will never see the end of. Designs, structure, materials is all down to your choice. It's a bottomless pit for the creativity in you.Horror value? being a BIG fan of horror games for decades I've become very disensitized to the usual scare factors and jump elements, but oh boy. Time after time, I've screamed like a little scared girl. Jumped out of my skin several hundred times and scared absolutely silly into abandoning highly secured castles and fortresses I've created myself in the middle of the night, because I've♥♥♥♥♥♥myself with fear and blind panic set in. Going outside after midnight on 7D2D is a very very bad idea! but when you hear a feral zombie horde approching, screaming and you hear them destroying your base with ferocity and alarming progress. You just want to flee!You craft your tools, you harvest/grow crops or hunt or scavenge food, craft clothes, weapons and collect minerals by awesome mining underground, or try to survive by just scavenging and looting.Playing this game alone can be a little too creepy and scary. With multiplayer it's a little less scary and hell of a lot of fun. Lot's of  adventures to be had, lots of scares, creativity and you have to think on your feet to survive. It's a real gamers game. no cutscenes, no voiceovers, no multiple option screens, no stupid waiting times. The content and scope is massive. It's not often I'll give top marks for a game but this is an absolute gem for real gamers. it's still in Alpha though, but more complete as a game than alot of 'finished' releases. I've not been interested in any other game for months! 10/10"
,Recommended,251570,13866435,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,fissidens,"This is a tough game to start, you die alot in the beginning, but once you get yourself set up with a base of operations that's relatively safe from zombie attacks it starts getting fun.My biggest recommendation is that if you die before getting a base(and bed) just start a new game. I started three games before I was able to set myself up with a base and bed.A few tips for starting out:- Loot everything- Craft a stone axe- Chop down a few trees- Find a small town, not a city- Break into the tallest building you can find with a flat roof. Block the door with a piece of one of the tree's you chopped down to prevent zombies from getting in long enough to loot the entire building.- Place a marker on the building then go find a bed in one of the surround buildings if you don't already have one.- Place the bed on the roof of your building. This will be where you spawn if you die.- Stay on you're roof when it gets dark. You may want to block off the entrance to the roof as well. I've heard zombies will climb ladders, but haven't seen it.Once you do all this you should be set to start actually enjoying the game.One last comment. I don't think this game is really worth $25. At least not at this stage. The controls and movements are pretty base, like an old school FPS. You can't even crouch to get under an obstacle. Actually the controls/movement is pretty much the same as minecraft, which is pretty ♥♥♥♥♥♥.I don't really care about the poor graphics, but the controls should at least be fluid.Despite the bad character movement and the poor graphics, just the fact that you can build a base to defend from zombies makes this game a worth a try if you have an influx of cash. If you are looking for a game to really make your money count this is not it."
