,Recommended,251570,13523071,"Posted: 22 December, 2014",all,Tzukasa,"If an open world sandbox game based on The Walking Dead were made in the style of Minecraft you'd get 7 Days to Die. It's simply, Awesome. This is EVERYTHING I wish I could do with Minecraft but it simply can't be modded to do. I'll be shelving Minecraft for this, prolly perm.While it's atm in Alpha 10, it's very stable and in over 38 hours of co-op online play with my friend neither of us have encountered a game breaking bug nor had Any CTD's. It's gotta be one of the most complete and well fleshed out Alphas I've ever played.Unlike some other games hosting a private multiplayer session for you and your friend to play is extremely simple and can all be done ingame through the multiplayer window. All around it's a very solid Indie survival/crafting/zombie game that I'm excited to see where it goes in the future with updates as the dev's are Very active in patching and adding content ect.P.S. There are ALOT of options you can change when you setup your world (and everytime you load it up you can change them which is nice). I HIGHLY recommend if you're new to change the option for gear droping to Not Drop on Quiting, and Only Drop your Toolbar/Hotbar on Death instead of both the toolbar and backpack. This will save you a crap ton of frustration as you try to figure out what you're doing. Also changing the enemy chase number down from 60 sec's to 30 sec's will help you keep from having a large train of enemys following you forever, at least until you figure out the machanics and get the gear to kill them ;)"
