,Recommended,251570,13991733,"Posted: 14 January, 2015",all,Shadow Okami,"In the first 3-4 weeks of this game I put in 77 hours and my friend put in over 120. If you're into survial/crafting then this game will keep you entertained for hours. I have played both single and multiplayer, and both are pretty fun. The players are generally better than Day Z or Rust and are more willing to cooperate. My friend and I joined a community of 8-10 other players and built a small city. Gravity affects blocks, and there are enough different block styles to design just abotu anything you want. Servers are very customizable from night/day cycles, loot density, loot respawn, block durability, and zombie spawning. It makes it easy to choose your challenge level and the randomly generated maps mean you never end up playing the same game twice. You could have a city with plentiful resources and only a few zombies or you could have scarce resources with high destructible environment with hordes of feral running zombies.On the downside, there are some glitches occasionally. When servers get overloaded there are lag spikes that cause the game to freeze and huge FPS drops. There are some cheaters and hackers that make it passed the anti-cheat (first house my friend and I holed up in got shot up and blown to pieces by three guys that had infinite ammo, infinite TNT, and were bulletproof). Sometimes I forget it's only in early access status because it already has so many features and is stable for the most part."
