,Recommended,251570,24211004,"Posted: 9 July, 2016",all,ThatOneGirl,"Excellent game, there are still some things that need worked out though. I run my own server and so far things have been great.If you are having trouble playing this game in 64 bit then switch it to 32 bit. It may not help but it worked for a friend of mine who crashed whenever he would look left or right.That being said, here is what I think of the game :)Graphics are great and the zombies look pretty creepy.I will say the dogs are a pain in the rear but they make it interesting. I swear I die more from the aggressive animals than I do from any zombies.The zombies don't spawn on the 7th day for me, they spawn on the 8th Night, just an fyi :)The crafting is awesome! It does suck if you have a low loot respawn because some items can only be found in one or two places and the spawn rate of those items are very low even in the normal gameplay setting.So far I am 60 days (In game days, real time days, 2 weeks) into the game and the horde keeps getting larger and harder, which I very much enjoy.The Open World aspect of the game is wonderful, I greatly enjoy being able to roam where I want, when I want. (As long as it isn't close to horde night, then my rear is parked at my base. lol)The only advice I can give to a newer player is, build a good strong foundation and thicker walls, because it will be crucial!Oh and love the spikes...although they are the death of me!I will add that I run a 50 minute day span, with 18 daylight in game hours, and my zombies are turned up by 1, to make it harder and because the horde didn't spawn on the normal preset server settings for multiplayer."
