76561198013224400,Recommended,251570,23541367,"Posted: 13 June, 2016",all,zztong,"TLDR: Alpha 14.6 and 14.7 -- 6/10 solo, default config. 7/10 solo, modified config. Multiplayer untested. It's not Adult Minecraft, but you can configure it that way if you want to.I keep revising this review as I play more.Adult Minecraft? No, at least not as the game comes configured. A solo default game is more like a First-Person Shooter crossed with a Tower Defense game. If you're not fortunate enough to start near a water source, you'll struggle with hunger and thirst, setting you up to get clobbered by the first 7-day horde.Crafting is decent, though you'll get some chuckles out of the nonsensical combinations. Crafting is drawn out as you need to find and learn recipes for many advanced things. You also may need to salvage equipment. A ""Cooking Pot"" for instance, can be manufactured, but you'll probably have to find one in salvage first in order to survive long enough to make a forge.The FPS aspect is decent and I think the game strikes a nice balance between graphics and playability. Crafting can be awkward at times, so it can be worth it to run a Creative Mode game alongside a Survival Mode game just so you can figure out what blocks you want and how they go together.If you're into XML, you can customize your game's configuration files. I wasn't all that fond of the overwhelming horde waves, for instance, and was able to adjust them. Similarly, I didn't care for the acid spewing zombie, so I switched its AI so it didn't think it had a ranged attack.I've been enjoying exploring the world. There are some quirks. The burning biomes will burn forever. Its easier to avoid thirst in a desert than other biomes because of the yuca plants. You can't always follow the terrain down to streams and rivers. Lakes will be at a low elevation, but the world can and does have low spots that aren't low enough to have water. Combine this with limited draw distances and you can find yourself spending many days looking for a water source.There doesn't seem to be a lot of lore, though a newspaper headline seems to indicate a nuclear event has occurred. Periodic airdrops suggest there is an active civilization, somewhere, though they don't seem to care to drop a map to their location. Many buildings seem to still have electricity. I can't decide if the apocolypse happened recently, or a long time ago. Nor can I explain how I came to wake up in my underwear off in the wilderness."
