76561198007866915,Recommended,251570,24768222,"Posted: 7 August, 2016",all,Dahaka,"Don't expect to be able to be of any use right away.This game is pretty fun in coordinated groups. The downside is that you, as a new player on a new server, are basically ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥. The most basic of zombies can murder you in just a few hits during the day, and at night it's basically game over if you don't have a base of some kind.Melee weapons early on are as much of a joke as you are and do virtually nothing to help you kill zombies that get too close. And guns are just zombie attractors, causing you to run out of bullets before you even down 1 zombie while 10 more show up to see what's going on.Zombie dogs and bears also make quick work out of you even at high levels, so have fun with them.My friends and I managed to play for a few weeks on our own server, we had a nice little setup going on, but every big wave of zombies would just reset our progress. You can't hide at all in the game and it forces you to fight no matter what you do. Sure there are base designs that you can do to make your life easier, but for the most part, the zombies will break everything to ensure that they get to taste your delicious brain juice.Fighting during the big waves is also a joke. It's easier to just unload all of your gear in a box somewhere and then just box everything and respawn until you kill everything. Which makes the big waves kind of a joke.The rest of the game is neat. Crafting is easy to work with. Mining can be fun if you get high enough skill. The biggest flaw is that you can only make guns if you find all the parts despite having access to things that should allow you to just make your own guns.There are still a lot of things they could do to improve the experience of the game. As it is now it's pretty bland and there aren't a whole lot of things to do. More defensive structures would be nice aside from just the two variations of spikes. Allowing people to access the same chest at the same time would be good too so you don't have to wait around for them to finish. A sort function for chests would be nice.Easier base zombies with tougher late game zombies. Better spawn mechanics for zombies as well. I found that I could just be out in the middle of nowhere and zombies would spawn in packs directly behind me and attack. This isn't fun and causes a lot of frustration for no reason. Heat mechanic needs to have a viable range that can be mitigated instead of just an always on thing. Even at the very bottom of the map, zombies can still dig their way to you during the big waves, which is broken. There should be some relative saftey.This game is good if you have a group of friends to play with. Solo it's a nightmare.Get it if it's on sale."
