ing you can get in 2016 for only 25 bucks or a lot less on a steam sale... Is something amazingI would recommend this game for the experience, and tell anyone that has time to kill, wants a new game, can understand the beauty of the survival genre from anywhere but Minecraft, and even remotely likes zombies that this is the game for you.I am aware that i have done little to no talking about the actual game play... That is obviously because anyone who is interested in this game enough that they went on its steam page, scrolled down to read reviews, and saw this one and clicked read more has quite obviously seen a video on the game and knows what the game play is like and anything that they haven't seen or heard is not something that i want to spoil because as i said...Its an experience, an experience i wish i could relive for the first time like my favorite movie or book.(and if that ain't enough for you to buy the game, then understand this... My father has sworn up and down his and my whole life that the only good game that is worth playing in the world, is Civilizations III... A game that on the steam account hes had for years has logged over twelve hundred hours on. the account literally had no other game on it to. Heck, the way i first even found STEAM was because that man told me one night about steams existence, immediately made me an account and bought Civ 3 on it. all 57 hours this account has logged into that game are from him playing.But then I got 7D2D...I showed himI let him play a little bithe actually enjoyed ithe asked to play moreand I knew something had happened.He then bought the game for his 4 year old HP Laptop, and played close to 700 hours of the game in a matter of months with what i would have to imaging was atrocious FPS...If this game can do something I didn't think was conceivable then you should know its a good game...)(Edit its been a while, the game changed. So did i... It isnt quite like the first time, but its still awesome.)"
