,Recommended,251570,33293428,Posted: 5 July,all,PETER,"this game is great if you play it with friends. the only real issues are replayability and lack of ""real multiplayer"". i say that because it only really works as a co-op game where all players are on the same team.as far as replayability goes, the game is dull after the first time you ""beat"" the game. once you play through it once with your pals and make a base that is basically invincible, the only things left to do are grind out new bases or pointlessly max your tools. any playthroughs after that are fairly boring because you know what to do to survive, making it a grind where you repeat tasks you've already done with no difficulty.the real fun of the game comes from learning how things work instead of doing them. such as learning the best spike defense against hordes for your base, not actually farming wood for 3 in game days to do it.it's true the game does have mods, but most are just extra content that has little impact or face the same problems with replayability.good game to get on sale with friends."
