,Recommended,251570,29039966,Posted: 5 January,all,Mkerv,"7 Days to Die is a zombie survival game with crafting and building. Every thing you craft, every action you take, every food or water you drink can help you survive. But on the night of day 7, you will be assaulted by a horde of zombies that will attempt to eat you no matter where you are. Build or fortify a base, add spikes and/or barbed wire, make some wooden clubs and bows+arrows and maybe you will make it past night 7.Pros+Simple crafting system w/ non-invasive tutorial that helps get you started+A lot of customization in terms of clothing/building options+Variable weather/climate depending on biome+Crafting/building/doing survival things levels most of your attributes, which turns into skill points that can be spent on perks. This is especially useful if playing with a group who desires to pool resourcesCons-AI pathing is pretty good but they seem to give up if unable to reach the player effectively-Combat is  meaty but a little clunky-Hordes on night 7 can sometimes be a bit of a bother, which can spell doom of new or inexperienced players-Optimization is alright but could be betterOverall, if you're looking for a zombie survival game, wait for this game to go on sale. Very fun but because it is still Early Access, there are some things that could be improved. Build 16 is coming soon as of this review, so maybe check out the game around that time."
