,Recommended,251570,24144175,"Posted: 6 July, 2016",all,Dunder Chief,"Got this game on sale and got 2 copies for a decent price.Gave one copy to a friend and said we should try it out, but another friend saw what we were playing and bought a copy himself.We are now a 5 man team, renting our own server, and just recently spent nearly 12 hours straight playing it.The balance of this game is such that you don't always feel hopeless, but certainly don't feel overpowered.I play a number of sandbox survival games, and this one fills all of the facets very well.Pros:Promotes teamwork without forcing teamwork. It is possible to go solo (either on a server or offline single-player), but it won't be easy and probably won't be as much fun.Includes all of the things you expect from a sandbox survival: Crafting (tools/weapons/armor), Building bases, mining for resources, scavenging, different biomes, killing things, a leveling system,  and maintaining health via food/water and medical supplies.The implementation of an inexcapable horde of zombies every 7 days is a wonderful feature in that you don't get bored because you always have the next big day looming over the horizon.All of the key gameplay elements are extremely well polished for an alpha build.The dev team seems to be really into what they are doing since updates seem to be constant without being overbearing.The PVP element can bring an interesting component to the game for those that want that extra layer of potential danger.The game doesn't force you to play a certain way but instead lets you approach the game in whatever way you prefer. If you want to be more gnomadic, you can. If you prefer to build a bunker and sit tight, you can do that too.Cons:Due to how quickly they are updating the game, the wiki articles aren't always up to date, which is bad for a good reason.Some of the zombies seem out of place in a game like this that seems to lean more toward realism than fantasy.Primarily, the Cop zombie that is fat, spits acid and explodes. While a common zombie type in zombie games, he doesn't really fit in this game (even though he is fun to go up against). Maybe if instead of spitting acid, it could rupture into a putrid disorienting cloud.There are currently some performance issues when dealing with hordes. Low frame-rate and sound drops out. They are working on it as I understand though.I no longer want to play other games because then I will have less time to play this one.Overall:This game is very well rounded and well polished for an alpha game, and I really look forward to what they have in the future. I got it on sale, but I would still recommend it at full price."
