,Recommended,251570,13399453,"Posted: 16 December, 2014",all,Xamllew,"I don't think I've ever been so threatened by slow shambling Romero style zombies in a game, but this game cleverly makes them very dangerous and sneaky. 7 Days to Die sorta plays like two games in one, during the day you've got an endless randomized world rich with detail and variation which you loot and endanger yourself from not only zombies but also terrain hazards such as cliffs and collapsing buildings. During the night the game plays a bit like a tower defense, get into a building (or make your own), board it up, bar the front door and prepare to fight off hordes until morning. Tons of craftable items which you build from junk and natural resources laying around. The game is rough in the graphics department but it's still one of the best looking voxelized games out right now.Even for an alpha this game has a good 15-20 hour endgame progression. I've put over 110 hours into this game so far and I'm still finding plenty to do, that amount of playbility from any game, let alone an early access, is impressive for me."
