,Recommended,251570,30023941,Posted: 18 February,all,Whole Foods,"I received the game as a gift from a friend.7 Days to Die is probably one of the better ""early access survival open world crafting"" games out there.The way the game progresses feels natural, it's a bit of a grind the first night or two as you'd expect but as soon as you cross that barrier of early game (usually when you finally build a forge) everything immediately feels much smoother. And from there, as you gain skills in crafting, weapons, scavenging, and what have you, it keeps getting easier.The zombies do get tougher but it doesn't feel like an unfair gain each 7 days, you're getting stronger just as much as the zombies are. And with the difficulty gain on your enemies, you also don't get bored- everthing is still a challenge.It's better with friends as well, you can build bigger and better and have a good time surviving together. Or antagonizing each other.  There's also a lovely roleplay element to the game, if you're more imaginative, with the character creation and an (admittedly small) collection of vanity furniture.TL;DR 7DtD is a zombie game with a sweet and simple early game that continues to be fun even after you've reached the 30th day."
