76561198154661444,Recommended,251570,25935048,"Posted: 8 October, 2016",all,aidynmaster,"There's some seriously mixed reviews for 7dtd.  So let me put my 2 cents in here...First of all, above anything else, you will spend a LOT of time in this game scavanging.  Come to a town, loot it building by building, and haul it all back to your base and sort it out.  You will do thisA LOT.  I feel like I do this less in the custom map rather than the random generation one because you often come across smaller but more common points of interest to loot.  There IS a craftable minibike, and that does help moving your loot back to base, but doesn't ease the process of looting every storage container you come across.Second, literally the entire game is built on xml files and if you don't like something or want to tweak something, you have the power to do so.  There's also a huge list of options to choose from in game such as whether zombies run at night, if and how often loot respawns, whether air drops (loot, usually weapons and meds) spawn...don't like zombie dogs?  Cut their movement speed down to that of a crawler.  Want to tweak or make your own recipes?  Go for it.  If an aspect about the game bothers you, then change it.  *runs off to classify the Sledgehammer as a weapon instead of a tool*Third...combat.  I've heard from a few people (I'm looking at you, PC Gamer -.-) that combat is an unpredictable mess of trading blows.  Anyone who enters melee combat even once with a zombie would realize there's a very obvious dance of swing, dodge, swing, dodge.  Do it right, you won't be touched.  Do it wrong, you're getting a black eye.  Both with melee and ranged combat, it's always about those headshots.  Because they're zombies.  You should know that.Fourth, you will probably not be relying on guns...like...ever.  Ammo is extremely hard to come by and any you find should be saved for day 7 hordes, ferals, and probably cops.  You'll rely heavily on a bow or crossbow for ranged combat.  Ammo is craftable, but typically not until very late game and Calipers, a tool used in ammo crafting, is ridiculously rare.Take heed to these points, and know that you will spend a lot of time looting and running back and fourth across the map, when considering purchasing this game.(And keep in mind I am writing this for pre-A15.)Edit for A15: They made food a lot harder to find from looting, so in addition you'll also be hunting animals for meat and setting up a farm as soon as you find seeds and find a home for yourself. (quick tip, you don't need a Hoe, you can plant on dirt that is dug up and placed down again)"
