76561198056510630,Recommended,251570,28090922,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,duomaxwellofafternet,"Allright, I've played this game a long long time now, and here's my opinion on it.One fine night Minecraft and The Walking Dead staggered out of a bar, drunker than♥♥♥♥♥♥ and fumbled their way into an intoxicated ♥♥♥♥fest that resulted in this glorious beacon of survival crafting.  It has a dark feel to it, as suits the zombie apocalypse, but if you manage to keep alive you can almost feel hopeful for your future.  Crafting is straightforward, gather stuff and use it to build better stuff.  I haven't played online yet (More on why in a moment) but my (mis)adventures in single player have left be more satisfied than Minecraft ever accomplished.  Sure, the stuff you build won't be as ""pretty"" and there _are_ some functionalities Minecraft has (See also, Redstone) that this lacks, but I personally didn't suffer at all for it.  The HeatMap functionality forces you to be cautious even in crafting and building and even farming.  I have had to switch gears from harvesting/planting my field to fending off a horde at the speed of growl.The 7th night event is an amazing piece of the game.  This is the night you are GOING to be in for a fight.  The horde knows where you are and they want your flesh.  You'll have to keep it in mind when building your base, because even the strongest defense can be breached by them in time.  The question becomes ""Can you survive the night?""My only complaint, and the reason I haven't played multiplayer, is also a complaint that I really can't lay at the feet of the game alone.  My FPS is approximately 15 on a good day.  More like 12 average, dropping to 10 when even as few as 3 zombies are in view.  It gets worse as I added lighting to my base.  But again, I can't lay this at 7DtD's feet:  My video card is so generic it's part name is literally ""Intel Generic Graphics.""  I suspect strongly that in the coming year when I get the money for an upgrade together, this complaint will vanish and I'll be found online working with friends, trying to evolve from a single zombie fortress to a godsdamned village.Tips:  Don't skimp on defenses.  Do not underestimate the value of a mining helmet, especially on the 7th night.  The humble bow is an incredibly useful weapon.  Zombies can absolutely smell you.  Also, maybe it's just the fact my framerate is garbage but I've found the AK to be a lacking weapon, and would rather have a Blunderbuss.This game has my recommendation 100%."
