,Recommended,251570,29227825,Posted: 13 January,all,JiXXR,"JiXXR REVIEW:I am not normally one who jumps on the Early Access games. In fact, I quite despise them. They are normally plagued with things that would be considered bad even 10 years ago. Poor mechanics, dated graphics, to name a few. It's essentially playing games from back when they were first being developed and weren't refined. Amateurs making poorly thrown together messes that somehow make it to the front page. Despite all this, 7 Days To Die stands strong.This game has its flaws. To name a few:-It's buggy. You will randomly fall through the ground and fall endlessly. Fortunately a quick log out/log in will fix this without losing all your stuff. Trees won't fall over after you chop them unless you destroy the grass ""inside it"". Animals and zombies run in circles comically. Items will disappear out of your inventory or fall through the ground leaving you to wonder where the F they went.-It's not the best looking. Despite having been upgraded to the latest version of the Unity Engine, don't come into this game expecting Crysis 3 or Battlefield 1 visuals. It's somewhere between Left 4 Dead and Minecraft. The game is poorly optimized a this point, but with some graphical console commands can be made to run on even the worst hardware. To play this game on max settings you better have a beastly computer.Now that we've got that out of the way let's talk about why I am giving this game 10/10. It is fun, engaging, and a great way to hang out and enjoy time with friends. Combining the crafting of Minecraft, the fun shoot 'em up survival of Left 4 Dead, and tower defense, this game is chock full of stuff you can do to pass the time. Whether you are playing alone or with friends, just going out and exploring is fun and challenging, and with the random level generation the possibilities are endless.One thing that I have heard others say about this game is that the 7th day horde is a hindrance. That is ruins the game and doesn't allow you to travel and explore. That is not the case. It just forces you to plan ahead and adds to the intensity of the game. You can travel all the way from one side of the map to the other and back with no issues as long as you are prepared. Bring enough cobblestone, spikes, and a hatch with you to make a temporary ""Oh♥♥♥♥♥♥quot; bunker, and you never have to get back to your ""base"" again. Get food and supplies on the fly. If the 7th day is a hindrance, you are playing the game wrong.All in all this game has huge potential. It's very fun, if you like stress. It's one of those kind of games that is as good as you make it to be. You will find stuff to do if you look for it and working with friends to make your way and survive is a blast.~JiX-"
