ames aren't design for your needs, but folk go onto the game forums and complain about the most redundant bs there is and it get's attention, then a whole host of other stuff needs to be looked at because of ""berfs"" that cry babies have called for.Countless what seems needless changes and ""fixes"" to things that weren't broken to begin with only serve to slow things down.I enjoyed this game because it kicked my♥♥♥♥♥ it made you think outside the box with regards to play style, I did try to play it like an arcade combat game but when I first started out I was no where near prepared, I quickly learned to go around what zombies I could in order to get loot, lure them away or onto traps, use the terrain to my advantage, while I searched for hopefully a water jar or tin of food.Sadly the game has become far easier now and it's been ever since the Devs stopped saying to people that complained ""The game is supposed to be hard"" and started saying ""Ok we will change it, please tell your friends to buy the game""Whether they have become a bit greedy since their intial success or something else, I couldn't say but had it not been for a few of the changes, then I would probably have given up hope and come here to tell people to not bother.They've pulled a bit of respect back with the changes in A15 but I personally feel they should have at least got the pc version into Beta before porting to console, that's anyone who's funded the fun pimps time and money they are using to try and cash grab on consoles and when an in depth pc game gets ported to a console? that can only mean a dumbing down of the indepth pc game.It's a fun game and if you get it on sale or something, plus you're looking for a bit of a challenge and something different than a zombie arcade shooter, you should enjoy it."
