,Recommended,251570,30246346,Posted: 28 February,all,React,"I would definitely recommend this game to anyone who enjoys playing open world survival horror games.  This game reminds me of Minecraft, which I used to play for few months.  But I got bored quickly.  You can craft, build, hunt, destroy, plant, train, and do whatever you want.  You can literally build or destroy anything in this world.  The best part is you can level up your character and spend your skill points to improve specific areas of your skills.  You can choose to be better at melee combat, gun fighter, or skilled builder.  But in general, the game is not easy.  It does not hold your hands and teach you step by step what you need to do to survive.  For instance, you can loot a bunch of stuffs from empty houses, buildings, or dead zombies, but you may not have a single clue how those items are being used.  You need to figure that out yourself.   Also, when your character is at level 1, it is extremely difficult to kill one zombie.  You need to train yourself to kill, hunt, and build.  It is hard and time consuming work with no tutorials.  Maybe that may be the reason why this game was rated at low score.  But once you learn how the game works, this game can get very addictive."
