,Recommended,251570,28081093,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,Ozzyberto,"In short: I can't get enough of this game. TFP are making this into a truly scary and enthralling survival experience.A few tips for the beginners out there:- The quickest, safest place is a second or third floor with broken stairs.- Whenever you're outside and not running around, crouch. You can immediately tell if a zombie is hunting you or if you're safe for the time being.- If you find yourself out in the open at night, crouch and don't move 'til dawn. If a zombie comes at you, fight it, don't run. Punch it to death if necessary.- As often as possible eat meat and drink tea. Get that wellness up.- If you dig a mine, dig diagonally. This way, once deep enough, even if you are heard from the surface zombies, they won't know how to get to you.I started playing at alpha 11 single player. I died too many times. I very much liked the gameplay so I when got really frustrated I lowered the zombie spawn rate to keep playing. I'm so glad I did. As I got better at killing them, I slowly raised it back to normal and now I'm confident (and skilled) enough to go out at night even if it means fighting a wandering horde.For the people considering buying this game:* There's crafting, but instead of memorizing tens or hundreds of recipes, you get a nice list menu where you can see what items are needed, and also if you still need to learn the recipe or if you need to use something else to craft (campfire, workbench, etc).* There's physics-based base building, no floating blocks or infinite suspended bridges here. It features an upgrade progression system where you can start by placing a wood wall and upgrade it using the right tool and materials from your inventory all the way up to steel.* While hand-to-hand combat is awkward at this point, I only do that when fighting one or two zombies max. Any other situation I use my bow/crossbow/gun (which is most of the time). Also, you can throw rocks to distract zombies.* You will get hungry/thirsty and hot/cold, this depends on your activity and biome. They are even linked, such as if you get too hot for a while, you will get dehydrated faster.* NPC traders, where you can get some really good stuff or sell your own.* Good guns are unusual and hard to get a hold of, but that's also kind of the point here. This is a survival crafting game. Not CS: Zombies.All in all, I'd say this is an 8.5/10. I can't wait to see what comes in the next update!"
