,Recommended,251570,28811055,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,Leeham,"7 Days to Die is a compelling crafting game set in a zombie infested world. Currently there is almost nothing in terms of storyline (at the time of writing), however just attempting to survive and the crafting elements make it quite addictive.There's not an overt amount of grinding for resources and the speed at which you level and progress is quite balanced. It is however, fairly difficult to survive and travel too far at lower levels. The difficulty parameters are fairly numerous though and can be altered to taste.When the story is implented I feel this game could take on a whole new atmosphere.The graphics are fair for a game of this size (the worlds are quite vast and varied) however quite basic, certainly in the melee combat and zombie mechanics, particularly over uneven terrain.The biggest problem I've had so far however is with clipping and disappearing surfaces and textures. It is unlikely but I have had one occasion of an essentially game-breaking bug where my character vanished into the nether and, due to the game's autosave feature everything was lost and required a restart from the very beginning.Hopefully the bugs are improved upon, possibly the graphics slightly improved as the storyline is implented before development has finalised. Otherwise, I would recommended this game if you're a fan of open-world crafting games and zombies!"
