76561198037987755,Recommended,251570,28324696,"Posted: 12 December, 2016",all,iCare. Roshmeck,"Time for a review I belive, considering the amount of time I've put into this game.I do not remember exactly when I got this game, but during those first hours it was punishing. It was poor looking. You could practically see the chunks loading and really poor distance drawing. Fast forward to alpha 15... Punishing, yes. It is still punishing in the start. I'm just happy I'm no longer a new player, considering the amount of times I would have died. :DConsidering the graphics, alot has changed. To the better of course. Distance drawing took a great leap forward, where I can see the outline of the terrain from miles away now. Lovely, just lovely. Buildings start drawing a tad too close still, but I can acctually live with that.When it comes to the gameplay, more fun now than at the start. I'm getting more and more invested as time goes by. During the progress of the alphas there has been some moments where I didn't find it fun. Especially the ""break-a-leg"" period. Sad and hilarious at the same time. Thankfully that has been fixed, so you no longer break your legs by just going down a gentle slope, or jumping out of water.Updates... Well, it is rather slow now. But considering the amount of things the devs are planning and putting in when there is a major update I can acctually live with that. As long as the development is moving forward. And it is moving forward. The latest improvements with the graphics and such is good in itself. But the drawbridge and catwalks? Oh yes, that was some lovely addition to the game. The changes made to how the spikes work? I love it. Even the change between alpha 15 too 15.1 was great. A small balance thing that made life a whole lot easier. Instead of having to repair the spikes every single step to just once, with a big increase in materials needed instead. So yes, the devs do look into what works and what does not work and change the mechanics accordingly.Some things that still bug me though is how the minibikes work. They are always locked in the horizontal plane and do not follow the terrain. Same thing with cars and such you find. I understand that it is due how the blocks work, but still a tad annoying. I wouldn't call it gamebreaking but it do take some from the immersion. Structural integrity is also abit weird at times. Alot of guessworking on what will work and what will not, especially on high buildings. And then we have the zombies reacting to spikes. They tend to bug out in a jumping animation when they get to spikes. Looks a tad silly and would be a great improvement if that could be fixed.Another thing would be the texture bug when mining at around -43meters. Having to hit stone just below just to get the texture bug to reset is also annoying.Overall though, I must recommend this game. Especially if you can find a few friends to play with on a server. The amount of things you can do, the ever timeconsuming search for certain materials (read brass) and how only your imagination set the limits on how you build your safe base, really shows a game with great promise. It is fun as it is, but with the development going forward as it do there are great things coming in the future.tl;dr: Get the game and whack some zombie skulls!"
