76561198003087849,Recommended,251570,26099014,"Posted: 18 October, 2016",all,Wrong Way,"Ever woken up early in the morning with the sun barely visible but its warmth is beginning to paint the sky many different hues?But there is still a cold fog making it difficult to see anything in front of you and the dark black and grey of branches creaking ever so slightly as a gust of wind blows gently nudging at the back of your mind, activating your alertness keying in your primitive fear and making you a little anxious.As you walk futher to find your vehicle you make out the form of a fellow human slowly walking in your direction, something feels off and your breath becomes a little more shallow as your fight or flight response begins to activate. Its cold enough that your breath keeps misting in front of you further obscuring your view.This person appears even more off as you get closer and the low moans from him make you think that he may be in distress but it feels wrong, the eerie cold of the fog seeping into your bones with obscured vision make you less helpful and brave and more like a scared rabbit, but you should see if hes alright... right? Thats the humane thing to do?This person notices you, their attention focused on you, his movements less ragged and now purposeful as he begins to move towards you, growling, screaming in guttural rage... this isn't right, this isn't safe... I have nothing to defend myself, this person is moving faster in my direction.. I see his clothes are ragged, bloodied, torn.. flesh is missing... this isn't a  person... my body is freezing in this weather, my bones ache... oh god I need to run...I run over a hill, my breath hard in my lungs, I look back and see I outpaced that thing, looking forward I see a house.. the lights are on, the thing behind me has lost interest but I am out of shape and begin to walk, thank god it wasn't faster. I see movement within the house, the fog has lifted a little but it still so cold I shiver or is it out of the loss of adrenaline from running from that monster.As I walk up the stairs, the floor creaks, and I  step on some trash making noise.. I hear a moan from inside but something is wrong... the front door is busted up, split and wreaked, there is more wood on the floor around then there normally should be for a door, the windows are haphazzardly boarded up..I enter cautiously, look around slowly.. I can't see anything.. the candle in the room doesn't illuminate enough of the area and from what I can see this house is a mess, what happened here?First a growl, then a scream.. its a woman, shes on me.. where did she come from!! My head is spinning as she hit me in the head, oh god is that blood? I swing back ineffectively, it has not slowed her assault now there is a man and through my blurred vision I can see both of these ""people"" are like the other man... my heart races as they assualt me, my swings do nothing to slow them...I feel almost at peace as I fall to the ground.. is this the real life? Is this over.. my vision fades, my body shifts and rocks as I feel them eating and ripping my flesh but it doesn't bother me....... the fear ebbs... the light fades........ I wake up, naked.. freezing.... early in the afternoon the sun barely visible but its warmth is beginning to paint the sky many different hues?The ambiance is amazing, the weather effects are wonderful. The game has gone through many iterations to reach the level it is now. The dev's have worked hard to bring this game to this level over the years and it shows. The npc models have improved, the gameplay is enjoyable. Nothing feels better then becoming good at a skill through continued practice and using a bow/arrow to remove a zombies head in a single shot.Its not a guarenteed headshot removal everytime and that makes the game fun. You have the right amount of risk vs reward and a great balance of work vs fun/play.The zombies during the day are as expected, slow and singleminded when they see you. At night they are tougher, faster and stronger.You will face hordes, at first small but they will grow over time and will depend on how much 'heat' is in the area. By 'heat'  the dev's built in this feature: The more activity in an area the more likely and larger/dangerous of a horde that will arrive.Hordes come in all sizes, variants of zombies and are damn scaryier at night.If you are good, you will survive hiding at night without dying once. I promise that by the 7th night your odds go down! and every 7 nights thereafter.The beginning tutorial is good for helping a new player understand basic mechanics, specifically on understanding craffting and  materials.There are multiple play modes: Single, local host and server. You can play by yourself, even offline in Single. In local host you host a server and can invite trusted friends to play with you and on Server you can have a dedicated server you play on or have your own pay service server.Not everything is top of the line graphics or play etc but its how everything comes together here that makes this game fun, enjoyable and tons of replayability.I am a zombie fan and love zombie games even more and besides the deadrising series this game is that survival horror/FPS crafting game that is hours of fun."
