,Recommended,251570,13820378,"Posted: 3 January, 2015",all,[SnL] Fallen Angel,"Let's face it..    The gaming world is full of two bit zombie hacks and so-called sandbox games.This is not one of those games.FIrst and foremost, you should probably know that the game has been and is continuing to develop, and the makers have upgraded features and resolved bugs.   It isn't dead in the water or slowing down, and it looks to continue right on to a full release.    Little chance of a burn from a developer deciding to stop working.The first time you play it you will inevitably run around and try to survive like it's another FPS shooter with zombies, and you'll die of dysentry or starvation.   Or both.   Once the ""newness"" of it wears off, you'll realize that the only way you will make it past those mythical seven days is to build...     THE ULTIMATE FORTRESS!Fast forward a few hours and you'll probably have a nice little wooden shack built up with some punji stick flowerbeds and feeling pretty much like you're living the dream.   That's right about the time the game will introduce you to the concept of a horde of zombie who have a penchant for tearing down anything that makes noise or sounds vaguely like you.Ahead of you is several tiers of building levels, complete with multiple stage buildings and reinforcing.   Sprinkle in a few traps and a will and desire to have a zombie free farm of growing food.   Then you will want to start exploring the world to find the things you don't have yet or haven't seen yet.    When you finally hit the point where you feel like you've explored the game pretty thoroughly, it's time to invite some friends or go online and find some new ones and you've got yet a whole new experience.If you enjoy games involving open worlds, building and crafting, resource gathering, you will find it here.If you enjoy games involving overwhelming odds, limited ammunition and guns, and having an extremely challenging fight to survive in a first person setting against zombies, you will also find it here.In the currently cluttered world of sandbox zombie survival, this is one of the few games that delivers a great time and has a promising future ahead of it."
