76561198028547477,Recommended,251570,28156219,"Posted: 3 December, 2016",all,Bankipriel,"The most fun I've had gaming this year.Exploration, crafting, and building are A++. Combat is intuitive, challenging, and (if you enjoyed Skyrim style fighting) quite enjoyable.Character leveling is fast, but full of tough choices. There are a ton of skills (leveld by using) and perks (purchased with points gained by leveling). There are lots of ways to gain an edge in the early game for a focused strategy. And you will need a strategy, because ...Every seven days, an increasingly terrifying horde of feral zombies attacks, and there is no escape. It doesn't matter how well I think I've prepared, or even how well I survived the last horde. Every time the blood moon rises, and the eerie musics sounds, I grow anxious, waiting for the inevitable ...I have barely scratched the surface of the incredibly detailed core map/world, Navezgane County, AZ. It's balanced, full of places to explore, and has all the biomes (desert, forest, plain, burned land, alpine meadow, snowy mountain).The random generated maps are where I think the real single player challenge lies. The maps are huge, and there is no guarantee of finding what you need to survive. All my best laid plans in my first randome-gnen game came to nothing, when I had to swim across a small sea, traverse a burning forest, to finally reach a bombed city as night fell ... as I ran out of water ... as I desperately searched for a single ****ing pot to boil water in ... as the zombies began to stir all around me in the dark ... as I began to die of thirst, hiding in a ruined grocery store.Navezgane, and the random worlds, are full of things to do, and crazy challenges to overcome.If you've ever wanted to test your knowledge and hypothetical Z-apocalypes survival skills, this RPG-tower defense-FPS hybrid is a ton of fun.And this review is only for the single player. I have yet to attempt a multiplayer game, but for my money, even if this game was only single player, it's worth it. If you've got a group of friends to play with/against, you'd be crazy not to."
