76561198071957710,Recommended,251570,11275122,"Posted: 16 July, 2014",all,Crion,"First TLDR: Buy it, Kill zombies, Build a base, Fight people, Grow a farm, Cower in your base at night, have a blast!Okay let's start with the basics:It's a hybrid Survival/Building/Crafting game. There are zombies. Playing with freinds makes all the difference for me and it is really easy to host your own server and invite them to your game. Procedural/Random worlds will be coming out fairly soon. And yes base building is a lot like minecraft, there I said it.I really like this game as-is even though it's still only in Alpha. Scavenging and surviving are fun and there are many options to raise or lower the difficulty based on your personal preference.Zombies can either be a minor nuisance or a major threat if you adjust your settings. They will chew through your base if you don't set it up right and this makes the base bulding challenging and rewarding. I hate the zombie dogs but love blasting them in the yapper with my shotgun.You have to keep some level of structural integrity to your buildings but you don't need to be an architect to build a solid base. That being said there are some similarities to minecraft in the blocky building style, crafting grid, and farming. So if you like that stuff, it's done well in 7DTD. I know they are working on tweaking and improving most of these systems.The game looks a lot better now that they have smoothed out the blocky terrain and I've heard that the graphics may get another overhaul nearer to the full release. It already looks pretty good.Guns make a satisfying weighty sound and the stealth/noise/smell mechanics adds a lot to the depth of the game.That being said there are still several bugs in the game and the developers are still working on major features of the game such as character leveling/skills/customization which are not implemented yet.I think it's a lot of fun and have already got many hours of entertainment out of it. If you're excited about it get it now! If you're on the fence I'd say get it when it's on sale, but still definitely check it out. If you don't like zombies, or minecraft, or survival games, or fun, then don't buy it because... wait why are you reading this review?!?!Plus I mean... come on... They're gonna add zombie bears"
