,Recommended,251570,29774957,Posted: 7 February,all,SyKo52,"This is a truly awesome game. I highly recommend it to any and all, regardless of your genre preferences. It's basically Minecraft for grown folks, but incudes so many survival, FPS, exploration, merching, RPG, horror, and many other elements at the same time, it definitely appeals to a huge demographic of gamers.  My main problem with Minecraft was the lack of things to do once you actually got your ""big bad build"", well, built, you'd explored the Nether, and killed the dragon. There's nothing else much to do. You're standing on top of it, looking around, eventually coming to the thought, ""Okay, now what? 0.o""Not with this game. This game responds with a resounding ""THIS ♥♥♥♥♥! RAAAWWWRR!!!!"" and they come at you full bore. As well, this game is exploratory in the same way as MC, but with a better engine, thus, better graphics. Keep in mind, it's still a voxel game with chunks generating as you render them. People need to keep this in mind when comparing this game to other current non-voxel games. People really seem to conveniently leave this fact out when making their comparisons.This is by far the best voxel game I've ever seen. It has very high replay value, and Joel and the team are constantly working to fix, improve, and update the game regularly. This is not a devfail project. Quite the opposite, in fact. So, don't be discourage or skiddish by the Alpha tag. It's an Alpha game alright, but it's not going to be dumped along the sideline like many in that catagory here on Steam, and honestly, I wouldn't be suprised to see this game go official soon.7 Days to Die is by far my favorite game to date. Honestly, I'd give it a 8.5 or maybe even a 9 out of 10 in it's current state, simply due to incompletion and small bugs, but include an asterick: (*the potential to become a 10/10 game). The survival aspect, the quality of the work, the increasing difficulty, the replay value... all of it make for a truly excellent game.(''''\__( 0.x )__/'''')  Watch yourself out there, survivor."
