,Recommended,251570,30106600,Posted: 22 February,all,DethBatCountry,"First off, before I start my criticisms of this game, I need to state that, overall, I love this game. It is the best Zombie game I have ever played (been Playing since Alpha Version 7). So far it is the second best survival/crafting game I have played, number 1 being ARK. It is basically Minecraft meets DayZ, with a bit of Rust/ARK thrown in. Though this game was out way before ARK, and I was not a fan of DayZ, as the Zombies seemed trivial, and the world unrewarding. This game can be scary at times, as you are rushing to build some sort of shelter to huddle (in silence) in for the night before the Zombies start running, which is a good thing. The physics added to the Voxel based system adds a bit of realism, and worry about whether or not your building will hold without supports, or whether you should mine that wall out another space, or will it collapse. The 7 day hordes add an extra bit of danger, which will be more than welcome at later points in the game. The Devs are engaged and seem to want to keep their player base happy, which is always a plus, and they continue to add new content, and improve on old content.All that being said, there are some things that I feel are dragging the game down a bit. One is the graphics. The look, and feel of the game, while fitting for the environment, is dull and monotonous. Even with the multiple different Biomes, they all feel pretty much the same. Not to mention the fact that (possibly because the game is Voxel based) the graphics are falling way behind the current standard of games. Another issue I have with the game, and this has been the same since I started playing a couple years ago, is that it eventually becomes too easy. Sure you could force yourself to have a weak shelter to add some danger to the mid-late game if you wanted to keep it interesting, but I feel the game should continue to be challenging, and not fall off so much once you get a few powerful items. It generally gets to a point for me , and all the ppl I play with, where we just decide it would be more fun to start a new world from scratch than to continue the one we already pretty much have everything on. This is the same thing Minecraft did to us.Now I can't say too much about it because I have well over 400 hours in this game, have started at least 20 different worlds, and am still playing it somewhat regularly. However that just speaks to what a good job The Fun Pimps did at creating the Zombie infested, loot stuffed, survival/crafting world that I have always wanted to see in a game. Anyone I convince to buy this game is instantly addicted. And, while it has some quirks, it is a great game that is still being improved upon."
