se building is funCo-Op/MPCombat is enjoyable and you can manouver  in and out of hordes of Zombies while shooting them if you've had a lot of experience on the old CoD zombies.Horde night is great because you have to keep track of time and day which keeps you immersed.Hunting for food like pigs and deer as well as scavanging for tinned foodWater is easy to find and purify making it easy to stock up meaning more time to mine or explore.When you die there is a marker on your on screen compass that shows you where your bag full of stuff is.They are still updating and adding to the game even though it has been in Early Access for just over 3 years(it hasn't been abandoned like so many other Early Access games.Both pro and conZombies going feral at night and running rather than being slow moving dosile morons is both a pro and con because it keeps you on gaurd and keeps you immersed but also limits what you can and can't do at night.Getting stunned by Zombie hits. It adds to the combat but it can be very frustrating at times to be honest.Cons:Graphics aren't the greatest but are still ok. They aren't horrible I'm honestly just a graphics ♥♥♥♥♥ and it could maybe run a bit better however it rarerly drops bellow 60 on max @ 1440p.Sometimes you just get f--ked and die and it can make you have a mini game rage but you'll keep playing and it only happens every now and then lolI would highly recommend this game to anybody looking for a base building survival game where they actually have to regularly defend the base from attack and who likes games like miscreated and Day Z although personally I like this way better than both of them"
,Recommended,251570,15773706,"Posted: 10 May, 2015",all,MegaDan,"Thought It would be badass to try and run inbetween buildings. I ran tooo quick, fell into some spikes and died. i then respawned with a friend and built a base. then i started placing landmines around. 3 nights later i was thinking 'didnt i put landmines here somewhe-' And then i stood on a landmine and died. 10/10 best fun i've had in a long time.Some more in depth stuff (information about gameplay)The fun element of this game is fantastic, but survival is one of the main shining points of this game. you have to hunt or scavenge to find food, or you will slowly degrade, not being able to run very far, not having much health, and eventually, after several days with no food or water, you die, and are stuck with minimum stats. Another hugely impressive part of this game is co-op. this game honestly gets boring after about 20-30 minutes playing on your own. but, i have had multiple 12+ hour sessions of this game on free nights with friends, and that is where the game is most fun. so i massively recommend playing with a friend. The AI in this game is not perfect, but it is fantastic. any sounds, such as opening your backpack, opening or eating food, will draw the attention of nearby zombies. the zombies get more vicious everyday, but on every 7th night (7,14,21,28 etc.) a Blood Moon attack will occur, basically causing you to have a serious freak out session.  many blood moon attacks have ripped through my / my joint owned (co-op) bases, and in the later attacks, almost totally wiped bases out (even with some very good defense). so if you buy this game, which i totally recommend 100%, be wary of your time. you dont have much of it. oh and team up with at least one person (but the more the better) for a better chance of surviving. Good Luck. and BUY THIS GAME. :3"
