76561198056402610,Recommended,251570,27773605,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,The Boss,"Having put lots of my life into this game that is still in the alpha stage.  I think its time I have an appropriate review of it.Graphics:  The Graphics are okay.  There are a little outdated compared to the other games but once you get past it the game is actually pretty good.Gameplay:  Overall, pretty good. You can do everything from build a new house or fortify a new one.  There are a lot of different ways to go about this game which is good because you have options and dont have to follow one set path.The one problem is the XP system.  A open-world game is supposed to let you have everything at your will, not being set back by what level you are or how many skillpoints you have.  A free roam game should also have replayability.  In most skill point based games once you reach the highest level the game gets boring and repetative and in a free roam game that is the worst thing that can happen.  I honestly hope that they get rid of this because it is a real problem and it hinders the experince you can have with this game.The game has potential and I would like to see what happens when they release the full version.  There are still some kinks to work out and I hope The Fun Pimps make this game into what they envision it to be.Rating for now: 8.5/10"
