76561198033543739,Recommended,251570,15747383,"Posted: 8 May, 2015",all,flyingltj,"I recommend this game, but with some reservations. 600+ hours in this game over the past year has shown me a lot and here's the rundown:Pros:-Excellent concept with excellent execution.-Expansive world with both storyline map and random map generation.-Super creepy atmospheric vibe with equally super creepy ambient sounds.-Creativity, problem solving, surviving, few dull moments, with lots to discover.-Bugs get fixed in a good, fast, realistic time frame.Cons:-Very low zombie variety, most zombies are just various skins on the same model.-Predictability in AI behavior, item scavenging, and resource gathering.-Game's staff on official forums frequently belittle and are intentionally rude to customers.-Game features listed on their kickstarter page are still not implemented into game after nearly 2 years, possibly due to their small staff size.  The features are coming, but at a snail's pace, again due to their small staff.All in all it's a very well polished game for an alpha.  This game really has a good vision and a bright future ahead of it.  If it could just pick up it's pace and step out of the semi-unprofessional atmosphere it seems to be in 7D would be much closer to the ideal zombie survival game.  Unfortunately I suspect this game will also keep it's ""Perpetual Alpha"" disclaimer far longer than most other games out there."
