76561198153532580,Recommended,251570,28850095,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,The Lord of Madness |TFM| |STAR|,"7 Days to Die is a post-apocalypse survival sandbox, putting you in the shoes... or, i guess, rags... of a ordinary human, trying to find his/her way along in this ruined world. As the dead walk again, your instincts will be put to the test. Where will you hide? What will you build as a weapon? Is it safe to go out at night? Whatever you decide to do, you must know that 7 days away, a horde will attack your base, so that they may destroy you. Do you have what it takes to survive against the increasing numbers?7 Days to Die revolves around surviving in a ruined world. You will be urged to make use of your limited time to prepare a base to defend against the horde. With this limited time, you will need to collect simple rescources, along with weapons, clothing, food, and more. Littered all around these gigantic worlds are the remains of houses and cities, which you can loot for goods. On the 7th night, you will be attacked by a large horde of zombies, who will destroy you, unless you can fend them off.Pros:-Many different settings, allowing you to adjust the gameplay to fit your wants-Multiplayer support, allowing you to survive with friends-Very in-depth character customization-A multitude of weapons, armor, tools, and building supplies will be at your disposal-Large, randomlly generated worlds, with a variety of biomes, each with their own pros and consCons:-Even at easiest difficulties, some may find the first days challenging-Not too many different types of buildings can be found-Several bugs and glitches still remain-Can become bothersome collecting supplies-There is no definiate way to spawn near your friends, so they may spawn a few feet away from you, or a few milesOverall:I rate 7 Days to Die 9/10. Although this game can be difficult for some, the time you will spend in this game will be worth while. With a multitude of customizing features, you can mold the gameplay however you wish. But as all sandboxes can be, boredum can set in, and very quickly. You will require a lot of patience to spend the in-game days chopping down trees, or for mining, just so you can build a couple parts that will influence your survival. If you like games, such as Unturned, or DayZ, this game is certainly for you!"
