,Recommended,251570,16863602,"Posted: 3 July, 2015",all,Soulcast,"The only way I would not recommend this game is if the person I was talking to was short on patience, or didn't like challenging games.Their is not an in game tutorial.... When you load for the first time, you are randomely placed and you have no idea what's going on, or what you are supposed to do. Because this is a survival game, time is very important (especially in the beggining); so, learning it on your own is harsh and may turn you away from the game. If you don't watch a fan-made tutorial video, or have a friend that knows what they are doing already, you will likely have to die many times; maybe even remake a few games. On top of that, each major update adds more content to make the game even more challenging.There are really two ways to play: Building a fortress or digging a hole and settling down, or, being a nomad and taking shelter in pre-made structures. Playing the ""Minecrafty"" portion of building structures to survive is not necessary, but some may find it easier than the gypsy life.The game is slow, and action comes in terrifying spurts. It's not about jumping in and slaughtering zombies; their are plenty of other games that offer that. This is a game about survival. The zombies add an additional challenge to survival. The developers have said that their end game goal is to make it difficult to survive even if zombies where absent. That's the game you would be buying.Either way, once you figure out the mechanics of the game, and what's important to do as soon as you spawn into the world, the game gets fun. Real fun. If you play with friends, it gets even better (for some, it may be the only way to play). Because the game is challenging, the fun is in the reward of survival. You can scour the internet and find stories people have posted of their time in game, and they usually end up dead. But how they got to that point made a story that you can't live in most games.It is a sandbox game, so you can do a lot. Trapped in a building? Break down the wall and run. Stuck in the middle of nowhere at night? Dig a hole and pray. You can't do EVERYTHING (but name a game where you can), but what is in the game so far allows you to do enough that it almost feels like you can do anything.The game is being actively worked on, with patch twelve planned to release today (07/03/15). Graphics aren't triple A, but few Indie games reach that level, and it's still better than you might expect. They have also been improving graphics as the patches come, re-doing models and various details.Ultimately, if you like challenging games that can feel rewarding, if you have the patience to beat the learning curve, if the graphics look good enough for you, and if you want something that is a little slower paced, then this game is for you. If you want something that's easy and action packed, you probably want to shop around some more."
,Recommended,251570,17409351,"Posted: 5 August, 2015",all,armiemann,"Where to begin... Proabobly that the game has a minibike and zombies. There is a lot more to the game than that of course. Aspects of Survival with Hunger, Health, and Hydration. Combat with Smell radiuses, weapon quality and effectiveness along with a slew of others. Unlike most sandboxes Structural integrety exists, meaning you have to consider how to build you base with considerations of durability from the swarms of zombies you must survive. The game in general is great but increadably un-optimised so for people with lower teir computers, beware FPS below 10 in player built areas."
