,Not Recommended,251570,14607417,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Donnie_Plays,"Most of the hours I have in this game came before Alpha 11.I have been playing this game for almost three years now. There was a time when I thought it was going to be the biggest video game in the world.This company made their stretch goals of $500,000 before the end of 2013. Today, almost four years later and with almost 2.5 million copies of the game sold, they continue tomostly focus on reworking or changing things that are already in the gameor have been in the game for a long time.The leveling system ruined the PVP elements of this gameWhen you are a lower leveled player, your odds of coming across decent loot are intentionally lowered to force you to grind. In other words, you have to do repetitive tasks over and over for a very long time and level up your looting skills before decent loot can really be found. It's ridiculous that two different people of different levels might find two completely different things when opening the same box for the first time, with the higher leveled person more likely to find higher leveled loot. The box should have whatever it has in it.The person opening it should have no bearing on that.Loot is not random if a higher leveled player is more likely to find better loot. That's a manipulated system that does not feel random.There was a time playing 7 days where I could start a new game on a new server, and I might find a good gun in the first hour of playing. That good gun could keep me going and keep me from fearing running into other players. That ended with the leveling system. Now I have to grind doing repetitive tasks just to be able to find that gun and by the time I actually get around to finding that gun, I no longer need it, because I'm already leveled so high I've already made 50 guns like the one I needed when I started out. You can no longer recruit friends to join servers with you, because they do not want to grind for hours to get to a place where they can compete.There was a time when I signed off of 7 Days To Die servers, and had to worry about my base, my loot. I would go to work and wonder if anyone was trying to raid my base. The thrill of PVP died with the leveling system. The PVP servers just are not the same now."
