76561198108132032,Recommended,251570,28823003,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,cmbrockman,"I have put a pretty fair amount of hours into this game i have got to say this is an algorithm of a game thats been hit pretty dang right on the spot. now dont get me wrong it has a few issues that i feel need to be adressed but ill get to those in a bit. But what should you epect from this game? Expect minecraft and rust combined in an epic race for time to fortify a base before every 7th day intervole in which you will have to fend from hordes of zombos and take back the world. Zombie games have become pretty disgustingly common in the gaming community over the past few years which isnt totally a bad thing but sometimes too much is too much, but this game... its doing alot of things right. The ability to have so much build freedom satisfies lots of creative indivisuals while the combat strikes good on alot of people looking for a mixed of slow and fast paced game play. ive spent hours grinding and building bases and it never seems to end and always leaves me staying up late and building more.       But, that being said youll find an intense amount more joyful gameplay while doing multiplayer, its fun to hang with friends and fortify your base as a team. If only servers were a bit more simple like say.. The Forest. But i highly reccomend this game to anyone looking for a minecraft/rust hybrid.The Goods:-Creative Freedom-Decent Graphics-Advanced game mechanics-Great Proof of concept-Good simple quest system-Fun multiplayer-Great foundation for future updates and expansionThe Ugly:This game is well done but the few issues it does have are quite big ones that may be subject to  opinion but this is what i have to say...Zombie Stun System:Its a very annoying mechanic that makes fighting zombies a very unrealistic experience and leads to me and all my friends deaths alot quicker than it should. The mechanic makes it so that when fighting a zombie if you get hit there is a relitively high chance that you will be stunned, which basicly freezes your character in place for a considerable amount of time which allows the zombos to pretty much get a load of free hits on you, ultimatly leaving you helplessly dead or close to dead . This whole mechanic doesnt make sense to me and i feel like the game would really benefit if it was removed or atleast made an option in the world creation menu.Buggy Zombie Dogs:Now, im not against the thought of ""zombie dogs"" but the way they act in game is almost unacceptable, this may be closer to an opinion but its an opinion with reason. when the dogs move around they not only spawn in packs of 2, but also they run very fast.. ok understandable.. they're dogs. but all i can say is that they are in need of a good nerf cuz they appear to be way too strong of an enemy and are nearly impossible to kill without being hit and ""stunned"" ^^^^ .. atleast once or twice, and nothing is worst then getting stunned twice in a row. Ok so? youve said theyre too tough, how does that make them buggy? well when they run around they dont even look like theyre running , more flying their legs move so slow but the entity itelf moves at incredible speed which makes trying to fight them a pain. idk seems buggy to me.Server creation:Just like any other game in this department, its server system is reletively primitive. i dont get why we still have to port forward our games just so our friends can join, and thats just private servers. Public servers to be fleshed out and ok but me personally have never enjoyed any public servers in any game like this only due to things like hacks and cheats that ultimatly lead to greifing and destruction. I feel like there should be a better server creation system so me and my friends can just make a server and play easier without hastle.Water Mechanics:not much to say here other than the title says it all. The water mechanics really need some work because right now its very unfleshed out and weird to work with, same goes for buckets with water, id go as far to say that buckets are useless. but overall this isnt a huge deal.NOTE: I do understand the game is in alpha in which is why im writing this. i understand the game is still heavily being worked on and all i can hope for is that some of these issues ive mentioned can e changed or improved.7 Days to Die is a great open world, sandbox, building/crafting, FPS game combo that hits alot of check marks on my lists of wants in a game, and id reccomend it to anyone coming from a rust aor minecraft liking to try this out and give it a go, i think youll really have lots of fun."
