76561197984301338,Recommended,251570,26028880,"Posted: 14 October, 2016",all,hornet688,"This game approaches the zombie apocalypse in a way I hadn't seen before but had always wanted to experience.  It offers players total freedom to do whatever they want, however they want.  Players get loads of options to customize their experience before they start a game, and these options can be modified upon resuming a game as well.  Furthermore, any aspect of the game you dislike can be easily modified by opening up the game files.  For example, maybe you don't like the pressure of weekly zombie hordes attacking you.  At first, I didn't either.  Worry not, you can easily disable the hordes by changing just a few numbers in the game files in a minute or two.  Then, when you feel ready, you can easily re-enable the hordes and delight in the challenges they pose.  Perhaps you think the zombie dogs run too fast?  You can slow them down by changing a number in a text file as well.  The community is very helpful with regard to modifying the game, and any quick search of the forums, on Steam or otherwise, will verify this.  In addition, there are several comprehensive mods that change many aspects of the game to suit various tastes, such as offering higher difficulty and increasing the complexity of the crafting system.I'd spent a couple hundred hours playing the game on the previous version, Alpha 14.  Now a new version, Alpha 15, has been released, and I can easily see myself spending another couple hundred hours or more with it.  The developers of this game are taking it on a long journey that I joined only recently, but I'm excited to be on board.  I can only imagine how much more I'm going to enjoy the game as time passes and the team and the modding community continue to improve the experience.  Maybe you aren't a fan of Early Access, or maybe you're just a bit wary of it.  No worries, throw the game on your wishlist and check up on it later.  It's true that it isn't finished yet.  However, it seems this game is going places, and I'm happy to be along for the ride as well as the destination.  Maybe you, too, might enjoy the ride.Dear reader, please note that all of my experiences and opinions of this game are based on the single player game mode.  I am doubtful that they are sufficiently representative of multiplayer experiences."
