76561198072016476,Recommended,251570,29810971,Posted: 9 February,all,GunstarHero,"So, what can i say about this game, well i can sum it up in 3 ways, fun, addictive and buggy as hell. 7 Days to Die has got to be one of the best survival crafting games of all time, imo. There is something so satisfying about popping zombies heads off with a hunting rifle or breaking their skull in with a sledgehammer.The pve element of this game can be a really fun experience, if you are just looking for a pve experience, i would suggest you play on a private server with your friends, in fact i would say pve, with some friends can be fun as hell, however, the main problem i have with the pve element of this game, is that if you are going to play on a server with more than 8 or so people, the ammount of zombies you will each get on horde nights will be significantly reduced, so much so that you could quite easily get absolutely none (not a joke), with the new system though we are supposed to get a mini horde each horde night instead of the horde going to just one person, which it used to do on a 15 player + server back in a14, now the horde you get, is based on how much you have died/level, this on paper sounds really good for balancing, however the problem is that it tends to be biggest players in the server that get the most zombies or more so, all of them for that horde night, this takes away the whole idea of the game away and makes it unenjoyableThe game really shines when it comes to the pvp element of the game, trying to break into someone’s base with some of your friends while the defenders shoot at you through arrow slits is exhilarating to be honest, you will rarely come across other players when you are out and about looting so base raiding is where the majority of pvp goes down, one key thing to note about raiding though, is that if the claim blocks are placed inside of peoples bases it makes the surrounding blocks very hard to penetrate using pickaxes and could take a substantial ammount of time (could take hours to raid bases made of concrete/steel), this is probably one of the best ideas for these types of games simply because you can’t just mindlessly sit there at level 1 bashing down blocks with a stone axe, the block strength varies from about 4 x block strength to about 64 x depending on what the server has set, anything set above 32 x is un-feasible imo, this is because it would take like 20 mins to break a single concrete block with a level 600 pickaxe, but I digress. One of the other issues I have with pvp is that there are so many ways to exploit the game and get into other peoples bases without breaking blocks at all, which can be extremely irritating.Pros:It’s so damn fun and addictiveMajor replay value for a £8 game.Really well rounded level system.The loot system is very dynamic, has very few issues, almost flawless.Basically Minecraft with guns.Surprisingly decent graphics for a voxel based game.One of the Creative Leads, MadMole has a YouTube channel where he posts upcoming development implementations for the next patch update, this provides insight into the development of the game (I love MadMoles videos but I wish he would include elements of the game that are from random gen rather than navezgane. )Great combat systemCons:LagMore lagMinibikes glitching all day long/falling off the mapIf a minibike were to get stuck under the map, which it frequently does, it can cause huge lag to the server, making the entire chunk completely unusable until an admin removes it using god mode. It can also do this if you manage to get it stuck in someone’s spike pit causing your fps to go to like 6.(on one server, someone managed to get a minibike stuck in a traders outpost which cannot be dug out as the blocks around it are invulnerable.)Not one server in this game does not lag when there are more than 10 people.Sometimes you can just randomly die, no reason, just standing still and you die.Duping is ridiculously easy, really ruins the game and I’m pretty sure everyone knows how to do it.Devs not interested in fixing clear and evident bugs which ruin the game for everyone, they have also stated that they do not aim for this game to be pvp and they seem to not care for larger servers that are over 12 players (fyi servers over that lag to all hell)This game is filled with hackers that are mostly Chinese, however many servers have IP filters and CBSM systems that block people with high ping from entering the game.EAC has a tendency to boot you for what seems like no reason at all.So many exploits that can be used such as minibike chassis being placed through vault doors.Very toxic community on pvp serversCan be very grindy, but you more or less expect that of survival games.(it doesn’t help that you can’t one hit rock with a maxed out pic and the miner 69r skill anymore.)Steep learning curve (you will die a lot)AI pathing can sometimes not work as the devs intended, I.E. running around in circles.Zombies can hit you from what seems like a couple of meters, they can also sometimes hit you even when there attack animation cycle is not visible (they have sometimes hit me when they are on the floor and no, not crawler zombies)Conclusion:For those that didn’t read all of it, here is a summary –It’s a hell of a lot of fun to play, in all honesty I have never had so much fun in a survival game and I can safely say that after 1000 + hours in this game, I’m still coming back for more, despite all of the bugs and lag this game has, I still love playing it but at the same time I hate playing it because I know within the time that I play it, I’m going to get bull ♥♥♥♥♥ed out of my minibike falling off the map or zombies lagging into me, as I previously stated this game is like minecraft with guns and then a load of steroids injected into it, all in all this is still my favourite game and if the development team put more effort into fixing the sheer ammount of bugs in this game it would be so ♥♥♥♥i good, that is literally the only thing holding it back."
