76561198007353781,Recommended,251570,8779692,"Posted: 19 January, 2014",all,Omnibus,"Still in alfa and feels more complete than some other (released) games out there. Zombie survival with minecraft like elements. Cant wait for everything else they have planned! Great job guys.Edit: I have been playing this on and off for 3 years now and have watched it grow. Every update is more exciting than the last and gets better and better. I have watched as this has taken shape from a blocky minecrafty enviroment to an upgraded skyrim like enviroment.This game has levels upon levels and each seemlessly intertwines such as the builder, which is what drew me to the game in the first palce and have had great fun building deathtraps for zombiekind.The exploring is intense and a joy as you would expect a zombie infested world to be. Your not a run and gun hero that can kill swaths of zombies without risk. Everything has its own risks and you have to constantly be on your guard like you should be in a zombiefest. No other game has captured the essence straight from Dawn of the Dead like this game.Once you get settled and you gain  a good amount of experience (RPG style with a ton of skills) and have built a shelter that can withstand the Blood moon on each of the 7th day (and you feel brave enough) you then start to roam outward, scavanging further and exploring new apocalyptic enviroments it becomes yet another game.The Devs work on this constantly and improve it with every update. I havent played too much on the multiplayer servers, it does tend to get harder to gather resorces but can also add a new human randomness to the game. Those I have seen and played amonst seem friendly and helpful as we're all trying to survive unlike some other games that water down the danger factor of a zombie infested world so they can go on a human hunt insted. Im sure there are players out there but this game compensates. Zombies can hear what your doing.This is still an early access alfa review although I would not let that sway you into thinking its unfinished or has game breaking bugs, it doesn't. Any bugs are quickly squashed and haven't seen anything that is game breaking at all. It also feels finished and is only getting polish with some extra goodies thrown in with each update. Best Zombie game ever. Will also scare the fluff out of you from time to time. Right when you least expect it. Awesome job guys! 9.5/10"
