,Recommended,251570,29503409,Posted: 26 January,all,HiFlyinLowlife,"""...and on the seventh night, the Lord pressed Alt-F4.""TL:DR - Fun, worth, great SP experience/Intense MP one7 Days to Die is one of those ""Two VERY Different Games"" game when it comes to a Single Player vs Multiplayer(Co-op private server). I'll try to keep it as short as possible, but my girlfriend can attest this is a game I am passionate about.Alone as a single player experience, you will still have fun and get your full money's worth and more.-Harvest Materials:to build tools, weapons and build a base. Surviving the night without is possible, just not so rewarding. Depending on the rules you set for yourself, one bad move could result in starting over somewhere else.-Hunt carefully:Meat is a necessary evil, but it also attracts zombies. So while you are hunting, you are being hunted.-Defend your base:The first night in your first tiny shack is intense. Pretty much the same experience I had in a temporary shack while exploring. You'll year them shuffle. You'll look through the door you hastily built and see one or two shuffle past. It's intense because when you DO get sensed and hunted, the doors and walls won't save you. You'll watch as they begin to break and frantically try to keep up with the damage. Depending on your luck you will either succeed long enough, or be forced to take off running and hope you get a few lucky shots in to slow them down.-Everything breaks:The physics in this game are fun. See a big water tower? break a few legs off at the bottom. It'l come crashing down and it's contents will pour over the ground, too. The terrain even has it's physics issues. As for the Zombies? Make them walk over spikes and they will crawl on the ground towards you after losing their legs.Multiplayer -The same as above but, your group will be nomadic. You'll build a base, then decide it isn't big enough. Clear a farmhouse and reinforce it. Scavenge the towns nearby, then decide you didn't get lucky enough to find that one shop you needed. Then the hunting parties form as you look for that one caliper you need.. or some extra iron to make the place more formidable.. or a motor to try to get some concrete flowing. Then as the night hits, everyone is alert to not only the zombies, but whatever the rest of the group is doing that might attract them."
