76561198008697677,Recommended,251570,35222781,Posted: 26 September,all,Toxicmoon,"As an old time gamer, starting with Atari and then later in years MMO’s I longed for the days of difficult content. MMORPGs seem to be obsolete as only fly by night short lived bland flavors.  Been a few years since a game was available that I felt rewarded for my time.  Enter 7 days to die.  This is a fantastic game.While it’s been out for many years I only picked it up a month ago.  I’ve heard a few mentions of it but never tried it for two reasons.  One the title, it implies an ending before you even buy it. While that it isn’t true from the outside looking in that’s how I perceived it. I’m not alone in this thinking as I’ve recommended this game to other age 30-40 guys and they avoided it based on the title for the same reason.Next the graphics are a bit dated looking compared to the polish out there.  Those two things kept me from really looking in to the game until recently.Survival games being the replacement for MMORPG’s or at least for me, I wasn’t really enticed with the choices out there.  PVP is plentiful but the lack of PVE in these games leave a lot to be desired.   When I first started 7 Days to Die and had my♥♥♥♥♥♥handed to me repeatedly I actually enjoyed it. Finally something with a bit of PVE challenge too it.I reached somewhere in the 70s and decided to reroll on a harder difficulty and start over.  After I got the swing of things I desired more of a challenge and the options provided to scale things up deliver!Despite its dated look, at least from a single player stand point I have to say this is the best survival game that I have played to date and I’ve played a lot of titles.   In the late future I’ll have to give the on-line thing a go and see how I fair in PVP. But right now I’m not even worried about it.  I have so many more places to explore and things to see.This is an immersive well thought out master piece, I love it.Desired requests:A graphics update or mod would be wonderful."
