76561198080965451,Recommended,251570,13605495,"Posted: 25 December, 2014",all,Swift Chimp,"Easily one of the best game I've ever played if you dont get this you should probably think very hard about your life. (skip to the bottom for a short version)Pros-Crafting holds your hand, but just enough so you get the whole experience of it, not in a way that makes you feel like the games doing it for you, and it is also very in-depth and generally makes alot of sense.-BLOCK PHYSICS, you can't nerd pole up without zombies hitting the bottom and the entire thing crashing down and you falling, and you can't infinately build sideways from a starting point, or the structure will soon fall, unless you support it.-Incredibly easy to play with your friends, and find them in the world, you can host your own free servers, and track your friends if they accept the invite, and also allow random players to join, and you don't need to use IP or open your ports, it's all public.-This game is actually a horror game alot of the time, unlike most ""horror survival games"", mostly since the zombies ai is done very well and they are a HUGE threat; for example, the zombies run at night, so sometimes your just running along a road hoping you can find a house before a horde of zombies finds you and kicks your head off, and the zombies can easily break down defenses in large groups, so you can just be hoping they dont get through your door before dawn comes.-The block models in this game are incredible, this is the first and only game game I've played that you can dig a hole in the ground, and it doesn't look like a square going down, it actually looks like a real, round hole, and I am in awe of how the devs were able to pull it off so well.-Base building is very easy, and intuitive, and also gives you many different options for walls and doors, such as plain wood walls and doors, up to solid iron doors and reinforced concrete walls, and many things inbetween.-Like i said above, the zombies are very well made, they break down walls at a reasonable pace, so it's not just obnoxious and unreal, but enough to make it a challenge still and every once in a while you have to repair walls, and are very realistically placed.-It's YOUR world! You can change almost everything about it! The setting for the world are very well thought out, you can change everything from crafting time and loot timers, to block durability and zombie spawning/difficulty, and almost everything inbetween that you can think of.-The game never gets old, I got this around 2 years ago and i still play it with my friends today.-The devs are constantly updating the game with actual game changing elements, not just how grass looks from a 47 degree angle on tuesdays if it was a full moon yesterday, and it's still in early access, and feels like a full game, not a broken mess.Cons-Murderous bees are spooky and loud-Have to bring down stuffed animals to hold and make me stop crying because of all the spooks.-Can't change settings in game, which makes people in privately hosted servers cry.SHORT VERSIONPros-Easy, intuitive craftng, yet still in-depth.-BLOCK PHYSICS, FINALLY. You can't just build a straight pole up without zombies hitting the bottom block and it all crashing down on you, and you can't infinately build to the side, without supporting it from below or the entire structure will collapse.-Very easy to play with friends and find them in-game, just host a server and go, or join a densely populated server with tons of other people.-Actually feels like a survival horror game, not a tree hitting, scavenging simulator.-Incredible block models, holes look like holes, not square death pits.-Base building is easy, and gives you complete control on what you want your base to look like.-The zombies are nothing short of amazing, and actually make the game challenging, since they can break through your base, but at a reasonable pace, so it's realistic, not obnoxious.-You can change almost everything about the world, from block durability, to loot timers and abundance, to zombie spawn rates and difficulty.-This is in early access, but feels like a finished product, with very minimal glitches, and a large amount of content in the game, and the devs are still consistantly updating it with substantial improvements, not tiny changes to unimportant aspects.Cons-2Spooky5MeSummary: Get the game"
