76561198069866870,Recommended,251570,11956189,"Posted: 2 September, 2014",all,Tom,"I play this with a few friends, and despite being in Alpha it's by far one of the most fun games we've played together, and it's only getting better and better.It's very much still in development, with a very active and responsive dev team. Over the few months I've owned and played this game it's already come on in leaps and bounds and I'm really enthusiastic about what it's going to turn into over the next few months.If you have played Minecraft (or even like the idea but hate the graphics) then definitely give this a go. It's not minecraft, at all, but it's grown from the same roots. If you're a fan of Fallout and open world games in general, then give it a go! It's even got a healthy dose of FPS shooter style action, you can protect your more engineering-minded friends from zombie hordes.The crafting system is very familiar to an old Minecraft player, but differs in many ways and there are already a large number of recipes to craft. Almost every item/block/plant in the game can be used for something, and already you can 'live' in the world in different ways - roving scavenger living off canned goods, survivalist farmer growing crops, hunter (deer, pig and rabbit) or even nawing on the rotten flesh of a zombie dog (not recomended).The debuff system is a agreat additon to the mix, you can become infected, bleed out, get sickness and even diarrhea which all needs various types of medical treatment (which you can scavenge or craft). It's now even possible to sprain or break your leg, making it increasingly difficult to survive!At this stage (Alpha 9.1) there's still a lot of balancing going on, and there's a lot more needed. There isn't a huge amount of features yet (though enough to make the purchase price well worth it), and after a week or so me and my friends 'ran out' of things to do, but we just leave it for a couple of weeks and come back fresh and it's great again.It's clear to see what direction the game is going in - a very good one - and reading the list of what is going to be added in future updates (cars, NPC survivors, radiant missions, livestock, upgraded zombie animations etc.)...I can't wait!In short, good fun, survival, looting, FPS, voxel mining-building game in an open world which is best enjoyed with friends on a dedicated server."
