,Recommended,251570,11124053,"Posted: 7 July, 2014",all,TheKyle,"Let me start off by saying this: 7 Days to Die is an amazing zombie/mining game that is very enjoyable.On the other hand, there are a few problems with it including:-It's not optimized AT ALL. (I can run Minecraft and Skyrim at highest settings with 60 FPS and can barely run this on lowest)-The water is very ugly, it doesn't have a movement animation and can turn invisible when placed using a bucket. (I want to make a hot tub people!)-The textures make it hard to tell what block you are mining while underground.-The game's sounds aren't very flattering.-Zombies sometimes break down a wall instead of going through the open doorway next to them.-Multiplayer is somewhat bad and tends to lag at the times that matter most. (Such as a horde attacking your cabin in the middle of the night)-More that are minor complaints that I won't care to tell.Now, I believe that all of these bugs/problems will be fixed in future updates. I personally can look past the majority of them.Good things about the game:-The day/night cycle that affects the zombies is very interesting.-The game treats you like a ♥♥♥♥♥. What I mean by this is that it doesn't tell you everything about how to play the game like you're a ten year old with down syndrome. I love that it lets you discover things on your own.-There is an actual challenge, you can't run into the game and expect to kill every zombie and be invincible.-The crafting is amazing.-Physics make building much more exciting.-The current map has very interesting locales including a factory, two large towns, a school, and military bases.-Waaaaaay more aspects that I will not list.Recommendation:7 Days to Die is an amazing game that is for anyone that likes survival, mining, zombie, or simulation games. The current state of the game is playable, but I would not recommend it to anyone that cannot tolerate or look past the flaws that 7 Days to Die has.8/10"
