,Recommended,251570,13231100,"Posted: 4 December, 2014",all,Richard,"Good game play. While I must say that it is still in early developmental stages, quite a few ""annoyances"" still exist such as players being able to duplicate items, quite a few methods for ""hackers"" to enable Creative Mode are available, and it's almost not shocking to find a regular player ""no-clipping"" around from time-to-time. But getting past these bugs and exploits, the game itself is taking on a good direction and the developmental team seems to be hard at work releasing patch after patch to fix known bugs. The only thing I wish they would focus on after this bugs, is the fact of optimizing the game. Video settings are very minimal, and even with a powerful PC; you may experience frame drops on a regular basis.On the server management side, setting up a dedicated server is relatively easy to do. However the ""modification"" aspect of your dedicated server will remain very limited for the time being as most of the files are compiled .dll files. While I can understand this on the client-side, it makes it very difficult to write any new add-ons for your server as far as server-side action is concerned. Alloc who is also on the 7DTD team, has written a few add-ons which I would recommend you pick up, including the ""Alloc's Mod"". It includes a lot of additional features that you can execute via the in-game console once you are in debug mode that assist with managing players which includes viewing player inventory, an unban function, a better teleporting feature, and a lot of other great assets.I think it would be unfair to give the game a rating due to it being in developmental stages, so I'd just recommend everyone pick up a copy and try it out. Definitely not a ""waste"" of money, and will be a lot better once the above things are worked out.Regards,RichardYouTube: IAMRichardT"
