,Recommended,251570,25943318,"Posted: 9 October, 2016",all,jo,"This game has the most bang I ever got for my bucks. Bought it 2 years ago, spent a few hundred hours on it (back then it was mostly minecraft with zombies) and put it away. Since then they've been making it a new game every half year or so, ""forcing"" me to spend another few hundred hours on it. By now, the game is a very complete experience: It's immersive, forcing you to be creative on a fun difficulty level (making it hard but not impossible once you know what you're doing), has tons of things to do even in single player, is beautiful graphics wise (at least for a ""minecraft-game"") and it's even starting to get story elements.There's a lot of criticism going around, for the devs being ""slow"" and the game still being in alpha after three years. Consider this: Yes, you have to wait a long time for every new alpha. Every new alpha is a whole new game experience though, basically giving you a new game for free. Considering all/most of the other alphas out there, which usually get released into beta/release status long before the game is even working right, just because the time frame or the project is reached - I'd much rather haver the devs take their time and fulfill the promises they've made, no matter how long it takes. And accompany them on the road they're taking, always being surprised at how nice they're coming along.Paying ~20$ for it, I got like 5 or 6 games out of it already. And I'm not talking starting 5 new single player games, I'm talking 5 totally brand new gaming experiences. I honestly don't know if I even want the game to go out of alpha status - I'd be missing the look at my library, hoping for a new update which will give me a new game for free.So - if you want a 100% polished and release ready game, with a story experience like DS or TES, don't buy this yet. Wait a few more years, until they're far enough along the road to release it. If you want a fun and immersive survival crafting game, which by now is pretty far along the road and has dlc worthy content improvements for free every half year or so, definetly buy this. It's one of the (few) games I'll never regret spending the full price on."
