76561198073945981,Recommended,251570,18903147,"Posted: 5 November, 2015",all,DarkOdysseus,"my buddy finally antagonized me enough to buy this game. I was leery at first, having played around 500 hours of Rust and having recently made a couple bad Early Access purchases. By looking at the screenshots the building system looked like minecraft, which turned me off. But I gave in and bought it. I have since enjoyed every minute of my 20 hours playing so far.Pros:.The map is awesome and diverse. You get all the biomes here, dessert, snow, forest, and urban. When you are in the dessert, you feel like you are in the dessert. When you are in the snow, you feel like you are in the snow. You will find tons of pre-built structures littering the landscape, mostly zombie infested, that will score you needed loot or the makings of a base..This is truly sandbox. Everything is destructible, I mean everything. You dont like that wall? Chop it down. Cant get into a building? Build a tunnel underneath it. That tree looking at you wrong? Turn it into sawdust..Building. The possibilities are near endless when it comes to building. The vast array of deployables and block types make your creativity levels spike. You can build the pyramids of Egypt, the eiffel tower, or the more intelligent heavily fortified defensive structure. Another key aspect is the ground manipulation. You could build a massive cave base or try and dig your way to china. Its up to you..Crafting is truly on par. You will need to gather resources of all kinds in order to craft what you want. Everything you come across will have a use, whether you know it or not. Items you pass up because you think you will never need it will become the must have item later in your play time. You will need a furnace to smelt metals, a fireplace to cook your food, and storage boxes to hold your gear..Weapons are diverse. I love the amount of guns, projectiles, and blunt force weapons you can find/build. You will need to collect the necessary gun parts in order to craft a weapon including the blueprint..Multiplayer is obviously an added bonus for me and the reason I purchased this game. But if you arnt into that, play solo.Cons:.It can sometimes get repetitive shooting arrows into a zombies scull while looting houses. Notice the word ""sometimes""..Zombies can be unforgiving. This isnt much of a con in the fact that this is how the game plays. Watch your back and dont make stupid moves. The term self preservation comes to mind..Trees sometimes seem to fall back toward you afting chopping one down causing instant death. My advice is once you chop a tree down back away and watch the direction of the fall..Zombie reach can seem a bit odd. Died multiple times because I thought I had enough distance between me and a zombie. Again, this is probably how the game plays. Dont get near zombies.My conclusion is this game is definitely worth a play for the price."
