,Recommended,251570,23340476,"Posted: 2 June, 2016",all,AudieMurphy,"Rust with zombies and destructible terrain.  Got this game to play with the significant other.  All in all, we've been having a blast.There is a fairly steep learning curve right off the bat, with our first few sessions playing like a rogue-like as we puttered about in crafting menus and hit various objects with various things in various ways to see what happened.  But quickly. things fell into place and we started fixing up a place we'd cleared out of zombies - battoning up the windows, fortifying the perimeter.  It worked great for the occasional roaming Zed, and we started stockpiling resources.The nights fell into a predictable pattern of a few zombies scratching at the walls, or doors, and clearing them out as needed.  Traps got the bulk of them, and we'd mop up the few remaining.  It was this complacency that led into Day 7.I was in the attic, looking out over the quiet homestead, when the sun set.  As the Blood Moon rose and the Chaos God laughed, I started seeing figures running on the darkening hillside.   First one, then a handful, then a dozen or more.  As the light faded, I heard them breaking through the traps outside.  Then, they were at the door.  Then, they were inside.Back to the drawing board.  A few play sessions later, we are in good shape.  ...I think.This game is very friendly to session-based coop play, and scratches my crafting survival itch perfectly.  Great atmosphere, in-depth crafting mechanics, and engaging gameplay, with there always being something to do to better your odds of survival.  The zombies are a bit wonky, but nowhere near DayZ levels of bad.  Very playable in its current state.I'd reccommend to anyone who remotely enjoys crafting survival games or open-world post-apocalyptic scavenging."
,Recommended,251570,24127928,"Posted: 5 July, 2016",all,Wolfmaster,"Day 1: Very helpful tutorial taught me how to make pants out of plants. Beat up some zombies with an axe made out of rocks. Found a rural cabin and managed to board it up to make a nice home. Crouched fearfully in the attic when night came.Day 2: Ground floor of my cabin was in shambles thanks to my zombie friends. Chopped up furniture to repair the damage. Looked for water to deal with my thirst but found nothing. Cut down some trees to bolster my makeshift house. Crawled back into the attic, severely dehydrated, when it got dark.Day 3: Drank some water I found off an undead soccer mom. Decided to ditch the cabin and found a big road. Followed it to a town (if you can call three buildings at an intersection a town). Found a bear. Decided to attack bear with a flimsy bow and arrows. Failed miserably. Ran from bear. Holed up in a general store and barricaded the doors. When night came, zombies started to pull apart my new base. Set up my bedroll and campfire on the roof. Got rained on.Day 4: Still surviving on very little water. Got hit by a zombie while looting a bird's nest. Developed an infection. Chased after an airplane and got lost. Found a lakeside cabin and way too many zombies. After clearing them out, filled all my empty jars and headed back to my house. Purified the water and feasted on bacon and eggs to celebrate my discovery.Day 5: Managed to kill an elk, skinned it with a sharpened zombie femur. Got chased by a pack of undead while bringing the meat back to my house. Beat them to death with an iron club. Searched in vain for antibiotics for my worsening infection. Found feces in a toilet and picked it up (from the clean end).Day 6: Remembered that a large horde is coming tomorrow night. Decided to gather as much garbage as I could to upgrade my home's defenses. Dug up dirt and created a garden on my roof. Planted some blueberries and cotton. Made a mental note to create pillars to support the roof.Day 7: This is it, last day before the horde comes. Made yet another journey to gather more wood. Saw that airplane again and followed it until it dropped a supply crate. Looted the crate. Found a submachine gun. Still no antibiotics. On the way back, spotted another bear and got mauled to death. Thankfully death is little more than a setback and I spawned back on my bed. At least I was no longer infected. Gathered my gear from my old corpse and started to reinforce the walls of my house. Ran out of iron and decided to huddle on the roof. Ten o'clock rolled around. Giant horde of zombies arrived and began beating on the walls of my place. Shot a few until I ran out of bullets. Huddled some more.Day 8: Zombie horde still in my house. Jumped off the roof to avoid them and sprained my leg. Beat a few of the zombies to death with my trusty club. Left for another scavenging run and finally found antibiotics, even though I didn't need them anymore. Headed back home to find that my garden had caused the roof to collapse while I was out, taking the entire building and my extra gear with it. Left to find a new place to stay. Got mauled by a bear again. GG."
