76561198067989240,Recommended,251570,8800368,"Posted: 21 January, 2014",all,BlueRLSH,"7 Days to DieEver wonder what it would be like to be a lone survivor or in a group of lone survivors living in a zombie apocalypse? This game is that very scenario. 7 Days to Die lets you choose between being a man or women each with two different skin choices as of its current 6.1 Alpha stage. The game allows you to live the horrors of surviving from starvations and dehydration while having to scavenge to stay alive fighting of hordes of at the moment way point GPS smart zombies. The game will house much smarter and less direct zombies in future updates. The company Fun Pimps has done everything and is still doing everything to make a great zombie shooter/role play/sand box/builder (mine Craft) like game. The graphics are pretty good and the games current glitches at times can give a good laugh. But 7 Days to Die is no joke. It is an extremely challenging game but can be set up for fun and simple too with its great list of game play options.  You can even turn the zombie spawns off to just build and explore ahead if you wish to just get a feel for the basic before having to run and fight for your life. Zombies run at night and can really overwhelmed you at night so finding a place to hold up for the night is a must. Zombie Dogs run all the time and just a pack of 4 can be overwhelming if not handled carefully. Mutant Bee’s fly around and are good to hunt for honey. While traditional game like deer, pigs, and rabbits can be hunted and cooked in special recipe’s for extended hunger relief.If you like action, adventure, shooters, and building this game is for you. Fun Pimps is still working on this game and updating it frequently and will even listen to ideas and information from players. I’m very happy I purchased this game. It has been an adventure. Keep in mind it will have bugs but they are always being worked on. For more information contact the Fun Pimps web site. I also recommend several of the play through on U-Tube. We have lots of good U tubers that go over the basics of the last Alpha 5 update and I’m sure more are working on the current 6.1 update to give current feedback and help to new players and the company. Until then purchase this game and have fun. It’s worth the money and will bring hours of enjoyment. Don’t forget PVP. Zombies are not just the only threat.- Crazy J"
