,Recommended,251570,8634235,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,I am a jelly doughnut,"An Early review:**Be warned if you do buy off this recommendation this is a very early development game.  Meaning all of this is subject to change or be completely different with each coming alpha patch.  Not to mention plenty of bugs, errors, CTD, instability, etc. that goes along with early testing / playing.**The last words from the last review on this were ""Great Potential Here"".  Amazingly The Fun Pimps have started to really shape this game into it's own.  With plenty of bugs and odd issues remaining, the addition of stealth, zombie wake system, timers for looting, crafting enhanced, as well as a major overhaul to the game graphically it is quite a great game for it's price.They have dropped the price a few times in this, which to some was very much so a slap in the face to those that purchased, but out of all the Early Access Games i've played this one is one of the few that I've put down for a few months and come back to something completely different.The sweeping changes and additions come and alter how you play almost entirely.  More server settings available to have your own personalized experience on your server, as well as the leveling armor and stealth systems.  The game from when i first reviewed it is no more, the improved version here is the version you may want to not pass up.Many will knock it for it's less than stellar graphical effects, but when it comes to minecraft like building and crafting this game has it all.  With smelters, mining being less blocky, and resources being actually rare.   It has only improved upon almost every aspect that it was weak for, granted adding more bugs and issues, but giving a great view of what the developers promised to have in for release.Overall if you want a fun time with some buddies, either base building, pvp'ing, or surviving the zombie horde this is a definate must to check out.(To be continued...)"
