,Recommended,251570,25849534,"Posted: 3 October, 2016",all,The Churtle,"Great game. Its been in alpha a long time and has slow but constant updates that have changed the game several times. The developers are active and I feel that they will eventually finish the game, though that may take a long time. This is both a good thing, as with each big update there is more to see and enjoy, and a bad thing as the map you may have sunk many hours into no longer works. I do worry about the recent ps4 port as this has slowed development down. hopefully its more like the minecraft console port where updates were seperate and more focus was put into finishing the main title.It feels like minecraft with a purpose, often in minecraft you'll build defences that you just dont need and never really get challenged. Here when you build a castle with a moat and spikes here its to defend yourself. Real stratagies are needed in order to survive and the 7th day horde is a fear that always sit in the back of your mind. I do feel as though its not as pretty as minecraft, I often found myself wanting more colours and different textures. It also lacks (at least as far as I know) the modding community but these are both things that by the time the final game comes out may not be a concern.Overall its worth a buy, but is better with a friend(s). It does have a bit of a shelf life though. The late game feels a little empty and easy, the hardest enemys are no longer too much of a threat and with no goal to accomplish other than to survive and be self sustaining it runs into a plateau  problem. It does have a litany of difficulty measures to help prevent this as long as possible but it is a constant eventuality. It does have great replayablity though and i have played several times over. I can't comment on the multiplayer severs as I've only played with mates but from what I've heard they are stable and relatively grief free."
