,Recommended,251570,25391316,"Posted: 6 September, 2016",all,Microsoft Word,"tldr - see at bottom.This game is still in early access, and I have to say that it's one of the few games whose developers are very active and always working on improvements. A large amount of features have been changed since its early-access debut, and much content has been added.This in itself is good, but it also brings a downside. The problem is that whenever a big update is released there is a high chance of your old save file no longer work, effectively wiping your progress. If you are not dissuaded by this fact and are willing to restart from scratch multiple times before the full release, then by all means do. I've done it a number of times, and I had fun exploring new content and mechanics each time.Other than that, the game is currently in a fairly solid state. The crafting mechanics are refined, the skill system is fun, and the survival features are fair and punishing. It's not the most difficult game to get into, but it's also not the easiest, so expect to die several times before getting the hang of exploration, combat, crafting, inventory management and survival bars.tldr: Solid game. Active development with frequent updates. Some updates wipe progress and have you restart from scratch."
