,Not Recommended,251570,11274011,"Posted: 16 July, 2014",all,Klingenmeister,"Since the team deleted several options for difficulty adjustments month ago and try to restrict the player more and more, I am forced to take back my thumb up for the game.You dont restrict the players choice, how he plays the game in an open world sandbox. The point of a sandbox is, to do whatever you want. If I want to set the zombie damage to max and their health to lowest, so I can one hit them and they can one hit me, why deleting that option?Whywouldyoudeleteafeaturein a game?also since 12.0 the citys are to far away from each other + caves are nearly patched out of the game (another restriction, great!) + there are no random ores in the ground anymore = 90% of the map is empty land you just have to walk through, with a few buildings between.Another good Zombie game idea became a walking simulator.- Also with 12.0 a player of my group encountered an exploit to duplicate infinite amount of ressources- the trunk of the new bike is bugged and simply deletes what I am putting into- the bears look dangerous in the preview pictures, but are slow stupid creatures, that are more sad than an actual dangerThe new loot system is completly broken. Why? The new player loot system works with your player level. The higher level you have, the higher loot you get. If you loot all cars with lvl 1, you wont get new higher level car parts later. Since cars are the survivors first loot choice, because they often have metal tools in the beginning of the game, they are empty before anyone has a decent level.Why does this game even have finite and infinite loot places? Why, after all this time, are cars still not respawning loot?This is the most decent zombie game sandbox out there, totally outranking games like DayZ and other, but the way Ive seen all those month the developers giving a♥♥♥♥♥♥about their community (like the pages over pages of people wanting the old difficulty settings back) I will no longer support this game.---(this is a review on the current state of the game, 16.07.2014, version 8.7)german review:http://www.topfree.de/7-days-to-die-7d2dYou are the only survivor! Run away, punch a tree, build a house!I had this game on the radar for a long time, but since the whole ""early access"" system is more like ""maybe we finish this game"", I couldnt get myself buying this game.But unlike many other early access this game is a lot of fun, even in its current state.Description:You start in a random position of the current map ""navezgane"". Around you, you find damaged cars, trash, buildings and camp sides. Everything is lootable and you can enter every building unlike the old dayZ (burn in hell for wasting 20€ of mine). You find a lot of stuff, that is usable (like food and weapons) and a lot of stuff, that doesnt look useful. But there is no item in this game you can call useless. Even empty cans you can transform into scrap metal and the moldy bread, that can kill you, if you eat it, can be used to make antibiotiks.And here we come to a great part of the game: The crafting system!At first looking completly confusing and not user friendly, it is a well thought system of item combinations (like in minecraft) that allows you to build any item you desire. Each craftable item has a tooltipp on the right side of your crafting table, so you always can look for help, if you dont know how to craft an item.But wait, there is more!Since this game dont want to be just another arcade sandbox game, it has some difficultys in its crafting and building system.You simply cant go into the woods and punch a tree. First, you have to find a tool in one of the abandoned buildings, or you are creative and craft a stone tool.Also crafting of a simple iron axe, pickaxe or showel is easy, but crafting a gun? This is where the fun is getting started. If you want to craft a pistol, you first have to find a few. Then you have to dissassemble them and use clay to make molds for every gun part. Every item you have to craft in the oven needs a mold. Every ingot, every gun part, cement, glass...Some rare items like snipers and SMGs are a long time project until you are able to craft them.Doing this alone is a real pain in the♥♥♥♥♥ This game rewards you for playing in a team. Every member has their job and some are scavenging, some are crafting and some are building and defending the base. A good group can hold and defend a large area.Unlike dayZ players are still your worst enemy, but PvP is a bad idea in most cases. Depending on your server config zombies be really tough, not only swarming you with howling mindless flesh eaters, but also throwing zombies at you, that can climb, dig, spit acid, be really tanky or crawling and hiding in the grass. With some non human zombies and mutation as allies, they are capable of raiding complete player bases, sometimes with hordes over 100 zombies at once.The game is still in its early stages, having only a handful of guns (2 shotguns, 2 pistols, 1 sniper, 1 smg and some explosive weapons you can discover for yourself), building bases out of wood, stone or concrete, crafting, a simple stealth systeme and a simple building integrity systembutpromising random maps, vehicles, more guns, more zombie types and a lot of other stuffit is worth taking a look at.I only talked about the basic aspects, since I dont want to spoil too many gameplay aspects for you, you surely wanne discover by yourself.Short:Will the game be worth it, when it is released? - YesIs the game playable and worth it in its current state? - Yes(remember: Bring friends, this is not a single player game)addition:For an early access game, that is based on a voxel system created map, made by an indie developer this game has some amazing grafics! Playing this on an outdated Gaming laptop I had an Fps rate of 20 - 30. It feels and looks more stable and ressource friendly than minecraft and other similar styled games and runs for hours without a single crash.So far I encountered nothing I could call a bug.Sure I sometimes glitched through the ceiling while mining, zombie AI is acting really weird sometimes and running zombies are ignoring bullets sometimes, but no crashes or gamebreaking bugs so far."
76561197979999026,Recommended,251570,17520850,"Posted: 13 August, 2015",all,Sister Spike,"I recommend this game for these reasons:You are immersed in a beautiful environment. Forests, deserts, snowy mountains, stunning skies. It gets more realistic with each update. Currently they are fine-tuning a new weather system. I strenuously object to the dense fog which in some locations is almost constant, obscuring the beauty, reducing visibility, and contributing nothing to game play. As other new features have been adapted, I trust this one also will be.The game allows for many play styles and ability levels. I am a clumsy coward and play defensively. Others are hot-shot warriors and roam the wilderness from Day One. The game has a steep learning curve, but re-starting is still fun. The learning is fun. It does not feel tedious or frustrating. Well, maybe once in awhile!The game is always new. I am a responsible adult with a real life, yet I have been so hooked by this game that I am embarrassed to see how many hours I've logged in it. I have not been sucked into a game like this for many years. Not since PS2 Mercenaries, another sandbox game. If you feel you've reached a plateau in your world, and it's not as interesting, you just start all over fresh. It is never the same twice.The game stretches you to try new styles, to explore, to experiment. Playing solo as I do, I am having to be a multi-tasker and figure out how to collect resources, hunt, discover and loot points of interest, fight with both melee and ranged weapons, and build a good strong base. And, there is some interior decorating involved as well!7D2D is still an alpha, yet I have played over 700 hours and more than got my money's worth. You know there will be bumps in the road with an Alpha, but the point here is the road keeps going and around every bend is something new to figure out or explore. I recommend you be patient with the bumps and keep on going."
