,Recommended,251570,18720728,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,[BUG] Shadow,"This is by far the best early access game I have come across.  The development points are consistant and each time a major update happens, it is really a major update.  Multiple minor updates follow, for fixes and tweaks as the major update gets vetted buy the community.  The game is good, and is getting better with each update.  The developers listen to the community and while  thankfully they do not adopt everything they listen and seriously consider it.  One of the nice things the developers do, is show things that are currently in development, and what to expect in the next major update.  This lets you know that the developers are working hard and have excellent ideas on improving the game.I really like their release system - it works.  Major updates are great for showcasing new and exciting features.  Minor updates show a definite interest in keeping the bug count under control.  It is very tempting to run rampant with new ideas and features while basics take a back seat or is ignored.  What you end up with is a great idea for a game that was poorly implemented.  Concentrating on just the basics without much on the new features is just as bad.  You would end up with a great game if it was released yester-year.  It is hard to keep a good balance.I believe this is a fine example on how early access should be done."
