76561198122411333,Recommended,251570,8994779,"Posted: 6 February, 2014",all,PhantomKnightXX,"After reading through reviews and watching a few clips of 7D2D in action, this game looked like something I would enjoy playing.  Understanding that it was still in Alpha stages I decided to invest the $35 and give it a try.  If you also decide to purchase it, remember that it is not a finalized or polished project and will be updated and changed as you play.  After 50+ hours of gameplay with the majority of that playing by myself, I will try to help any of those interested buyers decide one way or the other.  Take note, I am currently in Afghanistan so my internet connection is why I was not able to fully test the PvP aspect of this game fully.Potential-This game has a huge amount of potential and with each major update gets closer to it.  With what they plan on including in the final version of the game, I am excited to see how it plays out.  Right now though I don't see the cost being a correct value of the current game.Day/Night Cycle-The main difference in the time of day is the speed of the zombies.  They will sprint at night unless a light source is close to them.  So it produces an effect of resource gathering during the day and base building/defending during the night.Building-With the blocks not being squared, it adds realism to what you make. The thing that i enjoyed the most was that you needed to plan on building a structure that supports itself due to the fact that gravity affects every block. I have had the floor fallout from under me cause of that.Map-Large enough where it will take you a decent amount of time and resources to transverse but not big enough to the point of never exploring the other side of the map due to enemies or distance.  Currently have multiple ""zones"" where you find different plants and resources.  The locations of interest are sparsely spaced and with only two towns of note, keeps you on the go to find resources.Crafting-With no tutorial on what to do, it is all trail and error to craft anything.  When you have the correct items to make something, it shows in the crafting menu.  By clicking that item it will show you the blocks in the 5x5 grid that need to be filled to craft it.  Once you have crafted it, you will automatically remember which items you will need for future crafting.Stamina-Limits your ability to run or hit with full force.  Regenerates over time.  Creates a harder playing experience because you have to pay attention to it.  When it is low, you do less damage to blocks and creatures. Having the right tool for the job is almost a requirment in this game on any difficulty beyone easy.Hunger/Thirst-They constantly decrease and when low, you lose health and don't regenerate stamina.  Finding food and water is essential to survive.  Making your base by a water source takes care of that need and farming will fix the issue of food. Trying to hole up in a remote location only works after you have worked out a steady source of both.Enemies-The zombies being the main focus, are the typical movie zombie. During the day you get the slow bumbling side and at night the sprinting deadlier side.  Some different types to defend against increase the difficulty but not by much.  There are giant hornets for an aerial threat which might not fit the zombie theme but create an added item to consider when building something.  Zombie dogs are always fast and will attack from nowhere. Right now they tend to spin in circles when attacking you making it more of an annoyance then threat.  The main enemy to look out for is other people.A.I.-Until they finally update the A.I. of the zombies, the gameplay will never be what it should be.  The zombies currently know exactly where you are at regardless of anything.  For me, that has been my biggest complaint on this game. Thankfully it will be fixed within an update or two.CO-OP-This is where the game really shines.  Working with a few other people to create a fuctioning base of operations and to defend each other from the zombies or other players is what this game is all about.  If you have a large enough group of friends, creating two or more teams and trying to destroy/loot each other will easily siphon hours of your life away.  Once I am back in the States I will be focusing entirely on this aspect of the game.As it stands, I reccomend purchasing this game if you have a few friends that you will play with.  Surviving by yourself or just playing around in creative mode does not get close to what I feel is the greatest aspect of this game. A note prior to purchasing this, if you did not like minecraft, i would not recommend this game. 7D2D plays and feels similiar with just a greater focus on suriving than building."
