,Recommended,251570,10096222,"Posted: 12 May, 2014",all,Saiko,"I previously bought Rust as it was supposedly survival based, but turned out to be survival whilst getting trolled by someone who has access to guns already. This game I expected to be somewhere on the same level, but I was wrong.This game actually exceeded my expectations totally! Most early access title these days are half arsed and wind up going down the toilet rather swiftly as the updates become scarce. Again not the case with this game as updates seem to be happening on a weekly - fortnightly basis. What is more, you don't have to buy a server to play with your friends - You have all the tools you need included in the actual download, just click the server config, set it up and run the server file. Done.The AI is currently not the brightest as they will just throw themselves into your bullets but it is enough to get the job done and this will be addressed in a later patch with AI Pathing. I only recently figured out the building system in the game, it is unique (well I've never seen anything like it at least) in the sense that you can start with just the foundations of your house/base and upgrade it as opposed to destroying a block and replacing it with a new one with more durability. Crafting is also different as it will tell you what you are able to craft based on the items in your inventory, but, until you allocate the right items into the grid in the correct way it won't tell you how to craft something.Granted that can become a bit annoying at times, but that is what google is for! Weapons can be crafted also, as can ammo but you have to locate and learn recipies from books you can find in homes and towns... Filled with zombies, zombie dogs and some odd hornet type bugs that will scare the crap out of you eventually.It has it's flaws, but not nearly as many as some of the games out there today. I'd say if you are into the whole survival aspect then give this a go. The game does also feature PvP so you can setup a game where you can kill another player and take their items/base (base after a set timeframe as they just implemented land ownership) should you wish."
