76561198058752653,Recommended,251570,9301203,"Posted: 1 March, 2014",all,Dude,"This game is AWESOME!  If you liked minecraft's survival aspect, and wanted a single player version (ie not instant death) of rust, this is for you.You basically have to scavenge for food/water/resources, while killing/looting zombies/trash (dumpster diving anyone?).  You get to hunt deer, pigs, and rabbits for food and pelts (leather), you chop trees, mine resources, and you can even farm!  You can smelt various ores into pure bars, and with weapons you find you can make molds of their component parts (you have to break them down) and make as many as you need (provided you mine enough)  Currently, I have an upgraded wooden/metal base that has an upstairs hydroponics.  AWESOME!!!As of the current 9.2 build, they fixed the problem of not being able to hit the crawlers without getting the grass first (Thank you!) and the zombies move a little faster in daylight (still walking, thank you!)  Although, torch light and campfires have NO effect on them at night.  Please help!AlsoThere is less loot generated, so what you do find IS more precious.  I have played this for a while now, and every time I would have tons of food (hunted and scavenged)  Now, finding cans of food is more precious than finding materials, and farming actually becomes important - VERY GOOD!!!  That is true survival.Was thinking that having (hunted) and cooked food should deteriorate over time, that way having a cooler/electricity for refrigerator would be a welcome addition later in the game, but I'm honestly rethinking that now.  The loot change is actually Very good and instantly makes things feel more valuable.  Still, be nice to introduce electricity with the posibility of electric lights/flood lights, automated turrets, gas/coal/stirling engine electricity (small/simple) with posibility of solar (either direct solar power, or use mirrors/glass during the day to boil water for steam engine, and wood/coal gas at night)The above would be great for heating when weather effects come into play.  Need to be able to craft winter clothing, but leather should help (maybe bunny fur lined leather?)How about putting car batteries to use would be nice for night, and maybe introducing laptop/cellphone electronics would be nice (crafting turrents later, or as an add-on pack)  Maybe have small AA batteries or similiar for hand warmers/""pack"" warmers to put into clothing (pockets or slots in clothing, similiar to electric blanket.  While having to keep an eye on charge, and scavenge for batteries)How about introducing rain, so we could collect it with drains in houses for building away from rivers/lakes?Pipe bombs are nice, but how about home-made grenades?  Either that, or make their area of effect wider, or some kind of timer (audible noise) so I know when to throw it...... just a suggestion!How about a zombie that starts off a little taller but skinnier than the rest, that gets bigger (like the size of a sky scraper) by ingesting/incorporating other zombies into him.  Also, have the other zombies attack/be aggressive towards him (there's too much attention on you, be nice to have some zombie on zombie or monster on zombie action), that way the interaction between the inhabitants keep things interesting.Any way you slice it, This is a game that is setting the bar for survival games.  Tired of straight run and gun, go here shoot this there games?  This is for you.  You can build what you want, hunt what you want, craft everything you need while still looting for important resources.  We need more points of interest, and a bit more than just looting, but that is coming soon. Graphics are Much better than minecraft, and even though not as good as AAA games, it gets the job done, looks good, and better than most other voxel games."
