76561198011549320,Not Recommended,251570,20230174,"Posted: 2 January, 2016",all,officerdoofy790,"I truly would not reccommend this game in its current state. (TL;DR at bottom)Alpha 13 has ruined this game. Period. I've played since Alpha 9 launched and it was previously one of my top 5 favorite games. I loved the immersion, crafting system, and combat (even with all the bugs). However, since the patch, everything I've known has changed into an abomination (an HD abomination, though, so there's that!).Good:1. New Zombie Models. They are gorgeous to look at.2. Overall graphical improvements. Houses appear more realistic, as do some biomes. Really nice on the whole.Bad:1. The overall UI. It looks like hell. Instead of bringing up something fully interactive, I find it a chore to even drag and drop items now. Also, it covers the entire screen, appears out of place, and is just plain clunky. Don't even get me started on all the bugs with it...2. The weird zombie dance routine. Does it look cool watching it the first couple times (I stress the first couple times)? Yes. Does it look cool watching that zombie shamble and dance around your arrows/bullets? Not really. Does it look cool when those arrows/bullets hit micrometers below the head and thus do virtually no damage? No. Honestly, this looked impressive in their teaser video, but in practice, it gets extremely annoying at best.3. Dumbing down aspects of the game. Where the hell are the sticks? Where are the different meats? Where is the resource diversity that made me want to go after certain resource hubs rather than just punch a couple trees for an hour? It's absolutely atrocious at this time.4. Weapon/armor durability and crafting said weapons/armor.  There is absolutely no logical reason for some material requirements compared to others. Especially early game. I shouldn't need to tear the cloth out of three separate houses to make some cloth armor, and then have said armor cause me to die of heatstroke. Which brings me to...5. Temperature gauges. Terrible idea. Terrible implementation of said idea. Terrible environmental interactions because of said idea. Did I mention it was terrible? Why would I ever want to explore a desert or tundra again? Look up 'terrible'. This idea is listed twice under its definition.I could keep going but I think I'd be beating a dead horse by doing so.TL:DR: The game was great. Yes, it had flaws. Yes, it had bugs. Yes, the graphics were average. However, all of those things led to having players focus more on the gameplay. Great graphics do not equal a great game. Crafting and gathering are now unbearable, combat is a joke, and the game has lost the sense of where it was heading. As many others have said, the game was highly reccommended a month ago, but now has too many flaws to list. Please consider playing something else until they fix what they've done!"
