,Recommended,251570,14963385,"Posted: 19 March, 2015",all,Doom721,"I bought this game some time ago, many alpha builds before and it has come a very long way. I buy a lot of early access games and this is one of the few that actually has updated and progressed into a much better game over time.So you either start off in a prefabricated city, with set areas - or a randomly generated world with buildings strewn about into biomes ala Minecraft. Cities, forests, snowy areas, deserts etc. Seperated by rivers.The game is pretty unforgiving at times, but there are a lot, I mean A LOT of modular difficulty settings. You can change a lot of things with zombies, loot, time of day, air drops before you even get rolling.One comment I make a lot is this is the game I was personally looking for out of early alpha Minecraft. Though totally different games I expected a ""survival"" game and well Minecraft is a creative game first and foremost.You go along in 7 days, struggling to find food and water - constantly being attacked while trying to sneak away. Eventually making a safe haven. It starts to seem easy as you build up supplies, crates, beds ( spawn points ) and amass food, water. You think things are going well. This is all until you get farther along. By yourself this game is a challenge to survive if you don't build smart enough, or strong enough. Every seven days a wave of zombies come at night, each week gets harder and its in addition to all the zombie waves you attract from making tons of noise building, smell from killing etc.The game sometimes is an anti-game out to kill you depending on who you play with, or don't. You can change respawning loot settings, random gen worlds are massive and you can build above or below ground - but physics do apply in building so you can only stretch out that wooden pole platform so long before it needs supports. Supports zombies will kill. They will break♥♥♥♥♥♥so fast if it isn't durable, they are definitely a threat.I'm writing my review of this game during Alpha 10. As of exactly now performance is lacking and visually the game needed an overhaul which is coming in the upcoming build Alpha 11 and its switch to Unity 5. If you are looking for a sandbox survival game that actually encompasses survival I would say this is a fair challenge as long as you tweak the zombies up a bit, played it alone and in four player coop - with a few bugs ( sometimes you can't add in-game friends and see their marker etc ) but overall its pretty stellar."
