76561197961928270,Recommended,251570,8076485,"Posted: 16 December, 2013",all,KarlMonster,"In the future, a new strain of wild blueberries causes a Zombie Apocalypse. The whole world has fallen apart. Now you appear; alone, unarmed and with no supplies.You can do this! Search that car! Search what is left of the driver! Guns and ammo are not hard to find, but zombies, well - the woods are full of them! So you need more. You need equipment. You need a hunting knife, and a spiked club, then some barbed wire. You can't run forever, so you need building materials. A shovel and pickaxe would be just the thing. So how do you get those things? You make them!You start by punching a bush to get sticks. Then scavenge some scrap metal. Everyone's a zombie now, so they won't care that you just turned their lamppost into a garden hoe. Like a certain *other* game, your best hope of shelter on the first day will be to dig a hole in the ground and hide there, crying. With the pickaxe you have access to better and better building materials; now you can finally build yourself some shelter - except that the zombies can (eventually) break through stone blocks. How will you survive?More importantly, why aren't you playing this game right now?To be fair, the crafting system will baffle new players. You can only get a template to make a new item if you already have all of the components in your inventory. However, for an early access game, 7DtD already has everything that I ever wanted in Zombie Survival Horror.Edit: (Fall 2014) ... and then there was this time that I was in a house, with zombies outside beating on the walls. Then I found a motorized augur in the house, and discovered that I could use it on zombies. I didn't get out alive, but I had SO much fun trying!"
