,Recommended,251570,32308908,Posted: 9 June,all,metal_max_90,"Summary: This game, in my opinion, is hands down THE best Early Access title available on Steam - I have had thousands upon thousands of hours of fun, and it definitely worth the money I paid for it back in Alpha 13, at least 100 times over.7 Days to Die is dubbed 'The Survival Horde Crafting Game' by the developers, which is pretty much accurate although there is a TON to do in the game, way more than can be described in these few words.The survival aspect is very well done. The basics are all there - food, water, body temperature, but it doesn't stop there. Making good decisions will lead to your character becoming healthier over time, increasing their longevity to turn the tides in potentially deadly situations. But, make a bad call and you may find your character crippled with deadly diseases that are hard to cure, especially in the early game. You can keep your character healthy by eating good food - hunt game out in the wilderness or try and sneak into a house to scavenge jars of drinkable water, or luck out with a can of chicken soup. Some wild plants can also be used to make wellness-raising drinks that are even better for you than just boiled water. Knowledge is power!Your character will grow more skilled over time as they partake in activities. Building, fighting, crafting, repairing, exploring and scavenging will all contribute towards your character's skills. The skills sysem is quite in-depth. At the start of the game, your character will only have the skills necessary to create basic stone tools, which aren't the best at harvesting resources. But, as your character levels up they can unlock perks to make better quality tools, do more damage with both melee and ranged weapons, scavenge more effectively, or even survive for longer between eating and drinking, which could be crucial for long journeys. The way you build your character is totally up to you and roleplaying is fun in 7 Days to Die.And what good is survival and skills, without a beautiful world to explroe? Well, no need to answer that - 7 Days has got you covered. There are currently two world types you can play. Navezgane is the default, hand-crafted map that has been developed since the game's initial release, which expands nearly every new build. It's a small-ish map, but there is still plenty to do and many places to go and explore, including four major towns filled to the brim with loot (and of course, deadly zombies!) There is also a Random Gen (RWG) option. With RWG the map is built from a seed name, and it is much larger. In the most recent patch, the RWG has been completely overhauled and looks gorgeous. Lush green forests, plains and deserts, snowy tundras, and burned down forests (and sometimes entire cities!) will all generate in RWG. You never know what you're going to get. Survive in the wilderness and build your own base, or try to follow a road to a town and clear it out to claim as your own. Every RWG is a completely different experience.So, what's the point of all this? Well, survive as long as you can, eventually thriving. Live off the land, claim it as your own. Sounds good in theory, but the zombies aren't willing to let you do that. Every 7 days, the blood moon rises, turning the sky red, storms brew. Something in the air seems to turn the zombies nasty, and I mean REALLY nasty. They will start to hunt you on the 7th night in waves, each week getting tougher and tougher than the one before. You can either build a base to defend yourself in the week leading up to it, or take them on. The best part is that the hordes are dynamic and how well you have done in the week will determine how tough the horde is. If you're a new player and don't progress as quickly, the game can recognise this and will give you less zombies to fight on a horde night. If you're a seasoned survivor, you're going to have a tougher time! This in my opinion helps keep the game extremely fun - you're always going to feel challenged.Pros:- A new experience every time.- The game settings are very customisable.- Very easy to mod the game to change or add things.- Gorgeous random world generation.- Great mix of melee and ranged combat.- Some zombies have special abilities!- Crafting is intuitive and lots of different workstations.- You can build your own base or fortify a building to survive.- Zombies aren't your only threat.- Can play multiplayer, team up with friends.- Great developers and stream team, overall great community of players.Note: This game is still in Alpha. Some complain about this, however in my opinion I'm happy for it to stay that way for as long as needed. The developers are always adding new things into the game, new mechanics are getting introduced with every alpha. We're fortunate to have a team of devs that still put in their best efforts to make the game as best it can be even after so many copies have sold. That is the mark of a dedicated development team and one I will continue to support."
