,Recommended,251570,8134013,"Posted: 19 December, 2013",all,The Semp,"It's been a long while since my original review, and in that time the game has changed greatly. What once looked like a minecraft clone has grown into one of the first games to manage procedural generation in a non-voxel world.Now more than ever I recommend this game. It's fun solo, but even better when you get in with a PvE community and start networking. It becomes about who has access to lots of clay, ores, and wood fairly quickly creating a supply and demand barter economy that's rather fun. Building large bases to fend off zombie hordes with one or multiple friends is rewarding, especially with a recent combat revamp that makes killing zeds that much more satisfying.I'd like to point out the interactivity of the developers. As of this writing it's been a couple of weeks since the last major release, and they've spent that interim time patching the hell out of the game so it would work perfectly. Hell, they gave us a patch on Christmas Eve!In short, this game is fun and worth your time. The developers have built trust with the community, and there's a lot of flexibility in how you can make the experience your own. And of course, if you're that guy who likes to murder and rob people for their canned goods, their is PVP as well (;Just play it."
