76561198036086903,Not Recommended,251570,30958544,Posted: 5 April,all,Zadraax,"I played 7 Days to die a while ago and stopped once already.This game is really good in it's core mechanics and you can build almost everything from scrap, even in ""late"" game it will surprise you through recipes you didn't guessed before. The level up system is quite good and force every new players either to scaly build stuff from stone > wood > iron > forge iron > steel creating a real crafting rewarding environment.You may be lucky enough to find some good stuff through looting but as it is also degradable finding steel tool will only gime you a timely advantage if you're still stuck on iron (because you can't repair).All action in 7DTD will reward you with experience that will allow you to unlock new crafting knowledge or core competencies (bargaining, survivability,...)It may seems at first that you spend more ressources than you get, but with better tools comes better rewards.The turnoff in this game for me are zombies. I have to admit I am not openminded about zombies and dislike anything that could be else than running, walking and crawling zeds. Here you will encounter spitting zed, dogs zed, spider human zed,... for a classic zombie lover I was surprise to see thoses zed almost not being damage by my traps and climbing the walls my fortress.Dog zeds are the bigest pain in the a** to me as at the current time they are unpredictable. Once they spot you they will charge in straigh line making it easy to shoot, unless it's on damaged ground. In that case they will dash right and left untill they get to then will proced to maul you to death while jumping right and left making it so hard to defend yourself in melee combat. They're are ways to defeat them like running backward like shooting but meh,...Of course it's worse when you fall on a zombie dog pack.It as to be had to a poor zombie spawning management and IA with zed sometimes going explicitely for you base, zeds spawning zeroed on you, zeds finding you even if you're below earth, not moving, not doing a thing.I played with minimum zed spaws and overall easy settings. I would like to personalise which zeds I would encounter much more. I would love to increase zeds spawning, but if it comes with more weirdo, that's a no.Surviving, crafting and leveling do really takes enough time already. That would be fair not be mauled by unsane zed that randomly spawn all around.Therefore, recommanding the game for the crafting and survival aspect, but the zeds still need a lot of work (or options) and ruin the game to me.(Additionnal notes: the game is still in A15 and run moderatly good (playable medium FPS but sometimes FPS droprate). It crashed sometimes, for me, once every 2 or 3 hours.)"
