,Recommended,251570,13448990,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,ivanx,"7dtd is an amazing game. A bit sharp at the beginning, it gets you sucked in more and more with every next minute. Making a zombie survival minecraft was originally a great idea, and devs sure gave that idea a solid support.Here are main ideas:- at day you: scavange, build, fortify, hunt, craft, melt, mine- at night you hide in your lair trying to make the least noise possible, and if you were unlucky enough to hit night far away from base - sit on some roof hoping nothing comes for you, and not moving an inch. Zombies at night are feral, fast and deadly- everything is destructible, from most items you get back scrap materials, sometimes even the whole thing to reuse, but not everything is worth scrapping, you lose axe/pick durability, stamina and time to scrap items, some of them don't give you back as much- even ground is destructible up to 64 levels below water level, that is called mining, you can make tunnels, mine minerals and refine them into metals, powder.- zombies can surprise you, so you should stay vigilant all the time, unless you've made a solid house and is currently camping in it- water, food and diseases are another thing to be worried about when not fighting zombies- grid-based crafting with hundreds recipes, more are comming up with periodic updates- create or find medicine, create or find food, create or find clothes/armor- farm to get fresh veggiesDownsides:- the first glance at the game is a bit unappealing, graphics seem a bit outdated, but after you played it for a few hours it already seems awesome. Graphics are at half-life2 level, maybe. so 2008-ish. Don't expect crysis/far cry 3-like textures.- zombies sometimes get confused, especially when your base is built on a pilar (no exterior walls touching the ground, but i guess they are brainless creeps, so why would they know they need to destroy a pillar somwhere to collapse it?- currently if you set something cooking, refining or grow plants, trees, the progress stops as soon as you run too far from it, and no players pass by. As for cooking not only it would stop, but also the wood would still burn out - while no progresss to cooking is made,- items sometimes ""drop"" without player noticing, and all the dropped items disappear after 1 minute. So If you craft something in huge amounts and have no space in inventory. Once you open inventory all the stuff that can't be placed will be dropped on the ground silently. Same for accidently right clicking while selecting item. Also if your items are stored in a crate or any other container, once the container is destroyed, items will disappear. Hopesfuly devs would fix those inconveniences.- i've heard stories about waves of cheating, fortunately i've only been playing with friends and on protected servers, so i have yet to meet any.All the downsides do not affect gameplay much, but it would be perfect without them.Should you buy this game, if you're a fan of survivals or minecraft? - YES, absolutely!Should you wait for sale to buy it as cheap as a sandwich? - Wtf are you thinking!? Gather all your money in a cardboard box and send it to devs right NOW. Gabe already took enough of your money!Warning: this game is so addictive that you might lose your sleep, because you would not be able to stop think about it anymore"
