76561198048914044,Not Recommended,251570,10965719,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Vividry,"First off, I want to say that this game has an INCREDIBLE amount of potential and that as a customer I look forward to the final release. However, unfortunately I cannot recommend this game to anyone at its current full retail value. Again, this is an early access review as of Alpha 8.6 and I will update my review when and if it is fully released or it significantly improves.When I first bought this game I was hopeful for it as its premise sounded promising. The prospect of searching abandoned cities, surviving in a post-apocalyptic world, and building a house or crafting weapons and traps to fight off zombies and other invaders was too good to pass up. I must admit though, I only purchased this game because it was 45% off during the summer sale and I scratched my head at the initial $25 price tag that comes with its full price. However, I thought that surely it would be well worth it once I began to play... it was't.Is it a game worth playing? Absolutely. Is it worth $25? No. There is just not enough content in this game for me to recommend it at a $25 price tag. The graphics are good for sure, but the mechanics could use some work. There is lag when switching from one item to the next and it's rather irritating when being chased by zombies or dogs. And that brings up a couple other things: zombies and dogs. Zombies are everywhere! Now obviously, you'd expect zombies to exist in such a world, but it makes it more annoying than fun or challenging when you escape a zombie horde or finish killing off 5-10 zombies with your gun in an effort to protect your house only to have them respawn moments later. Now you're out of bullets, surrounded by zombies once again, and pretty much screwed.Of course, you could consider that more of an opinion than a problem with the game, but that personally kind of ruins the fun for me. It also kills the suspense. If there are zombies everywhere all the time, even in the woods and deserts, it gets boring rather quickly. The next point I wanted to discuss was the over-powered dogs. Run into these nasty animals and they WILL kill you. There are no ifs, ands, or buts about it. It probably took me at least four restarts before I wasn't killed by a dog, and one of those times it spawned me right next to one... thanks. It was such a deterrent that I almost gave up on the game right then and there, but pride wouldn't let me.Also, with regards to aesthetics, while I mentioned the graphics looked good for it still being in alpha the landscape is rather bland. Trash piles are everywhere for some strange reason and some of the buildings look like they were pretty much just copied and pasted. Naturally, this is what I would expect in an alpha stage game, but not at a $25 price tag. That said, the biomes in this game are pretty cool and I definitely thought they made it much better. Having different enviornments in a game like this makes it much more interesting.Anyways, while I have a lot to look forward to with the development of this game I just can't bring myself to give it a positive review right now given the price. I hope my review has been helpful for anyone looking to purchase this game. If not, well, in the end only you can decide whether it's worth it or not."
