76561198012923593,Not Recommended,251570,25949007,"Posted: 9 October, 2016",all,Blech,"This game has been in development for ever and ever (and ever ever).It still lacks basically the entire range mid -and engame content, with the game quickly becomming boring.When you have played the game for 10 hours, you will be able to start a new game and explore all the game has to offer within 10 hours, especially if you have a team of 2-4 members. Most of the time in your first game will be learning the mechanics, which i wouldn't describe as replayable gameplay.When a new game is stated, it is pretty much 2 hours to get a base going, 4 hours to get ready to plunder zombie infested areas, and after that you will very quickly get to a point where zombies are no longer a real danger.But the biggest flaw in this game by far, is its lack of anything to do. Once you have gotten your base up and running and raided for schematics and weapons, there is really nothing else to aspire to, other than defending against zombie hordes. There are no npc villages to build, no infrastructure to maintain, and nothing to evolve. There is your base, and the zombies. Period.For me, the game quickly becomes tiresome. There is nothing to strive towards, except the next ware of zombies. Surviving the zombies very quickly becomes the primary objective of the game. They stop being a hinderence for the actual objectives (Get tools, build shelter, get food, survive) and take their place as the sole objective (Have a base after horde night).If you are like me, and want to see some actual progression, be it an expanding shelter, more options, new assignments, evolving gameplay and so on, this game will quickly stop being all that fun. I have a hard time finding motivation to keep going 20 hours into a session.I realize that i have a fair number of hours in the game. I have picked it up and played it with friends through a number of updates. But the real question is: Would i, knowing what i do now, buy the game to play it for the first time, for the price? No, no i would not."
