,Not Recommended,251570,21490513,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Zeonhart,"I wanted to like this game a lot. I really did. When I first started, It had an interesting concept and enough content to get an idea of the direction they were heading. But now it feels like the game has gone in some other direction, and... it's just not fun any more.Perhaps the one, single, most devastating mechanic they added to the game, that takes away any fun at all, is the grind. Anything and everything you do takes in excess of 30 seconds to several MINUTES to complete. Building a simple wall, destroying a simple tree. I get the whole ""realistic"" appeal but it doesn't translate well into gameplay mechanics. If I want to mine into the earth, I shouldn't have to do it block-by-block if each block takes a full minute to excavate. It's just fecking boring.And then they added a penalty to dying. You know what? I like penalties for death. Dark Souls is one of my favorite games of all time. But you want to know the difference? When I die in Dark Souls, it feels like it's my fault. When I die in 7DTD, it's usually because 3 zombie dogs came sprinting at me like Usain Bolt with a bad case of diarrhea, and instantly surrounded me because I have no hope in hell of ever outrunning them the moment I hear a single bark, and they tear me to shreds in seconds. Sound like I'm salty over an isolated incident? This has happened the last 10 times I've tried getting back into this game. And it's never due to my own actions, it just happens seemingly as a random event.But I'm digressing. You know what the penalty for dying is? You lose 10% of your max HP and stamina. How do you get it back? Eating food. Seems simple right? Well, eating rare food you find once in a blue moon restores half a point, and you can only eat it once every 5-10 minutes or so, granted you have more than one piece. Doesn't help if you die again, that's another 10 points you have to restore.This game is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥."
