76561198056695587,Not Recommended,251570,21581315,"Posted: 2 March, 2016",all,Morghulis,"To review: Look at objectively with hindsight is my own personal dictionary definition. Having jumped on-board with a friend, we were looking for something different, he had played Rust, but the reviews kept me away. This seemed like the best deal for me, I am not a MP pew pewer or ganker or griefer. Just to old for minecraft....and I like to blow zombies heads off with shotguns. For a while 7dtd provided me with a tense, survivalish, base building experience. Even put it on creative as survival mode used to be too stressful.I wanted open world with interaction and story. I actually believed we were gonna get populated towns, with which we could interact. For the moment, we get a game where you die, until you get a base that is defendable, Combat is system dependant, and no doubt with top end you have no problem with the hitboxes, but on lower spec machines...dog=die, cops=acid that flies for miles with no regard for cover. Then again as soon as you have your farming set up....shotguns work well...even handguns do they trick, if you have built a base yourself.But that's fine, this can be remedied (although time is running out) even if the devs are not triple A level, I do think they should be scrumming this a bit tighter. But yet again a review is with hindsight, early access when this came out was relatively new on steam. So in essence there needs to be a point when early access stops. I can preorder a sofa, but I still want the sofa delivered so that I can sit on it!!!I love the tension you have at the start until the first red moon. If your base is not defendable....you can hide in the cold or warmth, changing between your lovingly scavenged beanie and football helmet, at each crack of the grass or site of a screamer.By the 4th moon, you have already built Minis tirith, with a TV lounge, bar, possibly even designed a cafeteria for your friends, who can all come and spend an evening discussing the good old days when killing zombies was hard....Don't worry you have spent the day building and planting land mines around the 'target point' as the zombies pile up one on top of each other, World War Z has alot to answer for. Your mates wait for first light, then saunter out to blast the remaining ferals, help with clear up then all go back to ..... WHAT? That's the problem open world is great, craft building is standard. This is the problem it seems with the whole game.....nothing more nothing less...There comes a point whne you ask yourself 'Why am I doing this?'.To conclude, 7dtd is not finished. It is twirling in an indecisive twister, hovering in the middle of a desert, surrounded by the skulls of many other zombie titles, and blossoming oasis that have been poisoned by DLC day 1, early access swindlers, and greedy game house management. They hope to one day find the town of triple A game houses, to discover the handbook 'To write a game in a timely manner' with it's gate unlocking bonus of 'design-develope-test-refine-RELEASE WITH A GOAL!!!'. However for the moment, I feel it still can't work out where central is.Really hope that alpha 14 gives something..really hope that alpha becomes beta with some meat on the bones....really hope that this makes sense as playing 7dtd doesn't at the moment...."
