,Recommended,251570,8283646,"Posted: 25 December, 2013",all,ebachura,"Update: This review is old and out of date.  The cons have been fixed.Pros: Clean interface, decent gameplay, good zombie sounds, combat can be fun (pvp too).Cons: null reference exception error (related to graphics device perhaps) that happens to a lot of people when you hit tab to see the score (not every time, but often enough to be annoying) if it happens, you have to wait and hope it stops OR end process and rejoin (which ruins your score).  Maps get old (they never change, no randomness to them really).  The crafting, though nice, is really thin and gets old (especially since the most useful items are more easily found than crafted).Suggestions to developers: Fix the tab/score issue that makes playing impossible when it occurs.  If a game is set to any kind of PVP mode (deathmatch, or with PVP switched on) make it so no one else can see your spawn point (when you lay down a bed or sleeping bag) currently this KILLS pvp.  Also, players shouldn't be given player location info simply by typing lp (listplayers) in the command menu, that's game breaking for PVP.  Also, as a server admin/host, I find it incredibly annoying that you can't ban/kick people based on steam ID and are forced to do it based on name (which they can change and which DOES NOT work for names with spaces).This game has serious potential if they fix the issues listed above and continue to add content and features.  Hopefully I won't regret buying it."
