 decent I guess(had everything on max), my 770 wasn't able to push it 144fps though, I was mainly hovering around 60 to 70 on torched areas and 30-ish where torches are. SLi may have helped here but of course ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥nvidia disabled it for XP.Audio, now surround sound would definitely help here, it is after all a zombie survival horror game and you NEED and WANT to know exactly where zombies are coming from(and I guess to a point, where other playesr are coming from if you're playing on a PVP server), whether they are running to you from behind or quietly sneaking up(sneaky little ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s!) and give you a pre-emptive strike - yes I've had a few try this but luckily I look around the area whilst mining/cutting for stones and wood. So yeah, 7.1, 5.1, 4, you know the traditional way.As of this review, the game is only in stereo, yes I've got a monitor that tells me which speaker are in used and have sound coming out of and it's only the front left and right.Yeah...not bad I enjoyed the 9 hours I had before writing up this review.Now more quests and possibly some NPCs about in the world that give additional main/side quests would be nice(or you know a hide out like they do in State of Deacy where there's a group of survivors or a base where you need to periodically save from horse like the seventh day one....) - maybe there are but I haven't travelled far enough to have come across one. Those dogs are annoying, especially in packs! :POh yeah, left control doesn't work when I set it to couch, but it DOES work if I set it to toggle crouch - but I prefer to hold my crouch key when crouching and my preferred crouch key os of course left control. c works for both toggle and hold, no idea why - maybe bug? Oh yeah, there was a nother bug where I don't what I did, but whenn you press tab to show inventory, the console comes up instead and thus you can't access inventory or any of that stuff. So that's another bug to fix....But hey, unlike DayZ, you can actually hit zombies without a Fire axe! and you can't die from a ladder either heehee....Ah yes, perhaps add in a 3rd person view mode because it would be cool to see my character's worn stuff and all. ☺Seven days later and I still haven't managed to fix myself up with a gun or two and nice kelvar armor or something...hah. I died quite a few times, but they were due to stupid reasons: falling from height, bleeding/infection (I didn't and couldn't find any cure at the time), testing how strong my fists are against a horde of zombies, etc. hahahaOh just found out EasyAntiCheat (EAC)doesn't work onXP x64 Pro, lel - why are they even using this when VAC is availalble from Steam? So I guess I can't join any servers with EAC enabled....Also Steam overlay doesn't work so you can't take screenshots the traditional way....It would be nice if the temperate reading was in degrees C and not degrees F as some people here use C and not F....=====================================================Played on ""The Beast""i7-3970x, 64GB RAM, 2x GTX 770s 4GB VRAM, WinXP x64 Pro, 4x SSDs, 2x HDDs, Rampage IV Extreme, X-Fi Titanium Fatal1ty Pro, custom water loop, 2x BD-drives, TJ07-BW, 850W PSU, and many fans! Resolution: 1920x1080"
