76561198076326766,Recommended,251570,28094167,"Posted: 30 November, 2016",all,123,"Development is kinda slow, and it isnt the most graphically stunning game to come out, but this game has its own atmosphere and charm that just pulls you in. Though many other games have done what 7D2D has done, and it can be buggy, this game still manages to stand out on its own and be fun every time you pick it up. The zombies are actually terrifying at night, and the devs, though slowly, have made each update meaningful and ive seen no content added that I havent praised. The crafting system is superb, and I simply love how theyve implemented minecraft-esque terraforming and building, but yet the game doesnt look like a block building game. You can dig out the land, and it looks natural and clean, and farming is actually rewarding. It actually feels like a genuine survival game rather than just pvp like some survival sims, as finding good weapons and ammo, and even food, does take time and effort. Looking forward to seeing how this game fares in the future."
