76561198050807728,Recommended,251570,20371228,"Posted: 7 January, 2016",all,TheGrizzlyHusband,"7 Days to Die is the first game I think deserves a review from me. Playing the game now for more than 1.000 hours from before Alpha 9 onwards I first want to express my appreciation to the team of developers, they have done an exceptional job - so far.The game itself - a post apocalyptic survival sandbox single/multiplayer game combines everything I and my family enjoy in gaming, Zombies, gathering, building, strategy up to a certain degree, hunting, mining, looting, and so on. Ever increasing recipies for creating different levels of materials, food, health items and weaponry combined with the rather new decreasing properties of nearly everything you use and repair, stamina and temperature dependent performance of the character - that btw can be created and edited in so many ways that my wife said it's nearly a game in itself - give this game an ever so realistic feel when you're on the way through deserts, mountains, plains and woodlands, stumble into villages and cities or find lonely houses, gas stations and shops, libraries to learn skills, and so much more.Minecraft like building techniques with the possibility to mine and destroy every single bit but also with the option to upgrade the many derelict places add the right amount of destraction from the dogs, bears and zombies that will hunt you down that seem to become more and more quietly approaching with every update the Fun Pimps publish.I could go on for hours in describing the features of the game, in trying to explain how engaging it becomes while playing it, but to say it in a simple sentence: if you enjoy a bit of fighting, shooting, looting, hiding, learning, crafting, building, exploring alone or together with others then this is the game I will recommend to you. As I mentioned before, I do play more games, not just 7 Days to Die, but this game is the only one so far, that ""deserves a review"", and a positive one, from me. Anyway, one must not forget that it is an early access game and that there are bugs within it, most of them dissappear within hours or days, thanks to a huge community of players that reports such things straight away. And according to the developers the journey of creating this game is not over yet, so I expect quite a bit more to come in the near future."
