,Recommended,251570,13237471,"Posted: 5 December, 2014",all,timthepig,"Having played this for a considerable amount of time now on a dedicated server with friends.  This game now offers the scalability of Minecraft in terms of it's infinitely generated random world.  You can also expand on this generation by using prefabs (locations or points of interest) which can be found with a little googling.  This really makes the game much more expansive and fuller.The attention of detail in some the design features is excellent and the developers do listen to the community.  Such features include the plane supply drop which happens periodically randomly on the map, the zombies become stronger and faster at night, the building of forts and making sure the design of the defenses and barricades are solid, the disorientation of mining without a light, the horde that appears at midnight every 7th day....probably too much to put in this here ""review"".Having played the likes of Dayz, Nether, Warz (Infestation stories) and various other attempts at the survival genre.  This is the one in my opinion.  It feels like at times I could be playing Minecraft, Left 4 dead, Fallout and Dayz all at once.Vehicles are due soon.  This I imagine will catapult the game up there though now I feel this feature will become more essential with the more prefabs and infinitely randomly generated worlds.I've been thwarted by early access a few times.  This one I seem to have absolute confidence for,  Buy it."
