,Recommended,251570,10860976,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,JuanDiego Montoya,"This game is like Counter-Strike. You suck horribly for a long time at first, but then you eventually get a clue of what you're doing. Later you pick up even more clues and by that time it's all over and you've found all the clues. The end.DAE EDIT???!?Graphics-6/8 very good for a blocky-type game like this, but in the attempt to look realistic texture-wise, it looks low quality. The menus are pretty poopy looking, but I suspect that they could be easily changed to look beautiful. The unity 5  update looks promising to make shaders be awesome!Gameplay-6/8 very good for a blocky-type game like this, but in the attempt to be realistic gameplay-wise, they messed up on balancing quite a bit. For example, making guns as starting out is insanely hard. But, the second you find all the pieces to one gun you can EASILY make copious amounts of it. I mean, 1 iron ingot is enough for 3-5 parts of a gun, depending on the gun's rarity. That means you can potentially make 5 guns with 3 ingots of iron (once again, depending on the gun's rarity). Also, BULLETS. The moment you learn the crafting for bullets, you have a practically infinite supply as long as you have a small amount of lead (easy to find) and a little brass. With a little of each, one can make 500+ bullets with little effort. Once again, it seems that they will be changing the balancing a little in the upcoming unity 5 update."
