,Recommended,251570,12415945,"Posted: 8 October, 2014",all,James Elvin the Wetty Reposter,"I brought this game with two other friends and we had no idea how the game would be. It turned out to a extremely fun game to play and I find it unique compared to any other zombie survival/stranded survival game.What I find that makes the game fun is how hard it is. Most games today make the zombies really weak and really simple to survive. In 7 Day's To Die it is the complete opposite. A few hits from a zombie or a couple of bites from a dog and your dead. Food is hard to come by and water sources are usualy infected with bacteria/viruses. Building a house is time consuming and requires a lot of resources and you don't want to be hanging around outside during the night......If you build a base in the middle of nowhere thinking that you are safe, during the night (when zombies sprint) a group of thirty zombies will come charging at your house and break down your door!Everything is breakable and you can build anywhere. There are multiple biomes that are relatively huge and there are loads of zombie variants.Is it worth the money for the game in alpha? - Yes it is! Considering the game is still in a alpha state, there are tons of more updates and features to be added!"
,Recommended,251570,11961497,"Posted: 2 September, 2014",all,Intell289,"Ok so lets get started... I deleted my old review because it was me when I was like 10 years old and i know have a very different opinion about this gamePROS:The gameplay mechanics are a little odd but are easy to understand after an hour or so of playing the game.The crafting in this game is really cool. I like how you need schematics and other various items in this game like workbenches instead of instantly making whatever you want in the palm of your hand.The zombies are not too hard but not too easy (except on variable 7 days and nights).Cons:The building and upgrading of a base has a very, may I say, ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ system. I need to build frames, and then smack them with a hammer, until they can actually be used as walls.Zombies detect from too far awayI understand this is in the pre alpha/alpha stages, but I have a few problems with the fact its been in alpha stages for almost 3 years. But what really bothers me are the graphics. On the highest settings, this game just look sloppy, messy, and misplaced. The ground looks like a bunch of brown and green mashed together. The zombies have little to no gore/blood on them. The houses are just overdone when it comes to destruction. This is a zombie apocalypse survival, not a game part of the Fallout Series.Final Thoughts:It is a great game, and has great gameplay, but the graphics are just not to my liking. I understand its in alpha stages, but its still no excuse after 3 years. I would reccomend this game to anyone who like building a base to keep out zombies and setting badass traps to make sure they die. This game gets a 8/10. -1 for graphics -1 for goofy building system."
