,Recommended,251570,13420128,"Posted: 17 December, 2014",all,DEADPOOL,"*****UPDATEI've been playing this game for Years now... and just when you start to get bored with it then it releases something that makes it a WHOLE new game. The dev's have NOT let this game die and the new stuff they add every month or so just keeps the traing going. I can't wait to see what the finished product looks like. Amazing. Graphics enhanced... World Enhanced... My review below doesn't even scratch the serface of this game now. YOU NEED TO TRY IT!**********At first, I was very skeptial about this game, The graphics didn't look interesting... The game play looked weak... I love survival games and zombie games... It was on sale so I figured I would finallly give it a shot. Needless to say... I would've spent the 24.99. In this game, You have so much more to focus on then the way the ""Enviroment"" looks. You need to focus on your health... Hunger... Thirst... Make sur you dont get sick or break a leg because youll need to splint it for a few days.. youll need to check evey corner around you because you're never alone, You need to make sure you're hiddin at night because they will run... and they will find you. If you want to know where their time went with this game, It was the survival aspect, They did it deeper and more complex then any of the other survival games I've played.  EVERYTHING is a resource... Yeah, You need to do the basics of course... Cut down a tree... Mine some rocks... But after that is thousands of things to do... Eat a can of food, Us the Tin to make metal scraps, Turn all the metal scraps into rebar... Or smelt them down into iron ignots then into forged iron then rebar, then take some cobblestone, break it down into gravel, smash some stones up to get some cement mix it together to get some concrete mix, use those wood planks on your rebar blocks, pour in the concrete and let it sit for a few DAYS to dry then poof. Reinfoced Concrete Block. You'll need to make or find a shovel to dig, and a pick axe to mine. You can do it with anything but the specific tools work faster for specific jobs, You can just a shovel to break down a wooded door but a axe will work better. Wanna make some cabnets for your fort? Grab some logs, Make some planks, Dye the planks with wild flowers, turn them into counter blocks, find some cobble stone and make them counter top pieces, gravb a few more things and boom. Need a weapon to start the game? Find some bushed and get a good stick and grass ""Youll need grass to make twine"" find a stone and sharpen it, make an axe. Want something with range? Turn some logs into planks into sticks, get some twine and make yourself a crossbow. Needless to say, I owned this game for a week and have 40 hours in it already ""ontop of a 50 hour work week"". My friends now have coppies. This game is amazing."
