,Recommended,251570,14304242,"Posted: 2 February, 2015",all,Kompromised,"I played this game when it was just released onto the Steam Early Access and to be honest, I didn't think it had much potential in the already crowded ""Zombie/Survival, Open-World"" genre, competing against juggernauts like the DayZ stand-alone and RUST (both of which seem to have petered out in my opinion, with HEAVY emphasis on DayZ). I hated the boxy/voxel environment that was present in 7 Days to Die (not the way you build, because that is good that it is voxel based but the environment in the world was also boxy and voxel based and that I did not like). However they must have listened to their fanbase because the took that inspired ""minecraft"" rip-off, voxel based environment and threw it out the window.I logged into the game not to long ago after about a 12 month break from the game the my first thought was ""Am I playing the same game?"" It had been changed so much for the better that I didn't even recognize it. This is one of the best ""open-world zombie survival"" games I have ever played and I am so happy that they threw out the old game, went back to the drawing board and crafted a masterpiece that has really clawed, bit and scratched it's way through the some of the half-finished, trash with a ""zombie survival horror"" tag slapped on it, to get to the top of the pile and became one of the best in the genre.In reference to the game, unlike most in the genre, the Zombies/Walkers in this game are really something to be feared, especially in large numbers and has the game progresses its not uncommon to come across a horde that is 25, 50 even 100 strong and if you think your safe indoors inside that nice house you boarded up and fortified or the base you crafted yourself from the ground up...think again. If they see you through a window, if you step too loudly on a piece of wood or get their attention in any other way, they will rip your house board by board from the foundation to the roof to get to their next meal. Use the daytime hours to get what you need done because the night belongs to them. I have never felt the same feeling of dread that comes over you when you hear the moans and the scratches of a horde that has you trapped in the building that you thought was safe, in any other game besides this one (and Project Zomboid, also another great zombie survival game).Beyond the main antagonist of the game, the walkers, you are also contending with the threat of disease, infection and your own hunger and thirst that needs to be managed constantly otherwise a slow death is all you'll have to look forward to and it often seemed that I was always one meal away from wasting away until the universe shined a light on me and I came across a deer or a wild pig that gave me life for another day.All and all, I believe that this game is one of the best early access games available on Steam and absolutely the best in it's genre and as always, it's more enjoyable online with friends."
