76561198104040378,Recommended,251570,19724313,"Posted: 15 December, 2015",all,Pneumo,"If you have nearly given up on the survival genre, i dont blame you... However, 7days to die isnt to be overlooked, and you wont be left with an unfinished nor be wasting your money.---The short version to this review is simply 'BUY THIS GAME' - (and not because i'm like a giggling schoolgirl with a crush on the weiner justin beiber- but because ...-Read the long version....********The long version********I've owned this game for around about a year or so, and bit by bit, i've been watching it go through its changes, as alphas do... Unlike most of the others in this genre, its kept with its original plans, and the developers have continued on, listening to the community, taking constructive critisism on the chin, even asking for others to point out its flaws, and addressing them when they get through other bugfixes and updates, evn managing to squish them into spaces where there werent gaps... so have no fear of throwing your hard earned cash at this game...To explain, 7days to die, is, as it states, a zombie survival game... but there are few, or if not none, that manage to feel like an actual zombie survival. I've played many survival games in the past, but none do it quite like this one- heres how it does it:-* You can start off, either within mulitplayer games, as with most or rather all survival games, OR you can play solo, in either a randomly generated/standard map.* You are placed randomly within a HUGE map and left with a bottle of boiled water, a can of chilli in a can, and a few basic bandages. ...and no clothes. (??) ...and then, its all up to you.** You will be, as you'd expect with a zombie survival- literally scavenging what you can, when you can, from wherever you can- Within abandoned cars, trash cans, cardboardboxes, houses, warehouses, nature itself, built up towns, ruined cities (...kinda bigger towns, rather than cities, but i believe thats what they're referred to as) ...these places are usually more populated with zombies and, even if you chose (within the options upon creating a new game....) to set spawn rate to low, theyre persistant, and it only gets harder, the more noise you make, the more you kill....you'll eventually have to run away and wait til they forget about you.*** Since the recent update (Dec 2015) theres been a thourough introduction of the RPG ish system- of which, you level up by gaining experience by doing all sorts of things, crafting, hunting, scavenging, digging etc, and at the same time as gaining experience, individual skills also gain experience... whereas when you level up, you are given a few skill points to add to the already gaining skills... blunt weapons, ranged, making weapons , crafting armour, crafting blocks etc... which has made the game even more in depth (even after i recently allowed myself to use the creative tools after many hours of play beforehand), ive now stopped since the update and started fresh, to play all over agin... as the level up system has only recently properly came into working order) ... also, as your crafting skills get better, you'll be able to craft higher ranking/teir weapons- which are shown by a colour coded system/better stats.**** Food and water is found by scavenging or taking from nature, hunting pigs, deer, rabbits, bears and chickens, also, you can, after making a safe location, begin to plant your own xrops after finding the seeds in the wild, or after eating vegetables or cutting down trees, cacti, and other vegetation...***** The building blocks come in many usueful and decorative forms, inner and outer walls and flooring, placed in a 'minecraft-esque manner, of literally nice looking blocks, but if youre against minecraft, then dont be worried, they dont look atall like simply coloured lego bricks that are clearly reconised as black outlined cartoony squares. ...on the flipside of building upward, you can dig undergorund, and unlike its block counterparts, they dont dig up as squares, moreso like a cubed netting, that you cant see due to the nicely blended layers of different resource types, that all can be used in some form of crafting, ie- sand to glass, stone within cement- withinside reinforced rebar walls etc. ...so you can build networking tunnels and that 'nice log cabin' ...with kitchen and sofa... underground...with traps...****** The graphics can be wound all the way up, or all the way down, and at maximum, if you can, it will stand its ground quite easily with all of the rest. Daytime nightime blend nicely, and depending on the visual settings that you've chosen, can have some very nice, and also a very chilling and lifelike feel at night.******* The zombies have recently had a visual and physical change, their movements have been made quite freaky, and they look all rotten and weird, as you'd expect... - you can change to if they can run or not (mines set to not run for a classic zombie affect... ....and that i dont want them to... because... you know...) ...their aggresion levels etc, which all work in tune with their senses... meaning that they can smell you (that 'chilli in a can' you start with- sort of sense you...) along with food that upsets your stomache because you've eaten raw meat or a stale sandwich, or a bit of fresh killed or cooked meat... your footsteps, rustling through bushes, jumping, shooting or being alerted by other zombie moans when they see you....brilliant.******** Whilst within a zombie horde, expect to be cut and begin to bleed out, become infected, stunned (just the same as you can stun or knock over zombies) or killed, ...or possibly die of dehydration or starvation... mauled by a bear, set on fire, or just the standard 'dig ungerground and forget gravity exists and have it all collopse ontop of you.To conclude, 7 days to die is worth the money, whatever price it is. The developers arent running off with your cash, theyre using it to fund progress, pure and simple... and even if tomorrow they hypothetically all gave up, your money STILL wont have been wasted.I cant imagine what the final game will be like upon completion, but i look forward to finding out whole heartedly. You will not be dissappointed.P.s - spelling and grammar maynot be perfect, i'm currently playing 7days to die, safe and secure whilst i wait for daylight in game... i dont like being chased in the dark by zombie dogs. (also, that may sound like daylight takes forever to come around, but ive got it all set to longest night/day duration...10/10 ...would hide at night and write reviews whilst periodically checking back again ...you know, just incase.DEV BLOG:http://joelhuenink.tumblr.com/"
