,Recommended,251570,20052951,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,Blind Captain,"I think I got the game about a year ago as early access and for the sale price I paid, I would have been happy for what I got. Except, in this case, the developers remain pretty active. In that time, I can't really think of an aspect of the game that has gone untouched. This plays with substantial depth as a survival game and also has the whole zombie element. Apparently a lot more will be coming. There are many things to craft and collect, hunting, mining, survival, skills, levelling, and a very big world.My main complaint is that sometimes the zombie aspect takes away from the game since it is done in too fake and cheesy of a way. The weapons don't feel especially unique since zombies generally take an absurd about of hits unless it's in the face and even then it may take more than one. This really takes a lot of the excitement and realism out of the accomplishment of upgrading from say a stone axe to a 768mm sniper rifle. Additionally, some of them feel almost cartoon-like. One of the hardest zombies is a fat police officer that will burp up a green corrosive liquid to like 100 feet away. Whenever that happens (usually a severe situation) it just completely ruins my immersion with how ridiculous it is. Meanwhile, many of the others (screeching zombie, dog zombie) are done in a way that better fits the ""survival horror"" vibe this game otherwise seems to be going for.Also, a general disclaimer, while in early access, every version number bump, your save games will break. So, a v13.1 save will work on v13.2, but not v14. This is an understandable limitation but can be upsetting if you create something very substantially."
