76561198025838739,Recommended,251570,8912926,"Posted: 30 January, 2014",all,Redderik,"It's Minecraft meets Walking Dead. I was intrigued and despite the hefty Alpha price, I took a gamble. I've put a bunch of hours and have played 21 in game days with 50 minute days. Here's where I'm at. The game has tons of potential. It is clear where they want it to go. You can pretty much build everything you see and  you have the classic gather, build, defend strategy with the harrassment of the ever present threat. The fast/slow zombies really add a dynamic of play as well.  ( I prefer slow zombies, they continously lull you into not taking them as a serious threat until the mobs shows up and you realize you underestimated the threat, lol)There is a long way to go, some features are not working yet (cooking with pots and stoves), movement issues, like zombies that hop around or jump impossibly high walls when they bump into them, and tons of wish list items, like crafting ""max"" or specific numbers of things. While the crafting is much more intuitive than minecraft, it's far from ""completely intuitive"" such as stew if the ingrediants are not in the right order they will not combine, etc.The self sustaining options and balanced dehydration, hunger aspects work well, as said, lots of potential for the ""next minecraft""  I'll reserve my recommendation to others until it's fully BETA, you pretty much have to love sandbox and troubleshooting to bother buying it now, don't spend this money thinking it's a full game, you'll be frustrated, and understandbly at $35. So far I have no regrets."
