,Recommended,251570,33090147,Posted: 1 July,all,MechMK1,"About the Game7 Days to Die is a self-titled ""Survival Horde Crafting Game"", which is pretty suitable.The core gameplay consists of scavenging items from various places such as gun-, hardware- or book-stores, building a base and defending it from zombies.Every 7th day, a ""blood moon"" occurs, which summons ferral zombies non-stop all night. Your goal is to build a base and weapons to defend against this horde.Additionally, the game has a perk system, which gives you slight bonuses the more you use a certain class of items (e.g. mining tools work more efficiently, blunt weapons deal more damage, etc.). The perk system is also used to gate certain materials and recipes, so players can't build the most powerful tools right away (e.g. stone tools first, then iron, then steel, etc...)TechnicalThe games technical implementation is mediocre. It's not terrible, but for the level of graphical fidelity, the performance is sub-par. On a rather good machine (i7-6700K, GTX 980 Ti), with high settings, I sometimes get frame drops down to 30 FPS, which won't go back up to 60 until I close the game and reload it.Of course, the game is playable most of the time - just don't expect the most polished experience here.The DefaultsMy biggest complaint of this title are the default settings. In all honesty, a loot respawn time of 30 days is just...not fun. Really, if you loot a gun store at your first day and get a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ lv. 6 pistol grip, you won't be able to loot it again until you're lv. 120 and are basically a walking death machine.Yes, you can set these options to a more sane number (like 5 days), but newer players either won't know this or say ""The game is supposed to be like this"" and then end up having a bad time. And you know, we're here to have a good time.Early AccessThe game is still in early access and active development. This comes with several pro's and con's attached. On the positive side, the game is being improved with every update. Just with the recent Alpha 16 update, the game got nice things like an automatic marker for your bike.Of course, this also means that the information on the Wiki will often be outdated and that any guide you will find may or may not accurately reflect what the game is like right now.Will I have fun with this game?I'd answer this question with ""Yes, if..."".If you are willing to put up with the game's rather steep learning curve and don't have a problem with dying a few times in the beginning, just to learn the basics, then you will likely have fun here.If you dislike the idea of dying because you just had bad luck or because the game failed to tell you vital information, then I suggest you not to play this game, at least not in its current state (Alpha 16.1)"
