,Not Recommended,251570,33574145,Posted: 15 July,all,Raunchy Potato,"Summary:Even for an early access game, this is in an unacceptably buggy and unoptimized state.  It has potential, there are good ideas behind it, and the devs update it regularly; but the updates do not address the key shortcomings of the game.Pros:-- Deep crafting system with a lot of options-- World generation give you lots of room to explore, mine, loot, etc-- Passable shooting controlsCons:-- Repeated bugs that cause you to have to sign out and sign back in to get rid of them (at best) or will persist until they cause something in the game to kill you (at worst)-- Awful optimization, requiring at least 16 gigs of RAM to run at anything resembling acceptable quality-- Requires far more system resources than games that look (and play) far superior to itOf all of the crafting-zombie-survival games on here, this is one of the deeper and more interesting ones.  However, its devs seem to have far more passion for designing than they do for optimization.  No game with PS2-era poly counts, prodecuarlly generated worlds, and such basic AI should require this much system resources to run.  And as they keep adding more and more into the game, it looks like it's only going to get worse.  If they don't address this issue soon, don't expect this game to ever leave early access."
