,Recommended,251570,13778968,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,5 Year Old Fugitive,"7 Days to DieAn early access survival zombie apocalypse game, with extensive crafting.GAMEPLAYCraftingCrafting in this game is very extensive. You can make almost everything to your desire, if you have the materials to do so. You can find special books that when you read them, you learn more crafting recipes. If you find a generic book, you don't learn anything. You can only turn the generic book into paper. You can find blueprints to learn more about guns and their recipes. You can make a campfire and cook food. The forge however, requires the ""Forge Ahead"" book.TerrainYou can set the terrain generation to Random or Navezgane. The game name influences the random generation, like in Minecraft with the seeds. When set to Navezgane, it creates a world that is always the same. Navezgane in the basically the world that gives the game a storyline about the apocalypse. There are many biomes to explore, from Radiation Zones to Forests.Loot60% of the time you find useless junk unless you have a Forge. The rest of the loot is food, clothing, drinks, weapons, and other USEFUL stuff. This ties in well with the Crafting because almost everything you find can be turned into something else. The game has a Airdrop option, which you can change the intervals between the airdrops. Airdrops will have extremely useful stuff, such as medical supplies and weapon blueprints.ZombiesZombies during the day aren't so bad. They move slow, don't agro easily, and don't deal much damage. Day and night both feature Zombie Dogs, which are ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s because they kill you easily, and move fast! Zombies and Dogs have many ways to sense and track you down. If you have meat on you, zombies can smell you from a distance. They can hear you access chests, campfires, forges, inventories, and pretty much everything. At night, the zombies traverse the world, in huge packs, have increased damage, have Sanic speed, and have increased sensing abilities. My advice is to build or fortify a house, and crouch to wait out the night.WIldlifeThere are animals that can be hunted and killed. They drop useful meats, animal fat, bones, and animal skins. This also ties well into Crafting because when you use the Leather Tanning book, you learn to craft animal hide/skin/whatever into Leather which can be crafted into Armor. Zombies will also track down and kill animals too.CharactersWHOA WHAT?! Yes, you can create your own character and customize him or her. :DServersYou can contact a hosting service and rent a server, or portforward your router to allow private computer hosting. You can also enable antihack and a password.7 Days to Die is really a great game, if you have a group of friends and want to survive in a semi-hardcore apocalypse game, purchase this game. This game is also on♥♥♥♥♥♥♥available for low prices! And yes I said ""semi-hardcore' survival because zombies are tough, but you can respawn.Final Score:8.5/10Since this game is in early access, you should expect a few bugs. Bugs are minimal however."
