,Recommended,251570,8564071,"Posted: 4 January, 2014",all,Spotter,"For those who enjoy Minecraft, Terraria, Day Z, Left 4 Dead, and Dead Island, this game brings a great blend of all such games. Though it's only in its Alpha stage, it already had a broad range for its gameplay.At its default, you really feel like you're fighting to survive in a post-apocalyptic world with Minecraft powers. Unlike games like Day Z, these zombies come in a large variety and run only in darkness, making night time truly frightening.Most other zombie games I've played allow zombie to break through preset areas, but in 7D2D, zombies can literally attack you from every angle and break through every defense with enough time.Even if you're well protected in a solid underground bunker, it's unsettling and down-right creepy how quickly the zombies arrive at your door at night, and how loudly the make their presence known while trying to smash their way in.Thankfully, it's not just the walls that keep the zombies away; 7D2D grants you the ability to craft a wide variety of defenses and basic necessities to survive, all from cooked food and beds to shotguns and spike pits.My main problem with this game is just how buggy it can be, but I understand it's still just in its Alpha phase, so that's easy to forgive."
