,Recommended,251570,10887488,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,JackFunk,"First off.  This is an early access game, but it is in solid shape.  The features that are there work well.Now, to the gameplay.  This is a survival game and it is tough, but fair.  You will die.  Often at first.  Exploration is necessary, as you need food, water and weapons.  The map is large and varied enough to make exploration interesting.  The combat is straight forward and reasonably challenging, but not overwhelming.  The crafting system is great.  There are a large variety of items that you can craft, from weapons to storage and building components.  You can build structures from a number of materials and construct many different defensive items.  You can mine for resources and use a forge to refine these into crafing materials.It is a lot of fun to play cooperatively.  My son and I have been building up an outpost, fending off zombies, and experimenting with the crafting system.  Once you really start crafting, the game becomes a lot more fun and the zombies much easier to deal with.As the game stands today, it is worth picking up.  I look forward to future updates that add even more features."
