76561198017612116,Recommended,251570,18588231,"Posted: 20 October, 2015",all,virtualsalvation,"If you enjoy survival crafting games you will most likely enjoy this one.* Mining: Mine, harvest or scavenge materials to craft stuff. Chop trees, mine below ground, break rocks.* Crafting: Craft tools, weapons, food or building materials. You can even craft a minibike with some effort.* Survival: Hunger, thirst and of course Zombies. Weather survival also coming in the next release.* Building: Build small shelters or huge bases above and below ground. Not like MC since there is structural integrity (SI) so you can't build something that would fall down in real life.* Multiplayer: Play on PVE or PVP servers. There are griefers on both but not as many as Rust or some other games. On PVP it is pretty much fair game, however on PVE it is pretty lame. From my experience it is not as bad as Rust or some other games in this genre.* Community: Active community playing and discussing the game. Devs are also active on the boards but not everyone likes everything they have to say. Most of the complaints are from people who don't feel ""heard"" or feel a response was rude although they seem far more active than most games though and respond to many questions or comments.* Audience: This game is targeted more at the 20-60yr old crowd. Mature content and not much tolerance for script kiddies or hackers. Exploits are patched fairly often and hackers are frequently banned.I do highly recommend this game but it could change significantly like any EA game. I already have gotten my money's worth many times over and every release has improved things but you never know. That said, if you like survival crafting games this one is definitely at or near the top. For zombie survival games it is hands-down the best. Just look at how many hours people have played (including those that gave negative reviews). It is addicting and those hours are not becaue you have to put in that much, but because you want to."
