76561197994996821,Recommended,251570,16941226,"Posted: 8 July, 2015",all,Septema,"Early Access- Alpha 12.4First off, this is an alpha access review so keep that in mind.  If you want a solid, never changing, completely fleshed out game, you aren't getting one.  It's changing and evolving constantly at this point as new features are added and old ones are tweaked based on the feedback from players and ideas the developers have.You are the survivor of an apocalypse event and if you wish to stay surviving, you better play smart.  If you think this is the walking dead where zombies will die if you make a mean face at them, you're doomed.  You are the one who dies easily.  You can starve, you can dehydrate, you can bleed out, you can fall, etc.  If you want to survive, be sneaky.  Don't try to fight the zombie horde, it will overcome you unless you are heavily armed and adequately prepared.  Learn when to fight versus when to run.  Find or make a decent overnight spot where you can hide like a mouse until dawn!  Hunt, scavenge, craft, fight, and hide.  Do it all, and maybe you will be the one who finds the cause and solution to the zombie apocalypse (story not implemented yet, though).The learning curve on this game is sharp and if you want victory handed to you, you should just move on to another game.  This one makes you work for it.Pros-The devs work on this game.  A lot.  Plenty of major and minor changes being made fairly often.Survival is a priveledge, not a right!  You WILL die.  A LOT!  Accept this now and you can enjoy the game.  If you don't, you will hate this game.These aren't the zombies from The Walking Dead.  You aren't going to stick one once with a dull stick and kill it.  They are already dead and pushing them further into fully dead isn't always that easy.  Junk weapons only irritate them and make them hungrier.  Better weapons work much better and you can kill with one hit with a decent weapon.Crafting is life.  You must craft whatever you need to survive.  You can find some functional items, but most finds are parts used to craft.You can fight or sneak by most monsters, but fighting can get you killed, sneaking can get you...closer to more zombies with the ones you snuck by still behind you so know when to fight and when not to.Visually, the game has improved exponentially from when I first tried it.  Now, trees look awesome, dirt looks like dirt, etc.  Way back when, everything was black silhouttes.  There's still room to improve though.The atmosphere is creepy.  A zombie coming around a corner suddenly and slapping you will make you jump back in your chair.  A horde of zombies chasing you at night will definately let you know if you have a heart condition.Cons-The devs work on this game.  A lot.  Changes occur fairly often, and sometimes completely alter the game.  You can get used to playing a set way and then an update changes AI behavior or spawn rates or loot, etc.  You have to be adaptable and some people find this a problem.Death can happen quickly and it can be painful to recover the  lost stats, so play smart to avoid the penalty.You start with almost nothing, which can be problematic when you encounter your first zombie and have no weapon....Single player can become rather tiresome once you have a safehouse, decent gear and weapons and little else to look forward too until story mode is implemented.Bugs and glitches.  It's alpha so expect them.  I haven't had many bugs since alpha 12 was implemented but other people claim to have encountered tons.  You might be on one spectrum or the other.  There are a number of graphical glitches but the devs do seem to work on them so every update makes for better and smoother visuals.Gathering items is the main pastime in this game at this point.  You will need to do it often to amass enough resources to do what you want.  Finding recipes can be challenging and some recipes make or break your gameplay.Zombies can break stone.  You make a decent, solid base out of concrete and zombies will still eventually break in unless you repair the damage they do.  I can't see a human breaking ithrough a 3 foot thick concrete wall regardless how many times they punch it, but these zombies can.The crafting interface isn't exactly the easiest to navigate through if you don't know what you want to make.  Some items are fairly self-evident such as clothing but cloth scraps...what are cloth scraps under?  If you don't know where to find a recipe, it can be a pain to search each type if you aren't sure what the recipe is named.  You can craft by finding the item name and just clicking it or you can place the items in the interface in the proper location and craft it that way.All things considered, this is one of the better survival horror titles out now and even as early access delivers a better game than many of todays fully released versions of other survival horror titles.  If you want a challenging game where you know you worked to survive, this is the one you waited for."
