ue, giving you headaches for days trying to manually fix the crap that developers couldnt make right from the start.Anyway, i wouldnt recommend the game if you would like to enjoy a game that works. This sure doesnt work. If you can see past several major issues, i would recommend getting it. Its alot of fun for about a week and if you are the kind of person who can replay games, you can get a ton of fun out of it. Just be aware that eventually, this game is going to die on you, since there is no endgame or any real point of the game (That you cant find in MInecraft or similar)"
