,Not Recommended,251570,34405408,Posted: 21 August,all,Fawkzi,"Wasted potential in an everlasting alpha (It's been in alpha for four years)When this game first hit I loved it. I used to play it with my buddy. Back then it was pretty basic in comparison to what it is now, it lacked some serious content but it was still fun to hop in and waste some time and at least the game actually ran properly back then.Frame rate dropping as low as 10fps, Audio Log.txt errors that pop up near constantly and get you killed since all control of your character ceases when these messages pop up and the whole Nullexception error messages too (These come and go at random from rare to every few seconds) it seems like the bugs have just gotten worse the further development goes and judging by the dates of forum posts in my quests to fix these bugs some of these issues date back almost two years.This game is also for the hardcore and I mean the 'hardcore' as in those who just want to be punished near constantly. I'm no stranger to difficulty and survival but this game goes at it a little too hard in the strangest of ways. You're in a zombie apocalypse but the zombies don't feel like a threat and are easily killed, animals however? One hit kills for days when you're a fresh level 1 just starting out. These animals murder you in an instant and you can't do a damn thing about it.I mean I get a horde of zombies tearing you to shreds if you let them box you in, the counter to it is to not let them box you in, Hell I even get the roaming, starving animals attacking your fresh meat looking self on sight but instantly killing you just because you're low level is a bit much, it feels like the game just demoralizes you before you have the chance to delve deeper in to the various systems on offer.The forge (Something you'll use alot) is also broken. Here's an example. To craft an Anvil you need Iron so you go out and collect Iron but apparently even when gettng 200 Iron you don't have any Iron (Acording to the forge) But there's an option to craft The Iron you need but in order to craft the Iron you need...you need to use the Iron you need. You need to use the Iron you need to craft the Iron you need to craft an Anvil and IT STILL SAYS YOU HAVE NO IRON. Broken af.It's not all bad though, the aforementioned systems are pretty damn good. You have your standard fare with crafting, eating, drinking (No sleeping though which is weird) Tending to your wounds and various ailments,infections,fractures and all sorts. I -love- these things but it's annoying as hell when all of my survival progress is ruined by some skinny looking starving dog killing me in an instant and seeing as they both spawn and attack you out of nowhere with only the growl that says 'It's too late, I'm right behind you' as a warning it gets too much too fast.The addition of animals in itself is wonderful. Getting to hunt, kill, gather and survive in more ways than just looking inside containers is awesome.I say get this if you don't mind the things I've mentioned above but bare in mind this is in alpha and I don't say that as in 'Forgive the bugs, it's only an alpha' I say this as in 'It's been four damn years and it's still in alpha with bugs that have existed for just as long'I personally can't reccomend it as a must buy in the current state of the game."
