,Recommended,251570,9366549,"Posted: 6 March, 2014",all,Warman,"I have to say, I did not expect this game to be that good.  It looked a little bit corny from the trailer and I only considered buying it after my friends exclaimed how amazing it was.The most amazing thing about this game are the zombies.  They pose a REAL threat and will stop at nothing to eat your brains.  Some of the most terryfing moments I have had in a zombie game have came from 7 Days to Die.  For example,  me and my brother attempted to build an underground base right in the middle of the main city.  It was going fine until night came.  The zombie horde ravenously dug through the dirt trying to reach us.  We thought we were safe 10 levels beneath the surface. They continued each and every night for 3 nights until they finally broke through.  When that one little hole was made, we were screwed.  They flooded in and quickly killed us.  We attempted to rebuild and even make a trench filled with spikes, but alas it just slowed them down.  Eventually, we had to abandon our underground home, leaving the tattered ruins as its legacy.I really wish I had been recording during these moments.  The AI + voxel based enviornment in this game give you something I have never experienced in a game thus far.  It is just awe striking when you witness the damage the horde can do to the enviornment or your own base.Additonally, the survival system is one of the best I have seen.  Finding food and water is an everday struggle when you first start.  The crafting system has also been rewarding to me.  I hope in the future they add more items and maybe more materials but as of right now I do not have much to complain about.  I will try to upload some pictures to this review (if I can) or to my Steam profile for those interested.In conclusion,  go get this game!"
