,Recommended,251570,9905327,"Posted: 22 April, 2014",all,Muuski,"I was introduced to this game by a youtube channel called Mack's Corner. I'm glad Mack has shown quite a few videos of this, because I love the game.While the zombie genre is not lacking in games, as they are being produced like Hollywood Blockbusters at the moment. A majority of them are god awful(I won't mention any names). This game succeeds where they go wrong. It blends things together so well. For an alpha, I was surprised at how good the gameplay was; the building, crafting and combat elements are fantastic. What this game is best for though, is atmosphere. You find zombies becoming more aggressive during the night, so you have to ensure you lock yourself away and build defenses or a house, while being chased by dozens of zombies. And believe me, when it's in the pitch black with the moon shining down with horrific zombie noises, it's pretty tense.The multiplayer is great, still needs a bit of work. But I've met some great people, as a whole the community seems great.There are some hiccups, such as frame rate issues, bugs such as floating trees and my backpack clipping into in the terrain and not being able to search it. But it's an alpha for God's sake what do you expect?This is one of the best purchases I've made, the developers have great contact with the community and release regular updates. May not appeal to all, but in my opinion this game is worth it's 18.99.Good Stuff!"
