76561197964373272,Recommended,251570,9116214,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,Ninjazz,"I'm not quite sure what the deal is with all the negative reviews, so I thought I'd chip in my own.First and foremost everyone, keep in mind this game is an ALPHA. It's not even to the stage of Beta yet, yet the game is a lot of fun and is only going to be getting better.There are many good and bad points to list so I'll just start make a list of points here:The GOOD-- Gameplay is fun- The zombies present a very real challenge- The physics engine and gravity make for an interesting challenge- Multiplayer Works Well- COOP!The BAD-- Some hacker/Griefer issues- Placeholder Graphics (for now)- Zombies can be annoyingly noisy- Server Admins need better tools- Some glitches/bugs and optimization stuff etc (It's an alpha)Overall I'm having a blast with the game. It plays well, it's fun, and it's a CHALLENGE, at least compared to a lot of the competition out there right now.The zombies can tear through nearly anything eventually, meaning you need to keep a vigil on your base to keep it from eventually collapsing. (Or be cheap and try to take advantage of a couple of well known exploits)You won't be building bases in the sky, because there's this funny thing called gravity...Oh, and it's dangerous to go out at night. Seriously, not a good idea.The crafting system, while rough, is quite impressive. Multiplayer games is really a joy, getting in a working with others to setup a base, or even town, together.There's PVP too, but only if the server has the function enabled. The game is really intended to be played coop.The graphics are so-so, but most of them are just temporary place-holders while the devs work to get all the background stuff working first, and then will later try to make it look prettier. (You know, doing the actual important stuff first, the way it should be done.) The lighting and things though are top notch. Despite the loaner graphics things look pretty nice overall.A lot of people give the game crap because of it's price. $35? Is that really so bad? I mean, sure it's more than minecraft or Rust, but it's still a long ways away from that $50-$60 for most AAA titles, and I've spent a lot more time enjoying this than most any AAA in recent memory. Plus you're supporting an indie developer that has no big publisher lording over them.So really, I always hear people complain about the price of the game, but they're comparing it to cheap titles, and not to computer games in general. All in all, it's up to you whether you think it's worth the price tag or not, I've not regretted buying it myself.Overall,The game is still in Alpha, and there's already so much fun to be had with it, most any of the problems (except the occasional hacker or griefer on public servers) are pretty minor. I've played most of the big name survival games coming up, Rust, Nether, etc. and this has so far been my favorite. I'm very excited to see where the devs take this from here on."
76561198001476196,Recommended,251570,9119851,"Posted: 15 February, 2014",all,Sanity'sEdge,"This is kind of a review, but foremost a reply to TeeJaxOff's review:TeeJaxOff's review is based on Alpha 4 (or maybe an early Alpha 5 version), but now the game is in Alpha 6 (almost 7 from what I read on the official forums. so much for updates getting in too slow.). It looks much better now, new biomes were implemented, the crafting system got an overhaul, and many more stuff was changed, added or fixed. Also I never encountered performance issues (i5 2500k+, gtx760, 8GB RAM, Win7), apart from one time when there were many, many zombies around tearing at my base, when also the roof (and it was a very big roof) came down on me, only then I experienced lag. The Hiding System isn't implemented yet, but it will. To a degree zombies already react to sound, but the problem that Zombies find you everywhere isn't that bad anymore. As for the no chance when the zombie horde comes: It is somewhat supposed to be that way. You scavenge during daytime and hide through the night, else you are in serious trouble, but that I consider to be fun part of the game. If you are out, far away from your base and you realize you won't make it back in time, you look for an abandoned building and build some makeshift fortifications (grab anything, chairs, tear down walls,...barricade the entrances and hide under the roof until it's day again). I find this review to be unfair and incorrect. There are issues, but it is an alpha, not even beta, so that is perfectly normal. The communication between the staff and the alpha testers/customers is in need of improvement, but it also isn't as bad as TeeJaxOff makes it sound like. Yes, he writes that he has no doubt that this game can be good one day, but nonetheless due to his review there will be many people who won't even consider giving the game a chance. It reads like this is one of the worst products of all times and this is far from truth. This is a great game, with even more potential, despite it's current flaws. It could be even better by now, but not with such a small staff (speaking of, they should hire 2-3 more people imo). Yes the price is set too high and it should be lower while it is in alpha/beta, but noone is forcing you to buy it at this price at the present development stage. Give it a try now, but realize that it is an unfinished product or wait until it's finished and then maybe take a second look, and then I'm pretty sure that you wouldn't believe that this game and the game in the review by TeeJaxOff could be the same.I recommend the game, though I know that it isn't finished and there is still alot missing, but I also know that this game will kick♥♥♥♥♥when it's done (and it's great fun even at this stage). Also I'm anxiously awaiting Alpha 7, wich will also give the game better textures and some terrain-improvement (a little less blocky ;) ), also the Hiding-System should be in then, which would be awesome (though if it's not, no big deal, it's done when it's done)."
